71namespace {

73class MipsAssemblerOptions {
74public:
75 MipsAssemblerOptions(const FeatureBitset &Features_) : Features(Features_) {}
76
77 MipsAssemblerOptions(const MipsAssemblerOptions *Opts) {
78 ATReg = Opts->getATRegIndex();
79 Reorder = Opts->isReorder();
80 Macro = Opts->isMacro();
81 Features = Opts->getFeatures();
82 }
83
84 unsigned getATRegIndex() const { return ATReg; }
85 bool setATRegIndex(unsigned Reg) {
86 if (Reg > 31)
87 return false;
88
89 ATReg = Reg;
90 return true;
91 }
92
93 bool isReorder() const { return Reorder; }
94 void setReorder() { Reorder = true; }
95 void setNoReorder() { Reorder = false; }
96
97 bool isMacro() const { return Macro; }
98 void setMacro() { Macro = true; }
99 void setNoMacro() { Macro = false; }
100
101 const FeatureBitset &getFeatures() const { return Features; }
102 void setFeatures(const FeatureBitset &Features_) { Features = Features_; }
103
104 // Set of features that are either architecture features or referenced
105 // by them (e.g.: FeatureNaN2008 implied by FeatureMips32r6).
106 // The full table can be found in MipsGenSubtargetInfo.inc (MipsFeatureKV[]).
107 // The reason we need this mask is explained in the selectArch function.
108 // FIXME: Ideally we would like TableGen to generate this information.
109 static const FeatureBitset AllArchRelatedMask;
110
111private:
112 unsigned ATReg = 1;
113 bool Reorder = true;
114 bool Macro = true;
115 FeatureBitset Features;
116};
117
118} // end anonymous namespace
119
120const FeatureBitset MipsAssemblerOptions::AllArchRelatedMask = {
121 Mips::FeatureMips1, Mips::FeatureMips2, Mips::FeatureMips3,
122 Mips::FeatureMips3_32, Mips::FeatureMips3_32r2, Mips::FeatureMips4,
123 Mips::FeatureMips4_32, Mips::FeatureMips4_32r2, Mips::FeatureMips5,
124 Mips::FeatureMips5_32r2, Mips::FeatureMips32, Mips::FeatureMips32r2,
125 Mips::FeatureMips32r3, Mips::FeatureMips32r5, Mips::FeatureMips32r6,
126 Mips::FeatureMips64, Mips::FeatureMips64r2, Mips::FeatureMips64r3,
127 Mips::FeatureMips64r5, Mips::FeatureMips64r6, Mips::FeatureCnMips,
128 Mips::FeatureFP64Bit, Mips::FeatureGP64Bit, Mips::FeatureNaN2008
129};

425
426 // Selects a new architecture by updating the FeatureBits with the necessary
427 // info including implied dependencies.
428 // Internally, it clears all the feature bits related to *any* architecture
429 // and selects the new one using the ToggleFeature functionality of the
430 // MCSubtargetInfo object that handles implied dependencies. The reason we
431 // clear all the arch related bits manually is because ToggleFeature only
432 // clears the features that imply the feature being cleared and not the
433 // features implied by the feature being cleared. This is easier to see
434 // with an example:
435 // --------------------------------------------------
436 // | Feature | Implies |
437 // | -------------------------------------------------|
438 // | FeatureMips1 | None |
439 // | FeatureMips2 | FeatureMips1 |
440 // | FeatureMips3 | FeatureMips2 | FeatureMipsGP64 |
441 // | FeatureMips4 | FeatureMips3 |
442 // | ... | |
443 // --------------------------------------------------
444 //
445 // Setting Mips3 is equivalent to set: (FeatureMips3 | FeatureMips2 |
446 // FeatureMipsGP64 | FeatureMips1)
447 // Clearing Mips3 is equivalent to clear (FeatureMips3 | FeatureMips4).
448 void selectArch(StringRef ArchFeature) {
449 MCSubtargetInfo &STI = copySTI();
450 FeatureBitset FeatureBits = STI.getFeatureBits();
451 FeatureBits &= ~MipsAssemblerOptions::AllArchRelatedMask;
452 STI.setFeatureBits(FeatureBits);
453 setAvailableFeatures(
454 ComputeAvailableFeatures(STI.ToggleFeature(ArchFeature)));
455 AssemblerOptions.back()->setFeatures(STI.getFeatureBits());
456 }
457
458 void setFeatureBits(uint64_t Feature, StringRef FeatureString) {
459 if (!(getSTI().getFeatureBits()[Feature])) {
460 MCSubtargetInfo &STI = copySTI();
461 setAvailableFeatures(
462 ComputeAvailableFeatures(STI.ToggleFeature(FeatureString)));
463 AssemblerOptions.back()->setFeatures(STI.getFeatureBits());
464 }
465 }
466
467 void clearFeatureBits(uint64_t Feature, StringRef FeatureString) {
468 if (getSTI().getFeatureBits()[Feature]) {
469 MCSubtargetInfo &STI = copySTI();
470 setAvailableFeatures(
471 ComputeAvailableFeatures(STI.ToggleFeature(FeatureString)));
472 AssemblerOptions.back()->setFeatures(STI.getFeatureBits());
473 }
474 }
475
476 void setModuleFeatureBits(uint64_t Feature, StringRef FeatureString) {
477 setFeatureBits(Feature, FeatureString);
478 AssemblerOptions.front()->setFeatures(getSTI().getFeatureBits());
479 }
480
481 void clearModuleFeatureBits(uint64_t Feature, StringRef FeatureString) {
482 clearFeatureBits(Feature, FeatureString);
483 AssemblerOptions.front()->setFeatures(getSTI().getFeatureBits());
484 }
485
486public:
487 enum MipsMatchResultTy {
488 Match_RequiresDifferentSrcAndDst = FIRST_TARGET_MATCH_RESULT_TY,
489 Match_RequiresDifferentOperands,
490 Match_RequiresNoZeroRegister,
491 Match_RequiresSameSrcAndDst,
492 Match_NoFCCRegisterForCurrentISA,
493 Match_NonZeroOperandForSync,
494 Match_NonZeroOperandForMTCX,
495 Match_RequiresPosSizeRange0_32,
496 Match_RequiresPosSizeRange33_64,
497 Match_RequiresPosSizeUImm6,
498#define GET_OPERAND_DIAGNOSTIC_TYPES
499#include "MipsGenAsmMatcher.inc"
500#undef GET_OPERAND_DIAGNOSTIC_TYPES
501 };
502
503 MipsAsmParser(const MCSubtargetInfo &sti, MCAsmParser &parser,
504 const MCInstrInfo &MII, const MCTargetOptions &Options)
505 : MCTargetAsmParser(Options, sti, MII),
506 ABI(MipsABIInfo::computeTargetABI(Triple(sti.getTargetTriple()),
507 sti.getCPU(), Options)) {
508 MCAsmParserExtension::Initialize(parser);
509
510 parser.addAliasForDirective(".asciiz", ".asciz");
511 parser.addAliasForDirective(".hword", ".2byte");
512 parser.addAliasForDirective(".word", ".4byte");
513 parser.addAliasForDirective(".dword", ".8byte");
514
515 // Initialize the set of available features.
516 setAvailableFeatures(ComputeAvailableFeatures(getSTI().getFeatureBits()));
517
518 // Remember the initial assembler options. The user can not modify these.
519 AssemblerOptions.push_back(
520 llvm::make_unique<MipsAssemblerOptions>(getSTI().getFeatureBits()));
521
522 // Create an assembler options environment for the user to modify.
523 AssemblerOptions.push_back(
524 llvm::make_unique<MipsAssemblerOptions>(getSTI().getFeatureBits()));
525
526 getTargetStreamer().updateABIInfo(*this);
527
528 if (!isABI_O32() && !useOddSPReg() != 0)
529 report_fatal_error("-mno-odd-spreg requires the O32 ABI");
530
531 CurrentFn = nullptr;
532
533 IsPicEnabled = getContext().getObjectFileInfo()->isPositionIndependent();
534
535 IsCpRestoreSet = false;
536 CpRestoreOffset = -1;
537 GPReg = ABI.GetGlobalPtr();
538
539 const Triple &TheTriple = sti.getTargetTriple();
540 IsLittleEndian = TheTriple.isLittleEndian();
541
542 if (getSTI().getCPU() == "mips64r6" && inMicroMipsMode())
543 report_fatal_error("microMIPS64R6 is not supported", false);
544
545 if (!isABI_O32() && inMicroMipsMode())
546 report_fatal_error("microMIPS64 is not supported", false);
547 }
548
549 /// True if all of $fcc0 - $fcc7 exist for the current ISA.
550 bool hasEightFccRegisters() const { return hasMips4() || hasMips32(); }
551
552 bool isGP64bit() const {
553 return getSTI().getFeatureBits()[Mips::FeatureGP64Bit];
554 }
555
556 bool isFP64bit() const {
557 return getSTI().getFeatureBits()[Mips::FeatureFP64Bit];
558 }

562 bool isABI_N64() const { return ABI.IsN64(); }
563 bool isABI_O32() const { return ABI.IsO32(); }
564 bool isABI_FPXX() const {
565 return getSTI().getFeatureBits()[Mips::FeatureFPXX];
566 }

632 bool hasMips64r6() const {
633 return getSTI().getFeatureBits()[Mips::FeatureMips64r6];
634 }
635
636 bool hasDSP() const {
637 return getSTI().getFeatureBits()[Mips::FeatureDSP];
638 }
639
640 bool hasDSPR2() const {
641 return getSTI().getFeatureBits()[Mips::FeatureDSPR2];
642 }
643
644 bool hasDSPR3() const {
645 return getSTI().getFeatureBits()[Mips::FeatureDSPR3];
646 }
647
648 bool hasMSA() const {
649 return getSTI().getFeatureBits()[Mips::FeatureMSA];
650 }
651
652 bool hasCnMips() const {
653 return (getSTI().getFeatureBits()[Mips::FeatureCnMips]);
654 }
655
656 bool inPicMode() {
657 return IsPicEnabled;
658 }
659
660 bool inMips16Mode() const {
661 return getSTI().getFeatureBits()[Mips::FeatureMips16];
662 }
663
664 bool useTraps() const {
665 return getSTI().getFeatureBits()[Mips::FeatureUseTCCInDIV];
666 }

669 return getSTI().getFeatureBits()[Mips::FeatureSoftFloat];

672 return getSTI().getFeatureBits()[Mips::FeatureMT];
673 }

676 return getSTI().getFeatureBits()[Mips::FeatureCRC];
677 }

680 return getSTI().getFeatureBits()[Mips::FeatureVirt];
681 }

684 return getSTI().getFeatureBits()[Mips::FeatureGINV];
685 }
686
687 /// Warn if RegIndex is the same as the current AT.
688 void warnIfRegIndexIsAT(unsigned RegIndex, SMLoc Loc);
689
690 void warnIfNoMacro(SMLoc Loc);
691
692 bool isLittle() const { return IsLittleEndian; }
693
694 const MCExpr *createTargetUnaryExpr(const MCExpr *E,
695 AsmToken::TokenKind OperatorToken,
696 MCContext &Ctx) override {
697 switch(OperatorToken) {
698 default:
699 llvm_unreachable("Unknown token");
700 return nullptr;
701 case AsmToken::PercentCall16:
702 return MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_GOT_CALL, E, Ctx);
703 case AsmToken::PercentCall_Hi:
704 return MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_CALL_HI16, E, Ctx);
705 case AsmToken::PercentCall_Lo:
706 return MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_CALL_LO16, E, Ctx);
707 case AsmToken::PercentDtprel_Hi:
708 return MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_DTPREL_HI, E, Ctx);
709 case AsmToken::PercentDtprel_Lo:
710 return MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_DTPREL_LO, E, Ctx);
711 case AsmToken::PercentGot:
712 return MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_GOT, E, Ctx);
713 case AsmToken::PercentGot_Disp:
714 return MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_GOT_DISP, E, Ctx);
715 case AsmToken::PercentGot_Hi:
716 return MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_GOT_HI16, E, Ctx);
717 case AsmToken::PercentGot_Lo:
718 return MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_GOT_LO16, E, Ctx);
719 case AsmToken::PercentGot_Ofst:
720 return MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_GOT_OFST, E, Ctx);
721 case AsmToken::PercentGot_Page:
722 return MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_GOT_PAGE, E, Ctx);
723 case AsmToken::PercentGottprel:
724 return MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_GOTTPREL, E, Ctx);
725 case AsmToken::PercentGp_Rel:
726 return MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_GPREL, E, Ctx);
727 case AsmToken::PercentHi:
728 return MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_HI, E, Ctx);
729 case AsmToken::PercentHigher:
730 return MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_HIGHER, E, Ctx);
731 case AsmToken::PercentHighest:
732 return MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_HIGHEST, E, Ctx);
733 case AsmToken::PercentLo:
734 return MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_LO, E, Ctx);
735 case AsmToken::PercentNeg:
736 return MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_NEG, E, Ctx);
737 case AsmToken::PercentPcrel_Hi:
738 return MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_PCREL_HI16, E, Ctx);
739 case AsmToken::PercentPcrel_Lo:
740 return MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_PCREL_LO16, E, Ctx);
741 case AsmToken::PercentTlsgd:
742 return MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_TLSGD, E, Ctx);
743 case AsmToken::PercentTlsldm:
744 return MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_TLSLDM, E, Ctx);
745 case AsmToken::PercentTprel_Hi:
746 return MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_TPREL_HI, E, Ctx);
747 case AsmToken::PercentTprel_Lo:
748 return MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_TPREL_LO, E, Ctx);
749 }
750 }
751};
752
753/// MipsOperand - Instances of this class represent a parsed Mips machine
754/// instruction.
755class MipsOperand : public MCParsedAsmOperand {
756public:
757 /// Broad categories of register classes
758 /// The exact class is finalized by the render method.
759 enum RegKind {
760 RegKind_GPR = 1, /// GPR32 and GPR64 (depending on isGP64bit())
761 RegKind_FGR = 2, /// FGR32, FGR64, AFGR64 (depending on context and
762 /// isFP64bit())
763 RegKind_FCC = 4, /// FCC
764 RegKind_MSA128 = 8, /// MSA128[BHWD] (makes no difference which)
765 RegKind_MSACtrl = 16, /// MSA control registers
766 RegKind_COP2 = 32, /// COP2
767 RegKind_ACC = 64, /// HI32DSP, LO32DSP, and ACC64DSP (depending on
768 /// context).
769 RegKind_CCR = 128, /// CCR
770 RegKind_HWRegs = 256, /// HWRegs
771 RegKind_COP3 = 512, /// COP3
772 RegKind_COP0 = 1024, /// COP0
773 /// Potentially any (e.g. $1)
774 RegKind_Numeric = RegKind_GPR | RegKind_FGR | RegKind_FCC | RegKind_MSA128 |
775 RegKind_MSACtrl | RegKind_COP2 | RegKind_ACC |
776 RegKind_CCR | RegKind_HWRegs | RegKind_COP3 | RegKind_COP0
777 };
778
779private:
780 enum KindTy {
781 k_Immediate, /// An immediate (possibly involving symbol references)
782 k_Memory, /// Base + Offset Memory Address
783 k_RegisterIndex, /// A register index in one or more RegKind.
784 k_Token, /// A simple token
785 k_RegList, /// A physical register list
786 } Kind;
787
788public:
789 MipsOperand(KindTy K, MipsAsmParser &Parser)
790 : MCParsedAsmOperand(), Kind(K), AsmParser(Parser) {}
791
792 ~MipsOperand() override {
793 switch (Kind) {
794 case k_Memory:
795 delete Mem.Base;
796 break;
797 case k_RegList:
798 delete RegList.List;
799 break;
800 case k_Immediate:
801 case k_RegisterIndex:
802 case k_Token:
803 break;
804 }
805 }
806
807private:
808 /// For diagnostics, and checking the assembler temporary
809 MipsAsmParser &AsmParser;
810
811 struct Token {
812 const char *Data;
813 unsigned Length;
814 };
815
816 struct RegIdxOp {
817 unsigned Index; /// Index into the register class
818 RegKind Kind; /// Bitfield of the kinds it could possibly be
819 struct Token Tok; /// The input token this operand originated from.
820 const MCRegisterInfo *RegInfo;
821 };
822
823 struct ImmOp {
824 const MCExpr *Val;
825 };
826
827 struct MemOp {
828 MipsOperand *Base;
829 const MCExpr *Off;
830 };
831
832 struct RegListOp {
833 SmallVector<unsigned, 10> *List;
834 };
835
836 union {
837 struct Token Tok;
838 struct RegIdxOp RegIdx;
839 struct ImmOp Imm;
840 struct MemOp Mem;
841 struct RegListOp RegList;
842 };
843
844 SMLoc StartLoc, EndLoc;
845
846 /// Internal constructor for register kinds
847 static std::unique_ptr<MipsOperand> CreateReg(unsigned Index, StringRef Str,
848 RegKind RegKind,
849 const MCRegisterInfo *RegInfo,
850 SMLoc S, SMLoc E,
851 MipsAsmParser &Parser) {
852 auto Op = llvm::make_unique<MipsOperand>(k_RegisterIndex, Parser);
853 Op->RegIdx.Index = Index;
854 Op->RegIdx.RegInfo = RegInfo;
855 Op->RegIdx.Kind = RegKind;
856 Op->RegIdx.Tok.Data = Str.data();
857 Op->RegIdx.Tok.Length = Str.size();
858 Op->StartLoc = S;
859 Op->EndLoc = E;
860 return Op;
861 }
862
863public:
864 /// Coerce the register to GPR32 and return the real register for the current
865 /// target.
866 unsigned getGPR32Reg() const {
867 assert(isRegIdx() && (RegIdx.Kind & RegKind_GPR) && "Invalid access!");
868 AsmParser.warnIfRegIndexIsAT(RegIdx.Index, StartLoc);
869 unsigned ClassID = Mips::GPR32RegClassID;
870 return RegIdx.RegInfo->getRegClass(ClassID).getRegister(RegIdx.Index);
871 }
872
873 /// Coerce the register to GPR32 and return the real register for the current
874 /// target.
875 unsigned getGPRMM16Reg() const {
876 assert(isRegIdx() && (RegIdx.Kind & RegKind_GPR) && "Invalid access!");
877 unsigned ClassID = Mips::GPR32RegClassID;
878 return RegIdx.RegInfo->getRegClass(ClassID).getRegister(RegIdx.Index);
879 }
880
881 /// Coerce the register to GPR64 and return the real register for the current
882 /// target.
883 unsigned getGPR64Reg() const {
884 assert(isRegIdx() && (RegIdx.Kind & RegKind_GPR) && "Invalid access!");
885 unsigned ClassID = Mips::GPR64RegClassID;
886 return RegIdx.RegInfo->getRegClass(ClassID).getRegister(RegIdx.Index);
887 }
888
889private:
890 /// Coerce the register to AFGR64 and return the real register for the current
891 /// target.
892 unsigned getAFGR64Reg() const {
893 assert(isRegIdx() && (RegIdx.Kind & RegKind_FGR) && "Invalid access!");
894 if (RegIdx.Index % 2 != 0)
895 AsmParser.Warning(StartLoc, "Float register should be even.");
896 return RegIdx.RegInfo->getRegClass(Mips::AFGR64RegClassID)
897 .getRegister(RegIdx.Index / 2);
898 }
899
900 /// Coerce the register to FGR64 and return the real register for the current
901 /// target.
902 unsigned getFGR64Reg() const {
903 assert(isRegIdx() && (RegIdx.Kind & RegKind_FGR) && "Invalid access!");
904 return RegIdx.RegInfo->getRegClass(Mips::FGR64RegClassID)
905 .getRegister(RegIdx.Index);
906 }
907
908 /// Coerce the register to FGR32 and return the real register for the current
909 /// target.
910 unsigned getFGR32Reg() const {
911 assert(isRegIdx() && (RegIdx.Kind & RegKind_FGR) && "Invalid access!");
912 return RegIdx.RegInfo->getRegClass(Mips::FGR32RegClassID)
913 .getRegister(RegIdx.Index);
914 }
915
916 /// Coerce the register to FCC and return the real register for the current
917 /// target.
918 unsigned getFCCReg() const {
919 assert(isRegIdx() && (RegIdx.Kind & RegKind_FCC) && "Invalid access!");
920 return RegIdx.RegInfo->getRegClass(Mips::FCCRegClassID)
921 .getRegister(RegIdx.Index);
922 }
923
924 /// Coerce the register to MSA128 and return the real register for the current
925 /// target.
926 unsigned getMSA128Reg() const {
927 assert(isRegIdx() && (RegIdx.Kind & RegKind_MSA128) && "Invalid access!");
928 // It doesn't matter which of the MSA128[BHWD] classes we use. They are all
929 // identical
930 unsigned ClassID = Mips::MSA128BRegClassID;
931 return RegIdx.RegInfo->getRegClass(ClassID).getRegister(RegIdx.Index);
932 }
933
934 /// Coerce the register to MSACtrl and return the real register for the
935 /// current target.
936 unsigned getMSACtrlReg() const {
937 assert(isRegIdx() && (RegIdx.Kind & RegKind_MSACtrl) && "Invalid access!");
938 unsigned ClassID = Mips::MSACtrlRegClassID;
939 return RegIdx.RegInfo->getRegClass(ClassID).getRegister(RegIdx.Index);
940 }
941

1006public:
1007 void addExpr(MCInst &Inst, const MCExpr *Expr) const {
1008 // Add as immediate when possible. Null MCExpr = 0.
1009 if (!Expr)
1010 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(0));
1011 else if (const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(Expr))
1012 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(CE->getValue()));
1013 else
1014 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createExpr(Expr));
1015 }

1018 llvm_unreachable("Use a custom parser instead");
1019 }

1167
1168 template <unsigned Bits, int Offset = 0, int AdjustOffset = 0>
1169 void addConstantUImmOperands(MCInst &Inst, unsigned N) const {
1170 assert(N == 1 && "Invalid number of operands!");
1171 uint64_t Imm = getConstantImm() - Offset;
1172 Imm &= (1ULL << Bits) - 1;
1173 Imm += Offset;
1174 Imm += AdjustOffset;
1175 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(Imm));
1176 }
1177
1178 template <unsigned Bits>
1179 void addSImmOperands(MCInst &Inst, unsigned N) const {
1180 if (isImm() && !isConstantImm()) {
1181 addExpr(Inst, getImm());
1182 return;
1183 }
1184 addConstantSImmOperands<Bits, 0, 0>(Inst, N);
1185 }
1186
1187 template <unsigned Bits>
1188 void addUImmOperands(MCInst &Inst, unsigned N) const {
1189 if (isImm() && !isConstantImm()) {
1190 addExpr(Inst, getImm());
1191 return;
1192 }
1193 addConstantUImmOperands<Bits, 0, 0>(Inst, N);
1194 }
1195
1196 template <unsigned Bits, int Offset = 0, int AdjustOffset = 0>
1197 void addConstantSImmOperands(MCInst &Inst, unsigned N) const {
1198 assert(N == 1 && "Invalid number of operands!");
1199 int64_t Imm = getConstantImm() - Offset;
1200 Imm = SignExtend64<Bits>(Imm);
1201 Imm += Offset;
1202 Imm += AdjustOffset;
1203 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(Imm));
1204 }
1205
1206 void addImmOperands(MCInst &Inst, unsigned N) const {
1207 assert(N == 1 && "Invalid number of operands!");
1208 const MCExpr *Expr = getImm();
1209 addExpr(Inst, Expr);
1210 }
1211
1212 void addMemOperands(MCInst &Inst, unsigned N) const {
1213 assert(N == 2 && "Invalid number of operands!");
1214
1215 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(AsmParser.getABI().ArePtrs64bit()
1216 ? getMemBase()->getGPR64Reg()
1217 : getMemBase()->getGPR32Reg()));
1218
1219 const MCExpr *Expr = getMemOff();
1220 addExpr(Inst, Expr);
1221 }
1222
1223 void addMicroMipsMemOperands(MCInst &Inst, unsigned N) const {
1224 assert(N == 2 && "Invalid number of operands!");
1225
1226 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(getMemBase()->getGPRMM16Reg()));
1227
1228 const MCExpr *Expr = getMemOff();
1229 addExpr(Inst, Expr);
1230 }
1231
1232 void addRegListOperands(MCInst &Inst, unsigned N) const {
1233 assert(N == 1 && "Invalid number of operands!");
1234
1235 for (auto RegNo : getRegList())
1236 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(RegNo));
1237 }
1238
1239 bool isReg() const override {
1240 // As a special case until we sort out the definition of div/divu, accept
1241 // $0/$zero here so that MCK_ZERO works correctly.
1242 return isGPRAsmReg() && RegIdx.Index == 0;
1243 }
1244
1245 bool isRegIdx() const { return Kind == k_RegisterIndex; }
1246 bool isImm() const override { return Kind == k_Immediate; }
1247
1248 bool isConstantImm() const {
1249 int64_t Res;
1250 return isImm() && getImm()->evaluateAsAbsolute(Res);
1251 }
1252
1253 bool isConstantImmz() const {
1254 return isConstantImm() && getConstantImm() == 0;
1255 }
1256
1257 template <unsigned Bits, int Offset = 0> bool isConstantUImm() const {
1258 return isConstantImm() && isUInt<Bits>(getConstantImm() - Offset);
1259 }
1260
1261 template <unsigned Bits> bool isSImm() const {
1262 return isConstantImm() ? isInt<Bits>(getConstantImm()) : isImm();
1263 }
1264
1265 template <unsigned Bits> bool isUImm() const {
1266 return isConstantImm() ? isUInt<Bits>(getConstantImm()) : isImm();
1267 }
1268
1269 template <unsigned Bits> bool isAnyImm() const {
1270 return isConstantImm() ? (isInt<Bits>(getConstantImm()) ||
1271 isUInt<Bits>(getConstantImm()))
1272 : isImm();
1273 }
1274
1275 template <unsigned Bits, int Offset = 0> bool isConstantSImm() const {
1276 return isConstantImm() && isInt<Bits>(getConstantImm() - Offset);
1277 }
1278
1279 template <unsigned Bottom, unsigned Top> bool isConstantUImmRange() const {
1280 return isConstantImm() && getConstantImm() >= Bottom &&
1281 getConstantImm() <= Top;
1282 }
1283
1284 bool isToken() const override {
1285 // Note: It's not possible to pretend that other operand kinds are tokens.
1286 // The matcher emitter checks tokens first.
1287 return Kind == k_Token;
1288 }
1289
1290 bool isMem() const override { return Kind == k_Memory; }
1291
1292 bool isConstantMemOff() const {
1293 return isMem() && isa<MCConstantExpr>(getMemOff());
1294 }
1295
1296 // Allow relocation operators.
1297 // FIXME: This predicate and others need to look through binary expressions
1298 // and determine whether a Value is a constant or not.
1299 template <unsigned Bits, unsigned ShiftAmount = 0>
1300 bool isMemWithSimmOffset() const {
1301 if (!isMem())
1302 return false;
1303 if (!getMemBase()->isGPRAsmReg())
1304 return false;
1305 if (isa<MCTargetExpr>(getMemOff()) ||
1306 (isConstantMemOff() &&
1307 isShiftedInt<Bits, ShiftAmount>(getConstantMemOff())))
1308 return true;
1309 MCValue Res;
1310 bool IsReloc = getMemOff()->evaluateAsRelocatable(Res, nullptr, nullptr);
1311 return IsReloc && isShiftedInt<Bits, ShiftAmount>(Res.getConstant());
1312 }
1313
1314 bool isMemWithPtrSizeOffset() const {
1315 if (!isMem())
1316 return false;
1317 if (!getMemBase()->isGPRAsmReg())
1318 return false;
1319 const unsigned PtrBits = AsmParser.getABI().ArePtrs64bit() ? 64 : 32;
1320 if (isa<MCTargetExpr>(getMemOff()) ||
1321 (isConstantMemOff() && isIntN(PtrBits, getConstantMemOff())))
1322 return true;
1323 MCValue Res;
1324 bool IsReloc = getMemOff()->evaluateAsRelocatable(Res, nullptr, nullptr);
1325 return IsReloc && isIntN(PtrBits, Res.getConstant());
1326 }
1327
1328 bool isMemWithGRPMM16Base() const {
1329 return isMem() && getMemBase()->isMM16AsmReg();
1330 }
1331
1332 template <unsigned Bits> bool isMemWithUimmOffsetSP() const {
1333 return isMem() && isConstantMemOff() && isUInt<Bits>(getConstantMemOff())
1334 && getMemBase()->isRegIdx() && (getMemBase()->getGPR32Reg() == Mips::SP);
1335 }
1336
1337 template <unsigned Bits> bool isMemWithUimmWordAlignedOffsetSP() const {
1338 return isMem() && isConstantMemOff() && isUInt<Bits>(getConstantMemOff())
1339 && (getConstantMemOff() % 4 == 0) && getMemBase()->isRegIdx()
1340 && (getMemBase()->getGPR32Reg() == Mips::SP);
1341 }
1342
1343 template <unsigned Bits> bool isMemWithSimmWordAlignedOffsetGP() const {
1344 return isMem() && isConstantMemOff() && isInt<Bits>(getConstantMemOff())
1345 && (getConstantMemOff() % 4 == 0) && getMemBase()->isRegIdx()
1346 && (getMemBase()->getGPR32Reg() == Mips::GP);
1347 }
1348
1349 template <unsigned Bits, unsigned ShiftLeftAmount>
1350 bool isScaledUImm() const {
1351 return isConstantImm() &&
1352 isShiftedUInt<Bits, ShiftLeftAmount>(getConstantImm());
1353 }
1354
1355 template <unsigned Bits, unsigned ShiftLeftAmount>
1356 bool isScaledSImm() const {
1357 if (isConstantImm() &&
1358 isShiftedInt<Bits, ShiftLeftAmount>(getConstantImm()))
1359 return true;
1360 // Operand can also be a symbol or symbol plus
1361 // offset in case of relocations.
1362 if (Kind != k_Immediate)
1363 return false;
1364 MCValue Res;
1365 bool Success = getImm()->evaluateAsRelocatable(Res, nullptr, nullptr);
1366 return Success && isShiftedInt<Bits, ShiftLeftAmount>(Res.getConstant());
1367 }
1368
1369 bool isRegList16() const {
1370 if (!isRegList())
1371 return false;
1372
1373 int Size = RegList.List->size();
1374 if (Size < 2 || Size > 5)
1375 return false;
1376
1377 unsigned R0 = RegList.List->front();
1378 unsigned R1 = RegList.List->back();
1379 if (!((R0 == Mips::S0 && R1 == Mips::RA) ||
1380 (R0 == Mips::S0_64 && R1 == Mips::RA_64)))
1381 return false;
1382
1383 int PrevReg = *RegList.List->begin();
1384 for (int i = 1; i < Size - 1; i++) {
1385 int Reg = (*(RegList.List))[i];
1386 if ( Reg != PrevReg + 1)
1387 return false;
1388 PrevReg = Reg;
1389 }
1390
1391 return true;
1392 }
1393
1394 bool isInvNum() const { return Kind == k_Immediate; }
1395
1396 bool isLSAImm() const {
1397 if (!isConstantImm())
1398 return false;
1399 int64_t Val = getConstantImm();
1400 return 1 <= Val && Val <= 4;
1401 }
1402
1403 bool isRegList() const { return Kind == k_RegList; }
1404
1405 StringRef getToken() const {
1406 assert(Kind == k_Token && "Invalid access!");
1407 return StringRef(Tok.Data, Tok.Length);
1408 }
1409
1410 unsigned getReg() const override {
1411 // As a special case until we sort out the definition of div/divu, accept
1412 // $0/$zero here so that MCK_ZERO works correctly.
1413 if (Kind == k_RegisterIndex && RegIdx.Index == 0 &&
1414 RegIdx.Kind & RegKind_GPR)
1415 return getGPR32Reg(); // FIXME: GPR64 too
1416
1417 llvm_unreachable("Invalid access!");
1418 return 0;
1419 }
1420
1421 const MCExpr *getImm() const {
1422 assert((Kind == k_Immediate) && "Invalid access!");
1423 return Imm.Val;
1424 }
1425
1426 int64_t getConstantImm() const {
1427 const MCExpr *Val = getImm();
1428 int64_t Value = 0;
1429 (void)Val->evaluateAsAbsolute(Value);
1430 return Value;
1431 }
1432
1433 MipsOperand *getMemBase() const {
1434 assert((Kind == k_Memory) && "Invalid access!");
1435 return Mem.Base;
1436 }
1437
1438 const MCExpr *getMemOff() const {
1439 assert((Kind == k_Memory) && "Invalid access!");
1440 return Mem.Off;
1441 }
1442
1443 int64_t getConstantMemOff() const {
1444 return static_cast<const MCConstantExpr *>(getMemOff())->getValue();
1445 }
1446
1447 const SmallVectorImpl<unsigned> &getRegList() const {
1448 assert((Kind == k_RegList) && "Invalid access!");
1449 return *(RegList.List);
1450 }
1451
1452 static std::unique_ptr<MipsOperand> CreateToken(StringRef Str, SMLoc S,
1453 MipsAsmParser &Parser) {
1454 auto Op = llvm::make_unique<MipsOperand>(k_Token, Parser);
1455 Op->Tok.Data = Str.data();
1456 Op->Tok.Length = Str.size();
1457 Op->StartLoc = S;
1458 Op->EndLoc = S;
1459 return Op;
1460 }
1461
1462 /// Create a numeric register (e.g. $1). The exact register remains
1463 /// unresolved until an instruction successfully matches
1464 static std::unique_ptr<MipsOperand>
1465 createNumericReg(unsigned Index, StringRef Str, const MCRegisterInfo *RegInfo,
1466 SMLoc S, SMLoc E, MipsAsmParser &Parser) {
1467 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "createNumericReg(" << Index << ", ...)\n");
1468 return CreateReg(Index, Str, RegKind_Numeric, RegInfo, S, E, Parser);
1469 }
1470
1471 /// Create a register that is definitely a GPR.
1472 /// This is typically only used for named registers such as $gp.
1473 static std::unique_ptr<MipsOperand>
1474 createGPRReg(unsigned Index, StringRef Str, const MCRegisterInfo *RegInfo,
1475 SMLoc S, SMLoc E, MipsAsmParser &Parser) {
1476 return CreateReg(Index, Str, RegKind_GPR, RegInfo, S, E, Parser);
1477 }

1480 /// This is typically only used for named registers such as $f0.
1481 static std::unique_ptr<MipsOperand>
1482 createFGRReg(unsigned Index, StringRef Str, const MCRegisterInfo *RegInfo,
1483 SMLoc S, SMLoc E, MipsAsmParser &Parser) {
1484 return CreateReg(Index, Str, RegKind_FGR, RegInfo, S, E, Parser);
1485 }

1487 /// Create a register that is definitely a HWReg.
1488 /// This is typically only used for named registers such as $hwr_cpunum.
1489 static std::unique_ptr<MipsOperand>
1490 createHWRegsReg(unsigned Index, StringRef Str, const MCRegisterInfo *RegInfo,
1491 SMLoc S, SMLoc E, MipsAsmParser &Parser) {
1492 return CreateReg(Index, Str, RegKind_HWRegs, RegInfo, S, E, Parser);
1493 }

1495 /// Create a register that is definitely an FCC.
1496 /// This is typically only used for named registers such as $fcc0.
1497 static std::unique_ptr<MipsOperand>
1498 createFCCReg(unsigned Index, StringRef Str, const MCRegisterInfo *RegInfo,
1499 SMLoc S, SMLoc E, MipsAsmParser &Parser) {
1500 return CreateReg(Index, Str, RegKind_FCC, RegInfo, S, E, Parser);
1501 }
1502
1503 /// Create a register that is definitely an ACC.
1504 /// This is typically only used for named registers such as $ac0.
1505 static std::unique_ptr<MipsOperand>
1506 createACCReg(unsigned Index, StringRef Str, const MCRegisterInfo *RegInfo,
1507 SMLoc S, SMLoc E, MipsAsmParser &Parser) {
1508 return CreateReg(Index, Str, RegKind_ACC, RegInfo, S, E, Parser);

1511 /// Create a register that is definitely an MSA128.
1512 /// This is typically only used for named registers such as $w0.
1513 static std::unique_ptr<MipsOperand>
1514 createMSA128Reg(unsigned Index, StringRef Str, const MCRegisterInfo *RegInfo,
1515 SMLoc S, SMLoc E, MipsAsmParser &Parser) {
1516 return CreateReg(Index, Str, RegKind_MSA128, RegInfo, S, E, Parser);

1520 /// This is typically only used for named registers such as $msaaccess.

1522 createMSACtrlReg(unsigned Index, StringRef Str, const MCRegisterInfo *RegInfo,
1523 SMLoc S, SMLoc E, MipsAsmParser &Parser) {
1524 return CreateReg(Index, Str, RegKind_MSACtrl, RegInfo, S, E, Parser);

1526
1527 static std::unique_ptr<MipsOperand>
1528 CreateImm(const MCExpr *Val, SMLoc S, SMLoc E, MipsAsmParser &Parser) {
1529 auto Op = llvm::make_unique<MipsOperand>(k_Immediate, Parser);
1530 Op->Imm.Val = Val;
1531 Op->StartLoc = S;
1532 Op->EndLoc = E;
1533 return Op;
1534 }
1535
1536 static std::unique_ptr<MipsOperand>
1537 CreateMem(std::unique_ptr<MipsOperand> Base, const MCExpr *Off, SMLoc S,
1538 SMLoc E, MipsAsmParser &Parser) {
1539 auto Op = llvm::make_unique<MipsOperand>(k_Memory, Parser);
1540 Op->Mem.Base = Base.release();
1541 Op->Mem.Off = Off;
1542 Op->StartLoc = S;
1543 Op->EndLoc = E;
1544 return Op;
1545 }
1546
1547 static std::unique_ptr<MipsOperand>
1548 CreateRegList(SmallVectorImpl<unsigned> &Regs, SMLoc StartLoc, SMLoc EndLoc,
1549 MipsAsmParser &Parser) {
1550 assert(Regs.size() > 0 && "Empty list not allowed");
1551
1552 auto Op = llvm::make_unique<MipsOperand>(k_RegList, Parser);
1553 Op->RegList.List = new SmallVector<unsigned, 10>(Regs.begin(), Regs.end());
1554 Op->StartLoc = StartLoc;
1555 Op->EndLoc = EndLoc;
1556 return Op;
1557 }
1558
1559 bool isGPRZeroAsmReg() const {
1560 return isRegIdx() && RegIdx.Kind & RegKind_GPR && RegIdx.Index == 0;
1561 }
1562
1563 bool isGPRNonZeroAsmReg() const {
1564 return isRegIdx() && RegIdx.Kind & RegKind_GPR && RegIdx.Index > 0 &&
1565 RegIdx.Index <= 31;
1566 }
1567
1568 bool isGPRAsmReg() const {
1569 return isRegIdx() && RegIdx.Kind & RegKind_GPR && RegIdx.Index <= 31;
1570 }
1571
1572 bool isMM16AsmReg() const {
1573 if (!(isRegIdx() && RegIdx.Kind))
1574 return false;
1575 return ((RegIdx.Index >= 2 && RegIdx.Index <= 7)
1576 || RegIdx.Index == 16 || RegIdx.Index == 17);
1577
1578 }
1579 bool isMM16AsmRegZero() const {
1580 if (!(isRegIdx() && RegIdx.Kind))
1581 return false;
1582 return (RegIdx.Index == 0 ||
1583 (RegIdx.Index >= 2 && RegIdx.Index <= 7) ||
1584 RegIdx.Index == 17);
1585 }
1586
1587 bool isMM16AsmRegMoveP() const {
1588 if (!(isRegIdx() && RegIdx.Kind))
1589 return false;
1590 return (RegIdx.Index == 0 || (RegIdx.Index >= 2 && RegIdx.Index <= 3) ||
1591 (RegIdx.Index >= 16 && RegIdx.Index <= 20));
1592 }
1593
1594 bool isMM16AsmRegMovePPairFirst() const {
1595 if (!(isRegIdx() && RegIdx.Kind))
1596 return false;
1597 return RegIdx.Index >= 4 && RegIdx.Index <= 6;
1598 }
1599
1600 bool isMM16AsmRegMovePPairSecond() const {
1601 if (!(isRegIdx() && RegIdx.Kind))
1602 return false;
1603 return (RegIdx.Index == 21 || RegIdx.Index == 22 ||
1604 (RegIdx.Index >= 5 && RegIdx.Index <= 7));
1605 }
1606
1607 bool isFGRAsmReg() const {
1608 // AFGR64 is $0-$15 but we handle this in getAFGR64()
1609 return isRegIdx() && RegIdx.Kind & RegKind_FGR && RegIdx.Index <= 31;
1610 }
1611
1612 bool isStrictlyFGRAsmReg() const {
1613 // AFGR64 is $0-$15 but we handle this in getAFGR64()
1614 return isRegIdx() && RegIdx.Kind == RegKind_FGR && RegIdx.Index <= 31;
1615 }
1616
1617 bool isHWRegsAsmReg() const {
1618 return isRegIdx() && RegIdx.Kind & RegKind_HWRegs && RegIdx.Index <= 31;
1619 }
1620
1621 bool isCCRAsmReg() const {
1622 return isRegIdx() && RegIdx.Kind & RegKind_CCR && RegIdx.Index <= 31;
1623 }
1624
1625 bool isFCCAsmReg() const {
1626 if (!(isRegIdx() && RegIdx.Kind & RegKind_FCC))
1627 return false;
1628 return RegIdx.Index <= 7;
1629 }
1630
1631 bool isACCAsmReg() const {
1632 return isRegIdx() && RegIdx.Kind & RegKind_ACC && RegIdx.Index <= 3;
1633 }
1634
1635 bool isCOP0AsmReg() const {
1636 return isRegIdx() && RegIdx.Kind & RegKind_COP0 && RegIdx.Index <= 31;
1637 }
1638
1639 bool isCOP2AsmReg() const {
1640 return isRegIdx() && RegIdx.Kind & RegKind_COP2 && RegIdx.Index <= 31;
1641 }
1642
1643 bool isCOP3AsmReg() const {
1644 return isRegIdx() && RegIdx.Kind & RegKind_COP3 && RegIdx.Index <= 31;
1645 }
1646
1647 bool isMSA128AsmReg() const {
1648 return isRegIdx() && RegIdx.Kind & RegKind_MSA128 && RegIdx.Index <= 31;
1649 }
1650
1651 bool isMSACtrlAsmReg() const {
1652 return isRegIdx() && RegIdx.Kind & RegKind_MSACtrl && RegIdx.Index <= 7;
1653 }
1654
1655 /// getStartLoc - Get the location of the first token of this operand.
1656 SMLoc getStartLoc() const override { return StartLoc; }
1657 /// getEndLoc - Get the location of the last token of this operand.
1658 SMLoc getEndLoc() const override { return EndLoc; }
1659
1660 void print(raw_ostream &OS) const override {
1661 switch (Kind) {
1662 case k_Immediate:
1663 OS << "Imm<";
1664 OS << *Imm.Val;
1665 OS << ">";
1666 break;
1667 case k_Memory:
1668 OS << "Mem<";
1669 Mem.Base->print(OS);
1670 OS << ", ";
1671 OS << *Mem.Off;
1672 OS << ">";
1673 break;
1674 case k_RegisterIndex:
1675 OS << "RegIdx<" << RegIdx.Index << ":" << RegIdx.Kind << ", "
1676 << StringRef(RegIdx.Tok.Data, RegIdx.Tok.Length) << ">";
1677 break;
1678 case k_Token:
1679 OS << getToken();
1680 break;
1681 case k_RegList:
1682 OS << "RegList< ";
1683 for (auto Reg : (*RegList.List))
1684 OS << Reg << " ";
1685 OS << ">";
1686 break;
1687 }
1688 }
1689
1690 bool isValidForTie(const MipsOperand &Other) const {
1691 if (Kind != Other.Kind)
1692 return false;
1693
1694 switch (Kind) {
1695 default:
1696 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected kind");
1697 return false;
1698 case k_RegisterIndex: {
1699 StringRef Token(RegIdx.Tok.Data, RegIdx.Tok.Length);
1700 StringRef OtherToken(Other.RegIdx.Tok.Data, Other.RegIdx.Tok.Length);
1701 return Token == OtherToken;
1702 }
1703 }
1704 }
1705}; // class MipsOperand
1706
1707} // end anonymous namespace

1709namespace llvm {
1710
1711extern const MCInstrDesc MipsInsts[];
1712
1713} // end namespace llvm
1714
1715static const MCInstrDesc &getInstDesc(unsigned Opcode) {
1716 return MipsInsts[Opcode];
1717}
1718
1719static bool hasShortDelaySlot(MCInst &Inst) {
1720 switch (Inst.getOpcode()) {
1721 case Mips::BEQ_MM:
1722 case Mips::BNE_MM:
1723 case Mips::BLTZ_MM:
1724 case Mips::BGEZ_MM:
1725 case Mips::BLEZ_MM:
1726 case Mips::BGTZ_MM:
1727 case Mips::JRC16_MM:
1728 case Mips::JALS_MM:
1729 case Mips::JALRS_MM:
1730 case Mips::JALRS16_MM:
1731 case Mips::BGEZALS_MM:
1732 case Mips::BLTZALS_MM:
1733 return true;
1734 case Mips::J_MM:
1735 return !Inst.getOperand(0).isReg();
1736 default:
1737 return false;
1738 }
1739}
1740
1741static const MCSymbol *getSingleMCSymbol(const MCExpr *Expr) {
1742 if (const MCSymbolRefExpr *SRExpr = dyn_cast<MCSymbolRefExpr>(Expr)) {
1743 return &SRExpr->getSymbol();
1744 }
1745
1746 if (const MCBinaryExpr *BExpr = dyn_cast<MCBinaryExpr>(Expr)) {
1747 const MCSymbol *LHSSym = getSingleMCSymbol(BExpr->getLHS());
1748 const MCSymbol *RHSSym = getSingleMCSymbol(BExpr->getRHS());
1749
1750 if (LHSSym)
1751 return LHSSym;
1752
1753 if (RHSSym)
1754 return RHSSym;
1755
1756 return nullptr;
1757 }
1758
1759 if (const MCUnaryExpr *UExpr = dyn_cast<MCUnaryExpr>(Expr))
1760 return getSingleMCSymbol(UExpr->getSubExpr());
1761
1762 return nullptr;
1763}
1764
1765static unsigned countMCSymbolRefExpr(const MCExpr *Expr) {
1766 if (isa<MCSymbolRefExpr>(Expr))
1767 return 1;
1768
1769 if (const MCBinaryExpr *BExpr = dyn_cast<MCBinaryExpr>(Expr))
1770 return countMCSymbolRefExpr(BExpr->getLHS()) +
1771 countMCSymbolRefExpr(BExpr->getRHS());
1772
1773 if (const MCUnaryExpr *UExpr = dyn_cast<MCUnaryExpr>(Expr))
1774 return countMCSymbolRefExpr(UExpr->getSubExpr());
1775
1776 return 0;
1777}
1778
1779bool MipsAsmParser::processInstruction(MCInst &Inst, SMLoc IDLoc,
1780 MCStreamer &Out,
1781 const MCSubtargetInfo *STI) {
1782 MipsTargetStreamer &TOut = getTargetStreamer();
1783 const MCInstrDesc &MCID = getInstDesc(Inst.getOpcode());
1784 bool ExpandedJalSym = false;
1785
1786 Inst.setLoc(IDLoc);
1787
1788 if (MCID.isBranch() || MCID.isCall()) {
1789 const unsigned Opcode = Inst.getOpcode();
1790 MCOperand Offset;
1791
1792 switch (Opcode) {
1793 default:
1794 break;
1795 case Mips::BBIT0:
1796 case Mips::BBIT032:
1797 case Mips::BBIT1:
1798 case Mips::BBIT132:
1799 assert(hasCnMips() && "instruction only valid for octeon cpus");
1800 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
1801
1802 case Mips::BEQ:
1803 case Mips::BNE:
1804 case Mips::BEQ_MM:
1805 case Mips::BNE_MM:
1806 assert(MCID.getNumOperands() == 3 && "unexpected number of operands");
1807 Offset = Inst.getOperand(2);
1808 if (!Offset.isImm())
1809 break; // We'll deal with this situation later on when applying fixups.
1810 if (!isIntN(inMicroMipsMode() ? 17 : 18, Offset.getImm()))
1811 return Error(IDLoc, "branch target out of range");
1812 if (OffsetToAlignment(Offset.getImm(),
1813 1LL << (inMicroMipsMode() ? 1 : 2)))
1814 return Error(IDLoc, "branch to misaligned address");
1815 break;
1816 case Mips::BGEZ:
1817 case Mips::BGTZ:
1818 case Mips::BLEZ:
1819 case Mips::BLTZ:
1820 case Mips::BGEZAL:
1821 case Mips::BLTZAL:
1822 case Mips::BC1F:
1823 case Mips::BC1T:
1824 case Mips::BGEZ_MM:
1825 case Mips::BGTZ_MM:
1826 case Mips::BLEZ_MM:
1827 case Mips::BLTZ_MM:
1828 case Mips::BGEZAL_MM:
1829 case Mips::BLTZAL_MM:
1830 case Mips::BC1F_MM:
1831 case Mips::BC1T_MM:
1832 case Mips::BC1EQZC_MMR6:
1833 case Mips::BC1NEZC_MMR6:
1834 case Mips::BC2EQZC_MMR6:
1835 case Mips::BC2NEZC_MMR6:
1836 assert(MCID.getNumOperands() == 2 && "unexpected number of operands");
1837 Offset = Inst.getOperand(1);
1838 if (!Offset.isImm())
1839 break; // We'll deal with this situation later on when applying fixups.
1840 if (!isIntN(inMicroMipsMode() ? 17 : 18, Offset.getImm()))
1841 return Error(IDLoc, "branch target out of range");
1842 if (OffsetToAlignment(Offset.getImm(),
1843 1LL << (inMicroMipsMode() ? 1 : 2)))
1844 return Error(IDLoc, "branch to misaligned address");
1845 break;
1846 case Mips::BGEC: case Mips::BGEC_MMR6:
1847 case Mips::BLTC: case Mips::BLTC_MMR6:
1848 case Mips::BGEUC: case Mips::BGEUC_MMR6:
1849 case Mips::BLTUC: case Mips::BLTUC_MMR6:
1850 case Mips::BEQC: case Mips::BEQC_MMR6:
1851 case Mips::BNEC: case Mips::BNEC_MMR6:
1852 assert(MCID.getNumOperands() == 3 && "unexpected number of operands");
1853 Offset = Inst.getOperand(2);
1854 if (!Offset.isImm())
1855 break; // We'll deal with this situation later on when applying fixups.
1856 if (!isIntN(18, Offset.getImm()))
1857 return Error(IDLoc, "branch target out of range");
1858 if (OffsetToAlignment(Offset.getImm(), 1LL << 2))
1859 return Error(IDLoc, "branch to misaligned address");
1860 break;
1861 case Mips::BLEZC: case Mips::BLEZC_MMR6:
1862 case Mips::BGEZC: case Mips::BGEZC_MMR6:
1863 case Mips::BGTZC: case Mips::BGTZC_MMR6:
1864 case Mips::BLTZC: case Mips::BLTZC_MMR6:
1865 assert(MCID.getNumOperands() == 2 && "unexpected number of operands");
1866 Offset = Inst.getOperand(1);
1867 if (!Offset.isImm())
1868 break; // We'll deal with this situation later on when applying fixups.
1869 if (!isIntN(18, Offset.getImm()))
1870 return Error(IDLoc, "branch target out of range");
1871 if (OffsetToAlignment(Offset.getImm(), 1LL << 2))
1872 return Error(IDLoc, "branch to misaligned address");
1873 break;
1874 case Mips::BEQZC: case Mips::BEQZC_MMR6:
1875 case Mips::BNEZC: case Mips::BNEZC_MMR6:
1876 assert(MCID.getNumOperands() == 2 && "unexpected number of operands");
1877 Offset = Inst.getOperand(1);
1878 if (!Offset.isImm())
1879 break; // We'll deal with this situation later on when applying fixups.
1880 if (!isIntN(23, Offset.getImm()))
1881 return Error(IDLoc, "branch target out of range");
1882 if (OffsetToAlignment(Offset.getImm(), 1LL << 2))
1883 return Error(IDLoc, "branch to misaligned address");
1884 break;
1885 case Mips::BEQZ16_MM:
1886 case Mips::BEQZC16_MMR6:
1887 case Mips::BNEZ16_MM:
1888 case Mips::BNEZC16_MMR6:
1889 assert(MCID.getNumOperands() == 2 && "unexpected number of operands");
1890 Offset = Inst.getOperand(1);
1891 if (!Offset.isImm())
1892 break; // We'll deal with this situation later on when applying fixups.
1893 if (!isInt<8>(Offset.getImm()))
1894 return Error(IDLoc, "branch target out of range");
1895 if (OffsetToAlignment(Offset.getImm(), 2LL))
1896 return Error(IDLoc, "branch to misaligned address");
1897 break;
1898 }
1899 }
1900
1901 // SSNOP is deprecated on MIPS32r6/MIPS64r6
1902 // We still accept it but it is a normal nop.
1903 if (hasMips32r6() && Inst.getOpcode() == Mips::SSNOP) {
1904 std::string ISA = hasMips64r6() ? "MIPS64r6" : "MIPS32r6";
1905 Warning(IDLoc, "ssnop is deprecated for " + ISA + " and is equivalent to a "
1906 "nop instruction");
1907 }
1908
1909 if (hasCnMips()) {
1910 const unsigned Opcode = Inst.getOpcode();
1911 MCOperand Opnd;
1912 int Imm;
1913
1914 switch (Opcode) {
1915 default:
1916 break;
1917
1918 case Mips::BBIT0:
1919 case Mips::BBIT032:
1920 case Mips::BBIT1:
1921 case Mips::BBIT132:
1922 assert(MCID.getNumOperands() == 3 && "unexpected number of operands");
1923 // The offset is handled above
1924 Opnd = Inst.getOperand(1);
1925 if (!Opnd.isImm())
1926 return Error(IDLoc, "expected immediate operand kind");
1927 Imm = Opnd.getImm();
1928 if (Imm < 0 || Imm > (Opcode == Mips::BBIT0 ||
1929 Opcode == Mips::BBIT1 ? 63 : 31))
1930 return Error(IDLoc, "immediate operand value out of range");
1931 if (Imm > 31) {
1932 Inst.setOpcode(Opcode == Mips::BBIT0 ? Mips::BBIT032
1933 : Mips::BBIT132);
1934 Inst.getOperand(1).setImm(Imm - 32);
1935 }
1936 break;
1937
1938 case Mips::SEQi:
1939 case Mips::SNEi:
1940 assert(MCID.getNumOperands() == 3 && "unexpected number of operands");
1941 Opnd = Inst.getOperand(2);
1942 if (!Opnd.isImm())
1943 return Error(IDLoc, "expected immediate operand kind");
1944 Imm = Opnd.getImm();
1945 if (!isInt<10>(Imm))
1946 return Error(IDLoc, "immediate operand value out of range");
1947 break;
1948 }
1949 }
1950
1951 // Warn on division by zero. We're checking here as all instructions get
1952 // processed here, not just the macros that need expansion.
1953 //
1954 // The MIPS backend models most of the divison instructions and macros as
1955 // three operand instructions. The pre-R6 divide instructions however have
1956 // two operands and explicitly define HI/LO as part of the instruction,
1957 // not in the operands.
1958 unsigned FirstOp = 1;
1959 unsigned SecondOp = 2;
1960 switch (Inst.getOpcode()) {
1961 default:
1962 break;
1963 case Mips::SDivIMacro:
1964 case Mips::UDivIMacro:
1965 case Mips::DSDivIMacro:
1966 case Mips::DUDivIMacro:
1967 if (Inst.getOperand(2).getImm() == 0) {
1968 if (Inst.getOperand(1).getReg() == Mips::ZERO ||
1969 Inst.getOperand(1).getReg() == Mips::ZERO_64)
1970 Warning(IDLoc, "dividing zero by zero");
1971 else
1972 Warning(IDLoc, "division by zero");
1973 }
1974 break;
1975 case Mips::DSDIV:
1976 case Mips::SDIV:
1977 case Mips::UDIV:
1978 case Mips::DUDIV:
1979 case Mips::UDIV_MM:
1980 case Mips::SDIV_MM:
1981 FirstOp = 0;
1982 SecondOp = 1;
1983 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
1984 case Mips::SDivMacro:
1985 case Mips::DSDivMacro:
1986 case Mips::UDivMacro:
1987 case Mips::DUDivMacro:
1988 case Mips::DIV:
1989 case Mips::DIVU:
1990 case Mips::DDIV:
1991 case Mips::DDIVU:
1992 case Mips::DIVU_MMR6:
1993 case Mips::DIV_MMR6:
1994 if (Inst.getOperand(SecondOp).getReg() == Mips::ZERO ||
1995 Inst.getOperand(SecondOp).getReg() == Mips::ZERO_64) {
1996 if (Inst.getOperand(FirstOp).getReg() == Mips::ZERO ||
1997 Inst.getOperand(FirstOp).getReg() == Mips::ZERO_64)
1998 Warning(IDLoc, "dividing zero by zero");
1999 else
2000 Warning(IDLoc, "division by zero");
2001 }
2002 break;
2003 }
2004
2005 // For PIC code convert unconditional jump to unconditional branch.
2006 if ((Inst.getOpcode() == Mips::J || Inst.getOpcode() == Mips::J_MM) &&
2007 inPicMode()) {
2008 MCInst BInst;
2009 BInst.setOpcode(inMicroMipsMode() ? Mips::BEQ_MM : Mips::BEQ);
2010 BInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(Mips::ZERO));
2011 BInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(Mips::ZERO));
2012 BInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0));
2013 Inst = BInst;
2014 }
2015
2016 // This expansion is not in a function called by tryExpandInstruction()
2017 // because the pseudo-instruction doesn't have a distinct opcode.
2018 if ((Inst.getOpcode() == Mips::JAL || Inst.getOpcode() == Mips::JAL_MM) &&
2019 inPicMode()) {
2020 warnIfNoMacro(IDLoc);
2021
2022 const MCExpr *JalExpr = Inst.getOperand(0).getExpr();
2023
2024 // We can do this expansion if there's only 1 symbol in the argument
2025 // expression.
2026 if (countMCSymbolRefExpr(JalExpr) > 1)
2027 return Error(IDLoc, "jal doesn't support multiple symbols in PIC mode");
2028
2029 // FIXME: This is checking the expression can be handled by the later stages
2030 // of the assembler. We ought to leave it to those later stages.
2031 const MCSymbol *JalSym = getSingleMCSymbol(JalExpr);
2032
2033 // FIXME: Add support for label+offset operands (currently causes an error).
2034 // FIXME: Add support for forward-declared local symbols.
2035 // FIXME: Add expansion for when the LargeGOT option is enabled.
2036 if (JalSym->isInSection() || JalSym->isTemporary() ||
2037 (JalSym->isELF() &&
2038 cast<MCSymbolELF>(JalSym)->getBinding() == ELF::STB_LOCAL)) {
2039 if (isABI_O32()) {
2040 // If it's a local symbol and the O32 ABI is being used, we expand to:
2041 // lw $25, 0($gp)
2042 // R_(MICRO)MIPS_GOT16 label
2043 // addiu $25, $25, 0
2044 // R_(MICRO)MIPS_LO16 label
2045 // jalr $25
2046 const MCExpr *Got16RelocExpr =
2047 MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_GOT, JalExpr, getContext());
2048 const MCExpr *Lo16RelocExpr =
2049 MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_LO, JalExpr, getContext());
2050
2051 TOut.emitRRX(Mips::LW, Mips::T9, GPReg,
2052 MCOperand::createExpr(Got16RelocExpr), IDLoc, STI);
2053 TOut.emitRRX(Mips::ADDiu, Mips::T9, Mips::T9,
2054 MCOperand::createExpr(Lo16RelocExpr), IDLoc, STI);
2055 } else if (isABI_N32() || isABI_N64()) {
2056 // If it's a local symbol and the N32/N64 ABIs are being used,
2057 // we expand to:
2058 // lw/ld $25, 0($gp)
2059 // R_(MICRO)MIPS_GOT_DISP label
2060 // jalr $25
2061 const MCExpr *GotDispRelocExpr =
2062 MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_GOT_DISP, JalExpr, getContext());
2063
2064 TOut.emitRRX(ABI.ArePtrs64bit() ? Mips::LD : Mips::LW, Mips::T9,
2065 GPReg, MCOperand::createExpr(GotDispRelocExpr), IDLoc,
2066 STI);
2067 }
2068 } else {
2069 // If it's an external/weak symbol, we expand to:
2070 // lw/ld $25, 0($gp)
2071 // R_(MICRO)MIPS_CALL16 label
2072 // jalr $25
2073 const MCExpr *Call16RelocExpr =
2074 MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_GOT_CALL, JalExpr, getContext());
2075
2076 TOut.emitRRX(ABI.ArePtrs64bit() ? Mips::LD : Mips::LW, Mips::T9, GPReg,
2077 MCOperand::createExpr(Call16RelocExpr), IDLoc, STI);
2078 }
2079
2080 MCInst JalrInst;
2081 if (IsCpRestoreSet && inMicroMipsMode())
2082 JalrInst.setOpcode(Mips::JALRS_MM);
2083 else
2084 JalrInst.setOpcode(inMicroMipsMode() ? Mips::JALR_MM : Mips::JALR);
2085 JalrInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(Mips::RA));
2086 JalrInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(Mips::T9));
2087
2088 if (EmitJalrReloc) {
2089 // As an optimization hint for the linker, before the JALR we add:
2090 // .reloc tmplabel, R_{MICRO}MIPS_JALR, symbol
2091 // tmplabel:
2092 MCSymbol *TmpLabel = getContext().createTempSymbol();
2093 const MCExpr *TmpExpr = MCSymbolRefExpr::create(TmpLabel, getContext());
2094 const MCExpr *RelocJalrExpr =
2095 MCSymbolRefExpr::create(JalSym, MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_None,
2096 getContext(), IDLoc);
2097
2098 TOut.getStreamer().EmitRelocDirective(*TmpExpr,
2099 inMicroMipsMode() ? "R_MICROMIPS_JALR" : "R_MIPS_JALR",
2100 RelocJalrExpr, IDLoc, *STI);
2101 TOut.getStreamer().EmitLabel(TmpLabel);
2102 }
2103
2104 Inst = JalrInst;
2105 ExpandedJalSym = true;
2106 }
2107
2108 bool IsPCRelativeLoad = (MCID.TSFlags & MipsII::IsPCRelativeLoad) != 0;
2109 if ((MCID.mayLoad() || MCID.mayStore()) && !IsPCRelativeLoad) {
2110 // Check the offset of memory operand, if it is a symbol
2111 // reference or immediate we may have to expand instructions.
2112 for (unsigned i = 0; i < MCID.getNumOperands(); i++) {
2113 const MCOperandInfo &OpInfo = MCID.OpInfo[i];
2114 if ((OpInfo.OperandType == MCOI::OPERAND_MEMORY) ||
2115 (OpInfo.OperandType == MCOI::OPERAND_UNKNOWN)) {
2116 MCOperand &Op = Inst.getOperand(i);
2117 if (Op.isImm()) {
2118 int64_t MemOffset = Op.getImm();
2119 if (MemOffset < -32768 || MemOffset > 32767) {
2120 // Offset can't exceed 16bit value.
2121 expandMemInst(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI, MCID.mayLoad());
2122 return getParser().hasPendingError();
2123 }
2124 } else if (Op.isExpr()) {
2125 const MCExpr *Expr = Op.getExpr();
2126 if (Expr->getKind() == MCExpr::SymbolRef) {
2127 const MCSymbolRefExpr *SR =
2128 static_cast<const MCSymbolRefExpr *>(Expr);
2129 if (SR->getKind() == MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_None) {
2130 // Expand symbol.
2131 expandMemInst(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI, MCID.mayLoad());
2132 return getParser().hasPendingError();
2133 }
2134 } else if (!isEvaluated(Expr)) {
2135 expandMemInst(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI, MCID.mayLoad());
2136 return getParser().hasPendingError();
2137 }
2138 }
2139 }
2140 } // for
2141 } // if load/store
2142
2143 if (inMicroMipsMode()) {
2144 if (MCID.mayLoad() && Inst.getOpcode() != Mips::LWP_MM) {
2145 // Try to create 16-bit GP relative load instruction.
2146 for (unsigned i = 0; i < MCID.getNumOperands(); i++) {
2147 const MCOperandInfo &OpInfo = MCID.OpInfo[i];
2148 if ((OpInfo.OperandType == MCOI::OPERAND_MEMORY) ||
2149 (OpInfo.OperandType == MCOI::OPERAND_UNKNOWN)) {
2150 MCOperand &Op = Inst.getOperand(i);
2151 if (Op.isImm()) {
2152 int MemOffset = Op.getImm();
2153 MCOperand &DstReg = Inst.getOperand(0);
2154 MCOperand &BaseReg = Inst.getOperand(1);
2155 if (isInt<9>(MemOffset) && (MemOffset % 4 == 0) &&
2156 getContext().getRegisterInfo()->getRegClass(
2157 Mips::GPRMM16RegClassID).contains(DstReg.getReg()) &&
2158 (BaseReg.getReg() == Mips::GP ||
2159 BaseReg.getReg() == Mips::GP_64)) {
2160
2161 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::LWGP_MM, DstReg.getReg(), Mips::GP, MemOffset,
2162 IDLoc, STI);
2163 return false;
2164 }
2165 }
2166 }
2167 } // for
2168 } // if load
2169
2170 // TODO: Handle this with the AsmOperandClass.PredicateMethod.
2171
2172 MCOperand Opnd;
2173 int Imm;
2174
2175 switch (Inst.getOpcode()) {
2176 default:
2177 break;
2178 case Mips::ADDIUSP_MM:
2179 Opnd = Inst.getOperand(0);
2180 if (!Opnd.isImm())
2181 return Error(IDLoc, "expected immediate operand kind");
2182 Imm = Opnd.getImm();
2183 if (Imm < -1032 || Imm > 1028 || (Imm < 8 && Imm > -12) ||
2184 Imm % 4 != 0)
2185 return Error(IDLoc, "immediate operand value out of range");
2186 break;
2187 case Mips::SLL16_MM:
2188 case Mips::SRL16_MM:
2189 Opnd = Inst.getOperand(2);
2190 if (!Opnd.isImm())
2191 return Error(IDLoc, "expected immediate operand kind");
2192 Imm = Opnd.getImm();
2193 if (Imm < 1 || Imm > 8)
2194 return Error(IDLoc, "immediate operand value out of range");
2195 break;
2196 case Mips::LI16_MM:
2197 Opnd = Inst.getOperand(1);
2198 if (!Opnd.isImm())
2199 return Error(IDLoc, "expected immediate operand kind");
2200 Imm = Opnd.getImm();
2201 if (Imm < -1 || Imm > 126)
2202 return Error(IDLoc, "immediate operand value out of range");
2203 break;
2204 case Mips::ADDIUR2_MM:
2205 Opnd = Inst.getOperand(2);
2206 if (!Opnd.isImm())
2207 return Error(IDLoc, "expected immediate operand kind");
2208 Imm = Opnd.getImm();
2209 if (!(Imm == 1 || Imm == -1 ||
2210 ((Imm % 4 == 0) && Imm < 28 && Imm > 0)))
2211 return Error(IDLoc, "immediate operand value out of range");
2212 break;
2213 case Mips::ANDI16_MM:
2214 Opnd = Inst.getOperand(2);
2215 if (!Opnd.isImm())
2216 return Error(IDLoc, "expected immediate operand kind");
2217 Imm = Opnd.getImm();
2218 if (!(Imm == 128 || (Imm >= 1 && Imm <= 4) || Imm == 7 || Imm == 8 ||
2219 Imm == 15 || Imm == 16 || Imm == 31 || Imm == 32 || Imm == 63 ||
2220 Imm == 64 || Imm == 255 || Imm == 32768 || Imm == 65535))
2221 return Error(IDLoc, "immediate operand value out of range");
2222 break;
2223 case Mips::LBU16_MM:
2224 Opnd = Inst.getOperand(2);
2225 if (!Opnd.isImm())
2226 return Error(IDLoc, "expected immediate operand kind");
2227 Imm = Opnd.getImm();
2228 if (Imm < -1 || Imm > 14)
2229 return Error(IDLoc, "immediate operand value out of range");
2230 break;
2231 case Mips::SB16_MM:
2232 case Mips::SB16_MMR6:
2233 Opnd = Inst.getOperand(2);
2234 if (!Opnd.isImm())
2235 return Error(IDLoc, "expected immediate operand kind");
2236 Imm = Opnd.getImm();
2237 if (Imm < 0 || Imm > 15)
2238 return Error(IDLoc, "immediate operand value out of range");
2239 break;
2240 case Mips::LHU16_MM:
2241 case Mips::SH16_MM:
2242 case Mips::SH16_MMR6:
2243 Opnd = Inst.getOperand(2);
2244 if (!Opnd.isImm())
2245 return Error(IDLoc, "expected immediate operand kind");
2246 Imm = Opnd.getImm();
2247 if (Imm < 0 || Imm > 30 || (Imm % 2 != 0))
2248 return Error(IDLoc, "immediate operand value out of range");
2249 break;
2250 case Mips::LW16_MM:
2251 case Mips::SW16_MM:
2252 case Mips::SW16_MMR6:
2253 Opnd = Inst.getOperand(2);
2254 if (!Opnd.isImm())
2255 return Error(IDLoc, "expected immediate operand kind");
2256 Imm = Opnd.getImm();
2257 if (Imm < 0 || Imm > 60 || (Imm % 4 != 0))
2258 return Error(IDLoc, "immediate operand value out of range");
2259 break;
2260 case Mips::ADDIUPC_MM:
2261 Opnd = Inst.getOperand(1);
2262 if (!Opnd.isImm())
2263 return Error(IDLoc, "expected immediate operand kind");
2264 Imm = Opnd.getImm();
2265 if ((Imm % 4 != 0) || !isInt<25>(Imm))
2266 return Error(IDLoc, "immediate operand value out of range");
2267 break;
2268 case Mips::LWP_MM:
2269 case Mips::SWP_MM:
2270 if (Inst.getOperand(0).getReg() == Mips::RA)
2271 return Error(IDLoc, "invalid operand for instruction");
2272 break;
2273 case Mips::MOVEP_MM:
2274 case Mips::MOVEP_MMR6: {
2275 unsigned R0 = Inst.getOperand(0).getReg();
2276 unsigned R1 = Inst.getOperand(1).getReg();
2277 bool RegPair = ((R0 == Mips::A1 && R1 == Mips::A2) ||
2278 (R0 == Mips::A1 && R1 == Mips::A3) ||
2279 (R0 == Mips::A2 && R1 == Mips::A3) ||
2280 (R0 == Mips::A0 && R1 == Mips::S5) ||
2281 (R0 == Mips::A0 && R1 == Mips::S6) ||
2282 (R0 == Mips::A0 && R1 == Mips::A1) ||
2283 (R0 == Mips::A0 && R1 == Mips::A2) ||
2284 (R0 == Mips::A0 && R1 == Mips::A3));
2285 if (!RegPair)
2286 return Error(IDLoc, "invalid operand for instruction");
2287 break;
2288 }
2289 }
2290 }
2291
2292 bool FillDelaySlot =
2293 MCID.hasDelaySlot() && AssemblerOptions.back()->isReorder();
2294 if (FillDelaySlot)
2295 TOut.emitDirectiveSetNoReorder();
2296
2297 MacroExpanderResultTy ExpandResult =
2298 tryExpandInstruction(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI);
2299 switch (ExpandResult) {
2300 case MER_NotAMacro:
2301 Out.EmitInstruction(Inst, *STI);
2302 break;
2303 case MER_Success:
2304 break;
2305 case MER_Fail:
2306 return true;
2307 }
2308
2309 // We know we emitted an instruction on the MER_NotAMacro or MER_Success path.
2310 // If we're in microMIPS mode then we must also set EF_MIPS_MICROMIPS.
2311 if (inMicroMipsMode()) {
2312 TOut.setUsesMicroMips();
2313 TOut.updateABIInfo(*this);
2314 }
2315
2316 // If this instruction has a delay slot and .set reorder is active,
2317 // emit a NOP after it.
2318 if (FillDelaySlot) {
2319 TOut.emitEmptyDelaySlot(hasShortDelaySlot(Inst), IDLoc, STI);
2320 TOut.emitDirectiveSetReorder();
2321 }
2322
2323 if ((Inst.getOpcode() == Mips::JalOneReg ||
2324 Inst.getOpcode() == Mips::JalTwoReg || ExpandedJalSym) &&
2325 isPicAndNotNxxAbi()) {
2326 if (IsCpRestoreSet) {
2327 // We need a NOP between the JALR and the LW:
2328 // If .set reorder has been used, we've already emitted a NOP.
2329 // If .set noreorder has been used, we need to emit a NOP at this point.
2330 if (!AssemblerOptions.back()->isReorder())
2331 TOut.emitEmptyDelaySlot(hasShortDelaySlot(Inst), IDLoc,
2332 STI);
2333
2334 // Load the $gp from the stack.
2335 TOut.emitGPRestore(CpRestoreOffset, IDLoc, STI);
2336 } else
2337 Warning(IDLoc, "no .cprestore used in PIC mode");
2338 }
2339
2340 return false;
2341}
2342
2343MipsAsmParser::MacroExpanderResultTy
2344MipsAsmParser::tryExpandInstruction(MCInst &Inst, SMLoc IDLoc, MCStreamer &Out,
2345 const MCSubtargetInfo *STI) {
2346 switch (Inst.getOpcode()) {
2347 default:
2348 return MER_NotAMacro;
2349 case Mips::LoadImm32:
2350 return expandLoadImm(Inst, true, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail : MER_Success;
2351 case Mips::LoadImm64:
2352 return expandLoadImm(Inst, false, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail : MER_Success;
2353 case Mips::LoadAddrImm32:
2354 case Mips::LoadAddrImm64:
2355 assert(Inst.getOperand(0).isReg() && "expected register operand kind");
2356 assert((Inst.getOperand(1).isImm() || Inst.getOperand(1).isExpr()) &&
2357 "expected immediate operand kind");
2358
2359 return expandLoadAddress(Inst.getOperand(0).getReg(), Mips::NoRegister,
2360 Inst.getOperand(1),
2361 Inst.getOpcode() == Mips::LoadAddrImm32, IDLoc,
2362 Out, STI)
2363 ? MER_Fail
2364 : MER_Success;
2365 case Mips::LoadAddrReg32:
2366 case Mips::LoadAddrReg64:
2367 assert(Inst.getOperand(0).isReg() && "expected register operand kind");
2368 assert(Inst.getOperand(1).isReg() && "expected register operand kind");
2369 assert((Inst.getOperand(2).isImm() || Inst.getOperand(2).isExpr()) &&
2370 "expected immediate operand kind");
2371
2372 return expandLoadAddress(Inst.getOperand(0).getReg(),
2373 Inst.getOperand(1).getReg(), Inst.getOperand(2),
2374 Inst.getOpcode() == Mips::LoadAddrReg32, IDLoc,
2375 Out, STI)
2376 ? MER_Fail
2377 : MER_Success;
2378 case Mips::B_MM_Pseudo:
2379 case Mips::B_MMR6_Pseudo:
2380 return expandUncondBranchMMPseudo(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail
2381 : MER_Success;
2382 case Mips::SWM_MM:
2383 case Mips::LWM_MM:
2384 return expandLoadStoreMultiple(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail
2385 : MER_Success;
2386 case Mips::JalOneReg:
2387 case Mips::JalTwoReg:
2388 return expandJalWithRegs(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail : MER_Success;
2389 case Mips::BneImm:
2390 case Mips::BeqImm:
2391 case Mips::BEQLImmMacro:
2392 case Mips::BNELImmMacro:
2393 return expandBranchImm(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail : MER_Success;
2394 case Mips::BLT:
2395 case Mips::BLE:
2396 case Mips::BGE:
2397 case Mips::BGT:
2398 case Mips::BLTU:
2399 case Mips::BLEU:
2400 case Mips::BGEU:
2401 case Mips::BGTU:
2402 case Mips::BLTL:
2403 case Mips::BLEL:
2404 case Mips::BGEL:
2405 case Mips::BGTL:
2406 case Mips::BLTUL:
2407 case Mips::BLEUL:
2408 case Mips::BGEUL:
2409 case Mips::BGTUL:
2410 case Mips::BLTImmMacro:
2411 case Mips::BLEImmMacro:
2412 case Mips::BGEImmMacro:
2413 case Mips::BGTImmMacro:
2414 case Mips::BLTUImmMacro:
2415 case Mips::BLEUImmMacro:
2416 case Mips::BGEUImmMacro:
2417 case Mips::BGTUImmMacro:
2418 case Mips::BLTLImmMacro:
2419 case Mips::BLELImmMacro:
2420 case Mips::BGELImmMacro:
2421 case Mips::BGTLImmMacro:
2422 case Mips::BLTULImmMacro:
2423 case Mips::BLEULImmMacro:
2424 case Mips::BGEULImmMacro:
2425 case Mips::BGTULImmMacro:
2426 return expandCondBranches(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail : MER_Success;
2427 case Mips::SDivMacro:
2428 case Mips::SDivIMacro:
2429 case Mips::SRemMacro:
2430 case Mips::SRemIMacro:
2431 return expandDivRem(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI, false, true) ? MER_Fail
2432 : MER_Success;
2433 case Mips::DSDivMacro:
2434 case Mips::DSDivIMacro:
2435 case Mips::DSRemMacro:
2436 case Mips::DSRemIMacro:
2437 return expandDivRem(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI, true, true) ? MER_Fail
2438 : MER_Success;
2439 case Mips::UDivMacro:
2440 case Mips::UDivIMacro:
2441 case Mips::URemMacro:
2442 case Mips::URemIMacro:
2443 return expandDivRem(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI, false, false) ? MER_Fail
2444 : MER_Success;
2445 case Mips::DUDivMacro:
2446 case Mips::DUDivIMacro:
2447 case Mips::DURemMacro:
2448 case Mips::DURemIMacro:
2449 return expandDivRem(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI, true, false) ? MER_Fail
2450 : MER_Success;
2451 case Mips::PseudoTRUNC_W_S:
2452 return expandTrunc(Inst, false, false, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail
2453 : MER_Success;
2454 case Mips::PseudoTRUNC_W_D32:
2455 return expandTrunc(Inst, true, false, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail
2456 : MER_Success;
2457 case Mips::PseudoTRUNC_W_D:
2458 return expandTrunc(Inst, true, true, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail
2459 : MER_Success;
2460
2461 case Mips::LoadImmSingleGPR:
2462 return expandLoadSingleImmToGPR(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail
2463 : MER_Success;
2464 case Mips::LoadImmSingleFGR:
2465 return expandLoadSingleImmToFPR(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail
2466 : MER_Success;
2467 case Mips::LoadImmDoubleGPR:
2468 return expandLoadDoubleImmToGPR(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail
2469 : MER_Success;
2470 case Mips::LoadImmDoubleFGR:
2471 return expandLoadDoubleImmToFPR(Inst, true, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail
2472 : MER_Success;
2473 case Mips::LoadImmDoubleFGR_32:
2474 return expandLoadDoubleImmToFPR(Inst, false, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail
2475 : MER_Success;
2476
2477 case Mips::Ulh:
2478 return expandUlh(Inst, true, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail : MER_Success;
2479 case Mips::Ulhu:
2480 return expandUlh(Inst, false, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail : MER_Success;
2481 case Mips::Ush:
2482 return expandUsh(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail : MER_Success;
2483 case Mips::Ulw:
2484 case Mips::Usw:
2485 return expandUxw(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail : MER_Success;
2486 case Mips::NORImm:
2487 case Mips::NORImm64:
2488 return expandAliasImmediate(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail : MER_Success;
2489 case Mips::SGE:
2490 case Mips::SGEU:
2491 return expandSge(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail : MER_Success;
2492 case Mips::SGEImm:
2493 case Mips::SGEUImm:
2494 case Mips::SGEImm64:
2495 case Mips::SGEUImm64:
2496 return expandSgeImm(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail : MER_Success;
2497 case Mips::SGTImm:
2498 case Mips::SGTUImm:
2499 case Mips::SGTImm64:
2500 case Mips::SGTUImm64:
2501 return expandSgtImm(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail : MER_Success;
2502 case Mips::SLTImm64:
2503 if (isInt<16>(Inst.getOperand(2).getImm())) {
2504 Inst.setOpcode(Mips::SLTi64);
2505 return MER_NotAMacro;
2506 }
2507 return expandAliasImmediate(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail : MER_Success;
2508 case Mips::SLTUImm64:
2509 if (isInt<16>(Inst.getOperand(2).getImm())) {
2510 Inst.setOpcode(Mips::SLTiu64);
2511 return MER_NotAMacro;
2512 }
2513 return expandAliasImmediate(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail : MER_Success;
2514 case Mips::ADDi: case Mips::ADDi_MM:
2515 case Mips::ADDiu: case Mips::ADDiu_MM:
2516 case Mips::SLTi: case Mips::SLTi_MM:
2517 case Mips::SLTiu: case Mips::SLTiu_MM:
2518 if ((Inst.getNumOperands() == 3) && Inst.getOperand(0).isReg() &&
2519 Inst.getOperand(1).isReg() && Inst.getOperand(2).isImm()) {
2520 int64_t ImmValue = Inst.getOperand(2).getImm();
2521 if (isInt<16>(ImmValue))
2522 return MER_NotAMacro;
2523 return expandAliasImmediate(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail
2524 : MER_Success;
2525 }
2526 return MER_NotAMacro;
2527 case Mips::ANDi: case Mips::ANDi_MM: case Mips::ANDi64:
2528 case Mips::ORi: case Mips::ORi_MM: case Mips::ORi64:
2529 case Mips::XORi: case Mips::XORi_MM: case Mips::XORi64:
2530 if ((Inst.getNumOperands() == 3) && Inst.getOperand(0).isReg() &&
2531 Inst.getOperand(1).isReg() && Inst.getOperand(2).isImm()) {
2532 int64_t ImmValue = Inst.getOperand(2).getImm();
2533 if (isUInt<16>(ImmValue))
2534 return MER_NotAMacro;
2535 return expandAliasImmediate(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail
2536 : MER_Success;
2537 }
2538 return MER_NotAMacro;
2539 case Mips::ROL:
2540 case Mips::ROR:
2541 return expandRotation(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail : MER_Success;
2542 case Mips::ROLImm:
2543 case Mips::RORImm:
2544 return expandRotationImm(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail : MER_Success;
2545 case Mips::DROL:
2546 case Mips::DROR:
2547 return expandDRotation(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail : MER_Success;
2548 case Mips::DROLImm:
2549 case Mips::DRORImm:
2550 return expandDRotationImm(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail : MER_Success;
2551 case Mips::ABSMacro:
2552 return expandAbs(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail : MER_Success;
2553 case Mips::MULImmMacro:
2554 case Mips::DMULImmMacro:
2555 return expandMulImm(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail : MER_Success;
2556 case Mips::MULOMacro:
2557 case Mips::DMULOMacro:
2558 return expandMulO(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail : MER_Success;
2559 case Mips::MULOUMacro:
2560 case Mips::DMULOUMacro:
2561 return expandMulOU(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail : MER_Success;
2562 case Mips::DMULMacro:
2563 return expandDMULMacro(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail : MER_Success;
2564 case Mips::LDMacro:
2565 case Mips::SDMacro:
2566 return expandLoadStoreDMacro(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI,
2567 Inst.getOpcode() == Mips::LDMacro)
2568 ? MER_Fail
2569 : MER_Success;
2570 case Mips::SDC1_M1:
2571 return expandStoreDM1Macro(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI)
2572 ? MER_Fail
2573 : MER_Success;
2574 case Mips::SEQMacro:
2575 return expandSeq(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail : MER_Success;
2576 case Mips::SEQIMacro:
2577 return expandSeqI(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail : MER_Success;
2578 case Mips::MFTC0: case Mips::MTTC0:
2579 case Mips::MFTGPR: case Mips::MTTGPR:
2580 case Mips::MFTLO: case Mips::MTTLO:
2581 case Mips::MFTHI: case Mips::MTTHI:
2582 case Mips::MFTACX: case Mips::MTTACX:
2583 case Mips::MFTDSP: case Mips::MTTDSP:
2584 case Mips::MFTC1: case Mips::MTTC1:
2585 case Mips::MFTHC1: case Mips::MTTHC1:
2586 case Mips::CFTC1: case Mips::CTTC1:
2587 return expandMXTRAlias(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail : MER_Success;
2588 }
2589}
2590
2591bool MipsAsmParser::expandJalWithRegs(MCInst &Inst, SMLoc IDLoc,
2592 MCStreamer &Out,
2593 const MCSubtargetInfo *STI) {
2594 MipsTargetStreamer &TOut = getTargetStreamer();
2595
2596 // Create a JALR instruction which is going to replace the pseudo-JAL.
2597 MCInst JalrInst;
2598 JalrInst.setLoc(IDLoc);
2599 const MCOperand FirstRegOp = Inst.getOperand(0);
2600 const unsigned Opcode = Inst.getOpcode();
2601
2602 if (Opcode == Mips::JalOneReg) {
2603 // jal $rs => jalr $rs
2604 if (IsCpRestoreSet && inMicroMipsMode()) {
2605 JalrInst.setOpcode(Mips::JALRS16_MM);
2606 JalrInst.addOperand(FirstRegOp);
2607 } else if (inMicroMipsMode()) {
2608 JalrInst.setOpcode(hasMips32r6() ? Mips::JALRC16_MMR6 : Mips::JALR16_MM);
2609 JalrInst.addOperand(FirstRegOp);
2610 } else {
2611 JalrInst.setOpcode(Mips::JALR);
2612 JalrInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(Mips::RA));
2613 JalrInst.addOperand(FirstRegOp);
2614 }
2615 } else if (Opcode == Mips::JalTwoReg) {
2616 // jal $rd, $rs => jalr $rd, $rs
2617 if (IsCpRestoreSet && inMicroMipsMode())
2618 JalrInst.setOpcode(Mips::JALRS_MM);
2619 else
2620 JalrInst.setOpcode(inMicroMipsMode() ? Mips::JALR_MM : Mips::JALR);
2621 JalrInst.addOperand(FirstRegOp);
2622 const MCOperand SecondRegOp = Inst.getOperand(1);
2623 JalrInst.addOperand(SecondRegOp);
2624 }
2625 Out.EmitInstruction(JalrInst, *STI);
2626
2627 // If .set reorder is active and branch instruction has a delay slot,
2628 // emit a NOP after it.
2629 const MCInstrDesc &MCID = getInstDesc(JalrInst.getOpcode());
2630 if (MCID.hasDelaySlot() && AssemblerOptions.back()->isReorder())
2631 TOut.emitEmptyDelaySlot(hasShortDelaySlot(JalrInst), IDLoc,
2632 STI);
2633
2634 return false;
2635}
2636
2637/// Can the value be represented by a unsigned N-bit value and a shift left?
2638template <unsigned N> static bool isShiftedUIntAtAnyPosition(uint64_t x) {
2639 unsigned BitNum = findFirstSet(x);
2640
2641 return (x == x >> BitNum << BitNum) && isUInt<N>(x >> BitNum);
2642}
2643
2644/// Load (or add) an immediate into a register.
2645///
2646/// @param ImmValue The immediate to load.
2647/// @param DstReg The register that will hold the immediate.
2648/// @param SrcReg A register to add to the immediate or Mips::NoRegister
2649/// for a simple initialization.
2650/// @param Is32BitImm Is ImmValue 32-bit or 64-bit?
2651/// @param IsAddress True if the immediate represents an address. False if it
2652/// is an integer.
2653/// @param IDLoc Location of the immediate in the source file.
2654bool MipsAsmParser::loadImmediate(int64_t ImmValue, unsigned DstReg,
2655 unsigned SrcReg, bool Is32BitImm,
2656 bool IsAddress, SMLoc IDLoc, MCStreamer &Out,
2657 const MCSubtargetInfo *STI) {
2658 MipsTargetStreamer &TOut = getTargetStreamer();
2659
2660 if (!Is32BitImm && !isGP64bit()) {
2661 Error(IDLoc, "instruction requires a 64-bit architecture");
2662 return true;
2663 }
2664
2665 if (Is32BitImm) {
2666 if (isInt<32>(ImmValue) || isUInt<32>(ImmValue)) {
2667 // Sign extend up to 64-bit so that the predicates match the hardware
2668 // behaviour. In particular, isInt<16>(0xffff8000) and similar should be
2669 // true.
2670 ImmValue = SignExtend64<32>(ImmValue);
2671 } else {
2672 Error(IDLoc, "instruction requires a 32-bit immediate");
2673 return true;
2674 }
2675 }
2676
2677 unsigned ZeroReg = IsAddress ? ABI.GetNullPtr() : ABI.GetZeroReg();
2678 unsigned AdduOp = !Is32BitImm ? Mips::DADDu : Mips::ADDu;
2679
2680 bool UseSrcReg = false;
2681 if (SrcReg != Mips::NoRegister)
2682 UseSrcReg = true;
2683
2684 unsigned TmpReg = DstReg;
2685 if (UseSrcReg &&
2686 getContext().getRegisterInfo()->isSuperOrSubRegisterEq(DstReg, SrcReg)) {
2687 // At this point we need AT to perform the expansions and we exit if it is
2688 // not available.
2689 unsigned ATReg = getATReg(IDLoc);
2690 if (!ATReg)
2691 return true;
2692 TmpReg = ATReg;
2693 }
2694
2695 if (isInt<16>(ImmValue)) {
2696 if (!UseSrcReg)
2697 SrcReg = ZeroReg;
2698
2699 // This doesn't quite follow the usual ABI expectations for N32 but matches
2700 // traditional assembler behaviour. N32 would normally use addiu for both
2701 // integers and addresses.
2702 if (IsAddress && !Is32BitImm) {
2703 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::DADDiu, DstReg, SrcReg, ImmValue, IDLoc, STI);
2704 return false;
2705 }
2706
2707 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::ADDiu, DstReg, SrcReg, ImmValue, IDLoc, STI);
2708 return false;
2709 }
2710
2711 if (isUInt<16>(ImmValue)) {
2712 unsigned TmpReg = DstReg;
2713 if (SrcReg == DstReg) {
2714 TmpReg = getATReg(IDLoc);
2715 if (!TmpReg)
2716 return true;
2717 }
2718
2719 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::ORi, TmpReg, ZeroReg, ImmValue, IDLoc, STI);
2720 if (UseSrcReg)
2721 TOut.emitRRR(ABI.GetPtrAdduOp(), DstReg, TmpReg, SrcReg, IDLoc, STI);
2722 return false;
2723 }
2724
2725 if (isInt<32>(ImmValue) || isUInt<32>(ImmValue)) {
2726 warnIfNoMacro(IDLoc);
2727
2728 uint16_t Bits31To16 = (ImmValue >> 16) & 0xffff;
2729 uint16_t Bits15To0 = ImmValue & 0xffff;
2730 if (!Is32BitImm && !isInt<32>(ImmValue)) {
2731 // Traditional behaviour seems to special case this particular value. It's
2732 // not clear why other masks are handled differently.
2733 if (ImmValue == 0xffffffff) {
2734 TOut.emitRI(Mips::LUi, TmpReg, 0xffff, IDLoc, STI);
2735 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::DSRL32, TmpReg, TmpReg, 0, IDLoc, STI);
2736 if (UseSrcReg)
2737 TOut.emitRRR(AdduOp, DstReg, TmpReg, SrcReg, IDLoc, STI);
2738 return false;
2739 }
2740
2741 // Expand to an ORi instead of a LUi to avoid sign-extending into the
2742 // upper 32 bits.
2743 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::ORi, TmpReg, ZeroReg, Bits31To16, IDLoc, STI);
2744 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::DSLL, TmpReg, TmpReg, 16, IDLoc, STI);
2745 if (Bits15To0)
2746 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::ORi, TmpReg, TmpReg, Bits15To0, IDLoc, STI);
2747 if (UseSrcReg)
2748 TOut.emitRRR(AdduOp, DstReg, TmpReg, SrcReg, IDLoc, STI);
2749 return false;
2750 }
2751
2752 TOut.emitRI(Mips::LUi, TmpReg, Bits31To16, IDLoc, STI);
2753 if (Bits15To0)
2754 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::ORi, TmpReg, TmpReg, Bits15To0, IDLoc, STI);
2755 if (UseSrcReg)
2756 TOut.emitRRR(AdduOp, DstReg, TmpReg, SrcReg, IDLoc, STI);
2757 return false;
2758 }
2759
2760 if (isShiftedUIntAtAnyPosition<16>(ImmValue)) {
2761 if (Is32BitImm) {
2762 Error(IDLoc, "instruction requires a 32-bit immediate");
2763 return true;
2764 }
2765
2766 // Traditionally, these immediates are shifted as little as possible and as
2767 // such we align the most significant bit to bit 15 of our temporary.
2768 unsigned FirstSet = findFirstSet((uint64_t)ImmValue);
2769 unsigned LastSet = findLastSet((uint64_t)ImmValue);
2770 unsigned ShiftAmount = FirstSet - (15 - (LastSet - FirstSet));
2771 uint16_t Bits = (ImmValue >> ShiftAmount) & 0xffff;
2772 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::ORi, TmpReg, ZeroReg, Bits, IDLoc, STI);
2773 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::DSLL, TmpReg, TmpReg, ShiftAmount, IDLoc, STI);
2774
2775 if (UseSrcReg)
2776 TOut.emitRRR(AdduOp, DstReg, TmpReg, SrcReg, IDLoc, STI);
2777
2778 return false;
2779 }
2780
2781 warnIfNoMacro(IDLoc);
2782
2783 // The remaining case is packed with a sequence of dsll and ori with zeros
2784 // being omitted and any neighbouring dsll's being coalesced.
2785 // The highest 32-bit's are equivalent to a 32-bit immediate load.
2786
2787 // Load bits 32-63 of ImmValue into bits 0-31 of the temporary register.
2788 if (loadImmediate(ImmValue >> 32, TmpReg, Mips::NoRegister, true, false,
2789 IDLoc, Out, STI))
2790 return false;
2791
2792 // Shift and accumulate into the register. If a 16-bit chunk is zero, then
2793 // skip it and defer the shift to the next chunk.
2794 unsigned ShiftCarriedForwards = 16;
2795 for (int BitNum = 16; BitNum >= 0; BitNum -= 16) {
2796 uint16_t ImmChunk = (ImmValue >> BitNum) & 0xffff;
2797
2798 if (ImmChunk != 0) {
2799 TOut.emitDSLL(TmpReg, TmpReg, ShiftCarriedForwards, IDLoc, STI);
2800 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::ORi, TmpReg, TmpReg, ImmChunk, IDLoc, STI);
2801 ShiftCarriedForwards = 0;
2802 }
2803
2804 ShiftCarriedForwards += 16;
2805 }
2806 ShiftCarriedForwards -= 16;
2807
2808 // Finish any remaining shifts left by trailing zeros.
2809 if (ShiftCarriedForwards)
2810 TOut.emitDSLL(TmpReg, TmpReg, ShiftCarriedForwards, IDLoc, STI);
2811
2812 if (UseSrcReg)
2813 TOut.emitRRR(AdduOp, DstReg, TmpReg, SrcReg, IDLoc, STI);
2814
2815 return false;
2816}
2817
2818bool MipsAsmParser::expandLoadImm(MCInst &Inst, bool Is32BitImm, SMLoc IDLoc,
2819 MCStreamer &Out, const MCSubtargetInfo *STI) {
2820 const MCOperand &ImmOp = Inst.getOperand(1);
2821 assert(ImmOp.isImm() && "expected immediate operand kind");
2822 const MCOperand &DstRegOp = Inst.getOperand(0);
2823 assert(DstRegOp.isReg() && "expected register operand kind");
2824
2825 if (loadImmediate(ImmOp.getImm(), DstRegOp.getReg(), Mips::NoRegister,
2826 Is32BitImm, false, IDLoc, Out, STI))
2827 return true;
2828
2829 return false;
2830}
2831
2832bool MipsAsmParser::expandLoadAddress(unsigned DstReg, unsigned BaseReg,
2833 const MCOperand &Offset,
2834 bool Is32BitAddress, SMLoc IDLoc,
2835 MCStreamer &Out,
2836 const MCSubtargetInfo *STI) {
2837 // la can't produce a usable address when addresses are 64-bit.
2838 if (Is32BitAddress && ABI.ArePtrs64bit()) {
2839 // FIXME: Demote this to a warning and continue as if we had 'dla' instead.
2840 // We currently can't do this because we depend on the equality
2841 // operator and N64 can end up with a GPR32/GPR64 mismatch.
2842 Error(IDLoc, "la used to load 64-bit address");
2843 // Continue as if we had 'dla' instead.
2844 Is32BitAddress = false;
2845 return true;
2846 }
2847
2848 // dla requires 64-bit addresses.
2849 if (!Is32BitAddress && !hasMips3()) {
2850 Error(IDLoc, "instruction requires a 64-bit architecture");
2851 return true;
2852 }
2853
2854 if (!Offset.isImm())
2855 return loadAndAddSymbolAddress(Offset.getExpr(), DstReg, BaseReg,
2856 Is32BitAddress, IDLoc, Out, STI);
2857
2858 if (!ABI.ArePtrs64bit()) {
2859 // Continue as if we had 'la' whether we had 'la' or 'dla'.
2860 Is32BitAddress = true;
2861 }
2862
2863 return loadImmediate(Offset.getImm(), DstReg, BaseReg, Is32BitAddress, true,
2864 IDLoc, Out, STI);
2865}
2866
2867bool MipsAsmParser::loadAndAddSymbolAddress(const MCExpr *SymExpr,
2868 unsigned DstReg, unsigned SrcReg,
2869 bool Is32BitSym, SMLoc IDLoc,
2870 MCStreamer &Out,
2871 const MCSubtargetInfo *STI) {
2872 // FIXME: These expansions do not respect -mxgot.
2873 MipsTargetStreamer &TOut = getTargetStreamer();
2874 bool UseSrcReg = SrcReg != Mips::NoRegister;
2875 warnIfNoMacro(IDLoc);
2876
2877 if (inPicMode() && ABI.IsO32()) {
2878 MCValue Res;
2879 if (!SymExpr->evaluateAsRelocatable(Res, nullptr, nullptr)) {
2880 Error(IDLoc, "expected relocatable expression");
2881 return true;
2882 }
2883 if (Res.getSymB() != nullptr) {
2884 Error(IDLoc, "expected relocatable expression with only one symbol");
2885 return true;
2886 }
2887
2888 // The case where the result register is $25 is somewhat special. If the
2889 // symbol in the final relocation is external and not modified with a
2890 // constant then we must use R_MIPS_CALL16 instead of R_MIPS_GOT16.
2891 if ((DstReg == Mips::T9 || DstReg == Mips::T9_64) && !UseSrcReg &&
2892 Res.getConstant() == 0 &&
2893 !(Res.getSymA()->getSymbol().isInSection() ||
2894 Res.getSymA()->getSymbol().isTemporary() ||
2895 (Res.getSymA()->getSymbol().isELF() &&
2896 cast<MCSymbolELF>(Res.getSymA()->getSymbol()).getBinding() ==
2897 ELF::STB_LOCAL))) {
2898 const MCExpr *CallExpr =
2899 MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_GOT_CALL, SymExpr, getContext());
2900 TOut.emitRRX(Mips::LW, DstReg, GPReg, MCOperand::createExpr(CallExpr),
2901 IDLoc, STI);
2902 return false;
2903 }
2904
2905 // The remaining cases are:
2906 // External GOT: lw $tmp, %got(symbol+offset)($gp)
2907 // >addiu $tmp, $tmp, %lo(offset)
2908 // >addiu $rd, $tmp, $rs
2909 // Local GOT: lw $tmp, %got(symbol+offset)($gp)
2910 // addiu $tmp, $tmp, %lo(symbol+offset)($gp)
2911 // >addiu $rd, $tmp, $rs
