5216// operand. Unlike the other alias, the m(f|t)t(lo|hi|acx) instructions
5217// do not map the DSP registers contigously to gpr registers.
5218static unsigned getRegisterForMxtrDSP(MCInst &Inst, bool IsMFDSP) {
5219 switch (Inst.getOpcode()) {
5220 case Mips::MFTLO:
5221 case Mips::MTTLO:
5222 switch (Inst.getOperand(IsMFDSP ? 1 : 0).getReg()) {
5223 case Mips::AC0:
5224 return Mips::ZERO;
5225 case Mips::AC1:
5226 return Mips::A0;
5227 case Mips::AC2:
5228 return Mips::T0;
5229 case Mips::AC3:
5230 return Mips::T4;
5231 default:
5232 llvm_unreachable("Unknown register for 'mttr' alias!");
5233 }
5234 case Mips::MFTHI:
5235 case Mips::MTTHI:
5236 switch (Inst.getOperand(IsMFDSP ? 1 : 0).getReg()) {
5237 case Mips::AC0:
5238 return Mips::AT;
5239 case Mips::AC1:
5240 return Mips::A1;
5241 case Mips::AC2:
5242 return Mips::T1;
5243 case Mips::AC3:
5244 return Mips::T5;
5245 default:
5246 llvm_unreachable("Unknown register for 'mttr' alias!");
5247 }
5248 case Mips::MFTACX:
5249 case Mips::MTTACX:
5250 switch (Inst.getOperand(IsMFDSP ? 1 : 0).getReg()) {
5251 case Mips::AC0:
5252 return Mips::V0;
5253 case Mips::AC1:
5254 return Mips::A2;
5255 case Mips::AC2:
5256 return Mips::T2;
5257 case Mips::AC3:
5258 return Mips::T6;
5259 default:
5260 llvm_unreachable("Unknown register for 'mttr' alias!");
5261 }
5262 case Mips::MFTDSP:
5263 case Mips::MTTDSP:
5264 return Mips::S0;
5265 default:
5266 llvm_unreachable("Unknown instruction for 'mttr' dsp alias!");
5267 }
5268}
5269
5270// Map the floating point register operand to the corresponding register
5271// operand.
5272static unsigned getRegisterForMxtrFP(MCInst &Inst, bool IsMFTC1) {
5273 switch (Inst.getOperand(IsMFTC1 ? 1 : 0).getReg()) {
5274 case Mips::F0: return Mips::ZERO;
5275 case Mips::F1: return Mips::AT;
5276 case Mips::F2: return Mips::V0;
5277 case Mips::F3: return Mips::V1;
5278 case Mips::F4: return Mips::A0;
5279 case Mips::F5: return Mips::A1;
5280 case Mips::F6: return Mips::A2;
5281 case Mips::F7: return Mips::A3;
5282 case Mips::F8: return Mips::T0;
5283 case Mips::F9: return Mips::T1;
5284 case Mips::F10: return Mips::T2;
5285 case Mips::F11: return Mips::T3;
5286 case Mips::F12: return Mips::T4;
5287 case Mips::F13: return Mips::T5;
5288 case Mips::F14: return Mips::T6;
5289 case Mips::F15: return Mips::T7;
5290 case Mips::F16: return Mips::S0;
5291 case Mips::F17: return Mips::S1;
5292 case Mips::F18: return Mips::S2;
5293 case Mips::F19: return Mips::S3;
5294 case Mips::F20: return Mips::S4;
5295 case Mips::F21: return Mips::S5;
5296 case Mips::F22: return Mips::S6;
5297 case Mips::F23: return Mips::S7;
5298 case Mips::F24: return Mips::T8;
5299 case Mips::F25: return Mips::T9;
5300 case Mips::F26: return Mips::K0;
5301 case Mips::F27: return Mips::K1;
5302 case Mips::F28: return Mips::GP;
5303 case Mips::F29: return Mips::SP;
5304 case Mips::F30: return Mips::FP;
5305 case Mips::F31: return Mips::RA;
5306 default: llvm_unreachable("Unknown register for mttc1 alias!");
5307 }
5308}
5309
5310// Map the coprocessor operand the corresponding gpr register operand.
5311static unsigned getRegisterForMxtrC0(MCInst &Inst, bool IsMFTC0) {
5312 switch (Inst.getOperand(IsMFTC0 ? 1 : 0).getReg()) {
5313 case Mips::COP00: return Mips::ZERO;
5314 case Mips::COP01: return Mips::AT;
5315 case Mips::COP02: return Mips::V0;
5316 case Mips::COP03: return Mips::V1;
5317 case Mips::COP04: return Mips::A0;
5318 case Mips::COP05: return Mips::A1;
5319 case Mips::COP06: return Mips::A2;
5320 case Mips::COP07: return Mips::A3;
5321 case Mips::COP08: return Mips::T0;
5322 case Mips::COP09: return Mips::T1;
5323 case Mips::COP010: return Mips::T2;
5324 case Mips::COP011: return Mips::T3;
5325 case Mips::COP012: return Mips::T4;
5326 case Mips::COP013: return Mips::T5;
5327 case Mips::COP014: return Mips::T6;
5328 case Mips::COP015: return Mips::T7;
5329 case Mips::COP016: return Mips::S0;
5330 case Mips::COP017: return Mips::S1;
5331 case Mips::COP018: return Mips::S2;
5332 case Mips::COP019: return Mips::S3;
5333 case Mips::COP020: return Mips::S4;
5334 case Mips::COP021: return Mips::S5;
5335 case Mips::COP022: return Mips::S6;
5336 case Mips::COP023: return Mips::S7;
5337 case Mips::COP024: return Mips::T8;
5338 case Mips::COP025: return Mips::T9;
5339 case Mips::COP026: return Mips::K0;
5340 case Mips::COP027: return Mips::K1;
5341 case Mips::COP028: return Mips::GP;
5342 case Mips::COP029: return Mips::SP;
5343 case Mips::COP030: return Mips::FP;
5344 case Mips::COP031: return Mips::RA;
5345 default: llvm_unreachable("Unknown register for mttc0 alias!");
5346 }
5347}
5348
5349/// Expand an alias of 'mftr' or 'mttr' into the full instruction, by producing
5350/// an mftr or mttr with the correctly mapped gpr register, u, sel and h bits.
5351bool MipsAsmParser::expandMXTRAlias(MCInst &Inst, SMLoc IDLoc, MCStreamer &Out,
5352 const MCSubtargetInfo *STI) {
5353 MipsTargetStreamer &TOut = getTargetStreamer();
5354 unsigned rd = 0;
5355 unsigned u = 1;
5356 unsigned sel = 0;
5357 unsigned h = 0;
5358 bool IsMFTR = false;
5359 switch (Inst.getOpcode()) {
5360 case Mips::MFTC0:
5361 IsMFTR = true;
5362 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
5363 case Mips::MTTC0:
5364 u = 0;
5365 rd = getRegisterForMxtrC0(Inst, IsMFTR);
5366 sel = Inst.getOperand(2).getImm();
5367 break;
5368 case Mips::MFTGPR:
5369 IsMFTR = true;
5370 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
5371 case Mips::MTTGPR:
5372 rd = Inst.getOperand(IsMFTR ? 1 : 0).getReg();
5373 break;
5374 case Mips::MFTLO:
5375 case Mips::MFTHI:
5376 case Mips::MFTACX:
5377 case Mips::MFTDSP:
5378 IsMFTR = true;
5379 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
5380 case Mips::MTTLO:
5381 case Mips::MTTHI:
5382 case Mips::MTTACX:
5383 case Mips::MTTDSP:
5384 rd = getRegisterForMxtrDSP(Inst, IsMFTR);
5385 sel = 1;
5386 break;
5387 case Mips::MFTHC1:
5388 h = 1;
5389 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
5390 case Mips::MFTC1:
5391 IsMFTR = true;
5392 rd = getRegisterForMxtrFP(Inst, IsMFTR);
5393 sel = 2;
5394 break;
5395 case Mips::MTTHC1:
5396 h = 1;
5397 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
5398 case Mips::MTTC1:
5399 rd = getRegisterForMxtrFP(Inst, IsMFTR);
5400 sel = 2;
5401 break;
5402 case Mips::CFTC1:
5403 IsMFTR = true;
5404 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
5405 case Mips::CTTC1:
5406 rd = getRegisterForMxtrFP(Inst, IsMFTR);
5407 sel = 3;
5408 break;
5409 }
5410 unsigned Op0 = IsMFTR ? Inst.getOperand(0).getReg() : rd;
5411 unsigned Op1 =
5412 IsMFTR ? rd
5413 : (Inst.getOpcode() != Mips::MTTDSP ? Inst.getOperand(1).getReg()
5414 : Inst.getOperand(0).getReg());
5415
5416 TOut.emitRRIII(IsMFTR ? Mips::MFTR : Mips::MTTR, Op0, Op1, u, sel, h, IDLoc,
5417 STI);
5418 return false;
5419}
5420
5421unsigned
5422MipsAsmParser::checkEarlyTargetMatchPredicate(MCInst &Inst,
5423 const OperandVector &Operands) {
5424 switch (Inst.getOpcode()) {
5425 default:
5426 return Match_Success;
5427 case Mips::DATI:
5428 case Mips::DAHI:
5429 if (static_cast<MipsOperand &>(*Operands[1])
5430 .isValidForTie(static_cast<MipsOperand &>(*Operands[2])))
5431 return Match_Success;
5432 return Match_RequiresSameSrcAndDst;
5433 }
5434}
5435
5436unsigned MipsAsmParser::checkTargetMatchPredicate(MCInst &Inst) {
5437 switch (Inst.getOpcode()) {
5438 // As described by the MIPSR6 spec, daui must not use the zero operand for
5439 // its source operand.
5440 case Mips::DAUI:
5441 if (Inst.getOperand(1).getReg() == Mips::ZERO ||
5442 Inst.getOperand(1).getReg() == Mips::ZERO_64)
5443 return Match_RequiresNoZeroRegister;
5444 return Match_Success;
5445 // As described by the Mips32r2 spec, the registers Rd and Rs for
5446 // jalr.hb must be different.
5447 // It also applies for registers Rt and Rs of microMIPSr6 jalrc.hb instruction
5448 // and registers Rd and Base for microMIPS lwp instruction
5449 case Mips::JALR_HB:
5450 case Mips::JALR_HB64:
5451 case Mips::JALRC_HB_MMR6:
5452 case Mips::JALRC_MMR6:
5453 if (Inst.getOperand(0).getReg() == Inst.getOperand(1).getReg())
5454 return Match_RequiresDifferentSrcAndDst;
5455 return Match_Success;
5456 case Mips::LWP_MM:
5457 if (Inst.getOperand(0).getReg() == Inst.getOperand(2).getReg())
5458 return Match_RequiresDifferentSrcAndDst;
5459 return Match_Success;
5460 case Mips::SYNC:
5461 if (Inst.getOperand(0).getImm() != 0 && !hasMips32())
5462 return Match_NonZeroOperandForSync;
5463 return Match_Success;
5464 case Mips::MFC0:
5465 case Mips::MTC0:
5466 case Mips::MTC2:
5467 case Mips::MFC2:
5468 if (Inst.getOperand(2).getImm() != 0 && !hasMips32())
5469 return Match_NonZeroOperandForMTCX;
5470 return Match_Success;
5471 // As described the MIPSR6 spec, the compact branches that compare registers
5472 // must:
5473 // a) Not use the zero register.
5474 // b) Not use the same register twice.
5475 // c) rs < rt for bnec, beqc.
5476 // NB: For this case, the encoding will swap the operands as their
5477 // ordering doesn't matter. GAS performs this transformation too.
5478 // Hence, that constraint does not have to be enforced.
5479 //
5480 // The compact branches that branch iff the signed addition of two registers
5481 // would overflow must have rs >= rt. That can be handled like beqc/bnec with
5482 // operand swapping. They do not have restriction of using the zero register.
5483 case Mips::BLEZC: case Mips::BLEZC_MMR6:
5484 case Mips::BGEZC: case Mips::BGEZC_MMR6:
5485 case Mips::BGTZC: case Mips::BGTZC_MMR6:
5486 case Mips::BLTZC: case Mips::BLTZC_MMR6:
5487 case Mips::BEQZC: case Mips::BEQZC_MMR6:
5488 case Mips::BNEZC: case Mips::BNEZC_MMR6:
5489 case Mips::BLEZC64:
5490 case Mips::BGEZC64:
5491 case Mips::BGTZC64:
5492 case Mips::BLTZC64:
5493 case Mips::BEQZC64:
5494 case Mips::BNEZC64:
5495 if (Inst.getOperand(0).getReg() == Mips::ZERO ||
5496 Inst.getOperand(0).getReg() == Mips::ZERO_64)
5497 return Match_RequiresNoZeroRegister;
5498 return Match_Success;
5499 case Mips::BGEC: case Mips::BGEC_MMR6:
5500 case Mips::BLTC: case Mips::BLTC_MMR6:
5501 case Mips::BGEUC: case Mips::BGEUC_MMR6:
5502 case Mips::BLTUC: case Mips::BLTUC_MMR6:
5503 case Mips::BEQC: case Mips::BEQC_MMR6:
5504 case Mips::BNEC: case Mips::BNEC_MMR6:
5505 case Mips::BGEC64:
5506 case Mips::BLTC64:
5507 case Mips::BGEUC64:
5508 case Mips::BLTUC64:
5509 case Mips::BEQC64:
5510 case Mips::BNEC64:
5511 if (Inst.getOperand(0).getReg() == Mips::ZERO ||
5512 Inst.getOperand(0).getReg() == Mips::ZERO_64)
5513 return Match_RequiresNoZeroRegister;
5514 if (Inst.getOperand(1).getReg() == Mips::ZERO ||
5515 Inst.getOperand(1).getReg() == Mips::ZERO_64)
5516 return Match_RequiresNoZeroRegister;
5517 if (Inst.getOperand(0).getReg() == Inst.getOperand(1).getReg())
5518 return Match_RequiresDifferentOperands;
5519 return Match_Success;
5520 case Mips::DINS: {
5521 assert(Inst.getOperand(2).isImm() && Inst.getOperand(3).isImm() &&
5522 "Operands must be immediates for dins!");
5523 const signed Pos = Inst.getOperand(2).getImm();
5524 const signed Size = Inst.getOperand(3).getImm();
5525 if ((0 > (Pos + Size)) || ((Pos + Size) > 32))
5526 return Match_RequiresPosSizeRange0_32;
5527 return Match_Success;
5528 }
5529 case Mips::DINSM:
5530 case Mips::DINSU: {
5531 assert(Inst.getOperand(2).isImm() && Inst.getOperand(3).isImm() &&
5532 "Operands must be immediates for dinsm/dinsu!");
5533 const signed Pos = Inst.getOperand(2).getImm();
5534 const signed Size = Inst.getOperand(3).getImm();
5535 if ((32 >= (Pos + Size)) || ((Pos + Size) > 64))
5536 return Match_RequiresPosSizeRange33_64;
5537 return Match_Success;
5538 }
5539 case Mips::DEXT: {
5540 assert(Inst.getOperand(2).isImm() && Inst.getOperand(3).isImm() &&
5541 "Operands must be immediates for DEXTM!");
5542 const signed Pos = Inst.getOperand(2).getImm();
5543 const signed Size = Inst.getOperand(3).getImm();
5544 if ((1 > (Pos + Size)) || ((Pos + Size) > 63))
5545 return Match_RequiresPosSizeUImm6;
5546 return Match_Success;
5547 }
5548 case Mips::DEXTM:
5549 case Mips::DEXTU: {
5550 assert(Inst.getOperand(2).isImm() && Inst.getOperand(3).isImm() &&
5551 "Operands must be immediates for dextm/dextu!");
5552 const signed Pos = Inst.getOperand(2).getImm();
5553 const signed Size = Inst.getOperand(3).getImm();
5554 if ((32 > (Pos + Size)) || ((Pos + Size) > 64))
5555 return Match_RequiresPosSizeRange33_64;
5556 return Match_Success;
5557 }
5558 case Mips::CRC32B: case Mips::CRC32CB:
5559 case Mips::CRC32H: case Mips::CRC32CH:
5560 case Mips::CRC32W: case Mips::CRC32CW:
5561 case Mips::CRC32D: case Mips::CRC32CD:
5562 if (Inst.getOperand(0).getReg() != Inst.getOperand(2).getReg())
5563 return Match_RequiresSameSrcAndDst;
5564 return Match_Success;
5565 }
5566
5567 uint64_t TSFlags = getInstDesc(Inst.getOpcode()).TSFlags;
5568 if ((TSFlags & MipsII::HasFCCRegOperand) &&
5569 (Inst.getOperand(0).getReg() != Mips::FCC0) && !hasEightFccRegisters())
5570 return Match_NoFCCRegisterForCurrentISA;
5571
5572 return Match_Success;
5573
5574}
5575
5576static SMLoc RefineErrorLoc(const SMLoc Loc, const OperandVector &Operands,
5577 uint64_t ErrorInfo) {
5578 if (ErrorInfo != ~0ULL && ErrorInfo < Operands.size()) {
5579 SMLoc ErrorLoc = Operands[ErrorInfo]->getStartLoc();
5580 if (ErrorLoc == SMLoc())
5581 return Loc;
5582 return ErrorLoc;
5583 }
5584 return Loc;
5585}
5586
5587bool MipsAsmParser::MatchAndEmitInstruction(SMLoc IDLoc, unsigned &Opcode,
5588 OperandVector &Operands,
5589 MCStreamer &Out,
5590 uint64_t &ErrorInfo,
5591 bool MatchingInlineAsm) {
5592 MCInst Inst;
5593 unsigned MatchResult =
5594 MatchInstructionImpl(Operands, Inst, ErrorInfo, MatchingInlineAsm);
5595
5596 switch (MatchResult) {
5597 case Match_Success:
5598 if (processInstruction(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI))
5599 return true;
5600 return false;
5601 case Match_MissingFeature:
5602 Error(IDLoc, "instruction requires a CPU feature not currently enabled");
5603 return true;
5604 case Match_InvalidOperand: {
5605 SMLoc ErrorLoc = IDLoc;
5606 if (ErrorInfo != ~0ULL) {
5607 if (ErrorInfo >= Operands.size())
5608 return Error(IDLoc, "too few operands for instruction");
5609
5610 ErrorLoc = Operands[ErrorInfo]->getStartLoc();
5611 if (ErrorLoc == SMLoc())
5612 ErrorLoc = IDLoc;
5613 }
5614
5615 return Error(ErrorLoc, "invalid operand for instruction");
5616 }
5617 case Match_NonZeroOperandForSync:
5618 return Error(IDLoc,
5619 "s-type must be zero or unspecified for pre-MIPS32 ISAs");
5620 case Match_NonZeroOperandForMTCX:
5621 return Error(IDLoc, "selector must be zero for pre-MIPS32 ISAs");
5622 case Match_MnemonicFail:
5623 return Error(IDLoc, "invalid instruction");
5624 case Match_RequiresDifferentSrcAndDst:
5625 return Error(IDLoc, "source and destination must be different");
5626 case Match_RequiresDifferentOperands:
5627 return Error(IDLoc, "registers must be different");
5628 case Match_RequiresNoZeroRegister:
5629 return Error(IDLoc, "invalid operand ($zero) for instruction");
5630 case Match_RequiresSameSrcAndDst:
5631 return Error(IDLoc, "source and destination must match");
5632 case Match_NoFCCRegisterForCurrentISA:
5633 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5634 "non-zero fcc register doesn't exist in current ISA level");
5635 case Match_Immz:
5636 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo), "expected '0'");
5637 case Match_UImm1_0:
5638 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5639 "expected 1-bit unsigned immediate");
5640 case Match_UImm2_0:
5641 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5642 "expected 2-bit unsigned immediate");
5643 case Match_UImm2_1:
5644 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5645 "expected immediate in range 1 .. 4");
5646 case Match_UImm3_0:
5647 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5648 "expected 3-bit unsigned immediate");
5649 case Match_UImm4_0:
5650 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5651 "expected 4-bit unsigned immediate");
5652 case Match_SImm4_0:
5653 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5654 "expected 4-bit signed immediate");
5655 case Match_UImm5_0:
5656 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5657 "expected 5-bit unsigned immediate");
5658 case Match_SImm5_0:
5659 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5660 "expected 5-bit signed immediate");
5661 case Match_UImm5_1:
5662 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5663 "expected immediate in range 1 .. 32");
5664 case Match_UImm5_32:
5665 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5666 "expected immediate in range 32 .. 63");
5667 case Match_UImm5_33:
5668 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5669 "expected immediate in range 33 .. 64");
5670 case Match_UImm5_0_Report_UImm6:
5671 // This is used on UImm5 operands that have a corresponding UImm5_32
5672 // operand to avoid confusing the user.
5673 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5674 "expected 6-bit unsigned immediate");
5675 case Match_UImm5_Lsl2:
5676 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5677 "expected both 7-bit unsigned immediate and multiple of 4");
5678 case Match_UImmRange2_64:
5679 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5680 "expected immediate in range 2 .. 64");
5681 case Match_UImm6_0:
5682 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5683 "expected 6-bit unsigned immediate");
5684 case Match_UImm6_Lsl2:
5685 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5686 "expected both 8-bit unsigned immediate and multiple of 4");
5687 case Match_SImm6_0:
5688 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5689 "expected 6-bit signed immediate");
5690 case Match_UImm7_0:
5691 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5692 "expected 7-bit unsigned immediate");
5693 case Match_UImm7_N1:
5694 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5695 "expected immediate in range -1 .. 126");
5696 case Match_SImm7_Lsl2:
5697 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5698 "expected both 9-bit signed immediate and multiple of 4");
5699 case Match_UImm8_0:
5700 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5701 "expected 8-bit unsigned immediate");
5702 case Match_UImm10_0:
5703 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5704 "expected 10-bit unsigned immediate");
5705 case Match_SImm10_0:
5706 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5707 "expected 10-bit signed immediate");
5708 case Match_SImm11_0:
5709 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5710 "expected 11-bit signed immediate");
5711 case Match_UImm16:
5712 case Match_UImm16_Relaxed:
5713 case Match_UImm16_AltRelaxed:
5714 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5715 "expected 16-bit unsigned immediate");
5716 case Match_SImm16:
5717 case Match_SImm16_Relaxed:
5718 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5719 "expected 16-bit signed immediate");
5720 case Match_SImm19_Lsl2:
5721 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5722 "expected both 19-bit signed immediate and multiple of 4");
5723 case Match_UImm20_0:
5724 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5725 "expected 20-bit unsigned immediate");
5726 case Match_UImm26_0:
5727 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5728 "expected 26-bit unsigned immediate");
5729 case Match_SImm32:
5730 case Match_SImm32_Relaxed:
5731 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5732 "expected 32-bit signed immediate");
5733 case Match_UImm32_Coerced:
5734 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5735 "expected 32-bit immediate");
5736 case Match_MemSImm9:
5737 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5738 "expected memory with 9-bit signed offset");
5739 case Match_MemSImm10:
5740 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5741 "expected memory with 10-bit signed offset");
5742 case Match_MemSImm10Lsl1:
5743 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5744 "expected memory with 11-bit signed offset and multiple of 2");
5745 case Match_MemSImm10Lsl2:
5746 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5747 "expected memory with 12-bit signed offset and multiple of 4");
5748 case Match_MemSImm10Lsl3:
5749 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5750 "expected memory with 13-bit signed offset and multiple of 8");
5751 case Match_MemSImm11:
5752 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5753 "expected memory with 11-bit signed offset");
5754 case Match_MemSImm12:
5755 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5756 "expected memory with 12-bit signed offset");
5757 case Match_MemSImm16:
5758 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5759 "expected memory with 16-bit signed offset");
5760 case Match_MemSImmPtr:
5761 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5762 "expected memory with 32-bit signed offset");
5763 case Match_RequiresPosSizeRange0_32: {
5764 SMLoc ErrorStart = Operands[3]->getStartLoc();
5765 SMLoc ErrorEnd = Operands[4]->getEndLoc();
5766 return Error(ErrorStart, "size plus position are not in the range 0 .. 32",
5767 SMRange(ErrorStart, ErrorEnd));
5768 }
5769 case Match_RequiresPosSizeUImm6: {
5770 SMLoc ErrorStart = Operands[3]->getStartLoc();
5771 SMLoc ErrorEnd = Operands[4]->getEndLoc();
5772 return Error(ErrorStart, "size plus position are not in the range 1 .. 63",
5773 SMRange(ErrorStart, ErrorEnd));
5774 }
5775 case Match_RequiresPosSizeRange33_64: {
5776 SMLoc ErrorStart = Operands[3]->getStartLoc();
5777 SMLoc ErrorEnd = Operands[4]->getEndLoc();
5778 return Error(ErrorStart, "size plus position are not in the range 33 .. 64",
5779 SMRange(ErrorStart, ErrorEnd));
5780 }
5781 }
5782
5783 llvm_unreachable("Implement any new match types added!");
5784}
5785
5786void MipsAsmParser::warnIfRegIndexIsAT(unsigned RegIndex, SMLoc Loc) {
5787 if (RegIndex != 0 && AssemblerOptions.back()->getATRegIndex() == RegIndex)
5788 Warning(Loc, "used $at (currently $" + Twine(RegIndex) +
5789 ") without \".set noat\"");
5790}

5792void MipsAsmParser::warnIfNoMacro(SMLoc Loc) {
5793 if (!AssemblerOptions.back()->isMacro())
5794 Warning(Loc, "macro instruction expanded into multiple instructions");
5795}
5796
5797void MipsAsmParser::ConvertXWPOperands(MCInst &Inst,
5798 const OperandVector &Operands) {
5799 assert(
5800 (Inst.getOpcode() == Mips::LWP_MM || Inst.getOpcode() == Mips::SWP_MM) &&
5801 "Unexpected instruction!");
5802 ((MipsOperand &)*Operands[1]).addGPR32ZeroAsmRegOperands(Inst, 1);
5803 int NextReg = nextReg(((MipsOperand &)*Operands[1]).getGPR32Reg());
5804 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(NextReg));
5805 ((MipsOperand &)*Operands[2]).addMemOperands(Inst, 2);
5806}

5808void
5809MipsAsmParser::printWarningWithFixIt(const Twine &Msg, const Twine &FixMsg,
5810 SMRange Range, bool ShowColors) {
5811 getSourceManager().PrintMessage(Range.Start, SourceMgr::DK_Warning, Msg,
5812 Range, SMFixIt(Range, FixMsg),
5813 ShowColors);
5814}
5815
5816int MipsAsmParser::matchCPURegisterName(StringRef Name) {
5817 int CC;
5818
5819 CC = StringSwitch<unsigned>(Name)
5820 .Case("zero", 0)
5821 .Cases("at", "AT", 1)
5822 .Case("a0", 4)
5823 .Case("a1", 5)
5824 .Case("a2", 6)
5825 .Case("a3", 7)
5826 .Case("v0", 2)
5827 .Case("v1", 3)
5828 .Case("s0", 16)
5829 .Case("s1", 17)
5830 .Case("s2", 18)
5831 .Case("s3", 19)
5832 .Case("s4", 20)
5833 .Case("s5", 21)
5834 .Case("s6", 22)
5835 .Case("s7", 23)
5836 .Case("k0", 26)
5837 .Case("k1", 27)
5838 .Case("gp", 28)
5839 .Case("sp", 29)
5840 .Case("fp", 30)
5841 .Case("s8", 30)
5842 .Case("ra", 31)
5843 .Case("t0", 8)
5844 .Case("t1", 9)
5845 .Case("t2", 10)
5846 .Case("t3", 11)
5847 .Case("t4", 12)
5848 .Case("t5", 13)
5849 .Case("t6", 14)
5850 .Case("t7", 15)
5851 .Case("t8", 24)
5852 .Case("t9", 25)
5853 .Default(-1);
5854
5855 if (!(isABI_N32() || isABI_N64()))
5856 return CC;
5857
5858 if (12 <= CC && CC <= 15) {
5859 // Name is one of t4-t7
5860 AsmToken RegTok = getLexer().peekTok();
5861 SMRange RegRange = RegTok.getLocRange();
5862
5863 StringRef FixedName = StringSwitch<StringRef>(Name)
5864 .Case("t4", "t0")
5865 .Case("t5", "t1")
5866 .Case("t6", "t2")
5867 .Case("t7", "t3")
5868 .Default("");
5869 assert(FixedName != "" && "Register name is not one of t4-t7.");
5870
5871 printWarningWithFixIt("register names $t4-$t7 are only available in O32.",
5872 "Did you mean $" + FixedName + "?", RegRange);
5873 }
5874
5875 // Although SGI documentation just cuts out t0-t3 for n32/n64,
5876 // GNU pushes the values of t0-t3 to override the o32/o64 values for t4-t7
5877 // We are supporting both cases, so for t0-t3 we'll just push them to t4-t7.
5878 if (8 <= CC && CC <= 11)
5879 CC += 4;
5880
5881 if (CC == -1)
5882 CC = StringSwitch<unsigned>(Name)
5883 .Case("a4", 8)
5884 .Case("a5", 9)
5885 .Case("a6", 10)
5886 .Case("a7", 11)
5887 .Case("kt0", 26)
5888 .Case("kt1", 27)
5889 .Default(-1);
5890
5891 return CC;
5892}
5893
5894int MipsAsmParser::matchHWRegsRegisterName(StringRef Name) {
5895 int CC;
5896
5897 CC = StringSwitch<unsigned>(Name)
5898 .Case("hwr_cpunum", 0)
5899 .Case("hwr_synci_step", 1)
5900 .Case("hwr_cc", 2)
5901 .Case("hwr_ccres", 3)
5902 .Case("hwr_ulr", 29)
5903 .Default(-1);
5904
5905 return CC;
5906}
5907
5908int MipsAsmParser::matchFPURegisterName(StringRef Name) {
5909 if (Name[0] == 'f') {
5910 StringRef NumString = Name.substr(1);
5911 unsigned IntVal;
5912 if (NumString.getAsInteger(10, IntVal))
5913 return -1; // This is not an integer.
5914 if (IntVal > 31) // Maximum index for fpu register.
5915 return -1;
5916 return IntVal;
5917 }
5918 return -1;
5919}
5920
5921int MipsAsmParser::matchFCCRegisterName(StringRef Name) {
5922 if (Name.startswith("fcc")) {
5923 StringRef NumString = Name.substr(3);
5924 unsigned IntVal;
5925 if (NumString.getAsInteger(10, IntVal))
5926 return -1; // This is not an integer.
5927 if (IntVal > 7) // There are only 8 fcc registers.
5928 return -1;
5929 return IntVal;
5930 }
5931 return -1;
5932}
5933
5934int MipsAsmParser::matchACRegisterName(StringRef Name) {
5935 if (Name.startswith("ac")) {
5936 StringRef NumString = Name.substr(2);
5937 unsigned IntVal;
5938 if (NumString.getAsInteger(10, IntVal))
5939 return -1; // This is not an integer.
5940 if (IntVal > 3) // There are only 3 acc registers.
5941 return -1;
5942 return IntVal;
5943 }
5944 return -1;
5945}
5946
5947int MipsAsmParser::matchMSA128RegisterName(StringRef Name) {
5948 unsigned IntVal;
5949
5950 if (Name.front() != 'w' || Name.drop_front(1).getAsInteger(10, IntVal))
5951 return -1;
5952
5953 if (IntVal > 31)
5954 return -1;
5955
5956 return IntVal;
5957}
5958
5959int MipsAsmParser::matchMSA128CtrlRegisterName(StringRef Name) {
5960 int CC;
5961
5962 CC = StringSwitch<unsigned>(Name)
5963 .Case("msair", 0)
5964 .Case("msacsr", 1)
5965 .Case("msaaccess", 2)
5966 .Case("msasave", 3)
5967 .Case("msamodify", 4)
5968 .Case("msarequest", 5)
5969 .Case("msamap", 6)
5970 .Case("msaunmap", 7)
5971 .Default(-1);
5972
5973 return CC;
5974}

5976bool MipsAsmParser::canUseATReg() {
5977 return AssemblerOptions.back()->getATRegIndex() != 0;
5978}
5979
5980unsigned MipsAsmParser::getATReg(SMLoc Loc) {
5981 unsigned ATIndex = AssemblerOptions.back()->getATRegIndex();
5982 if (ATIndex == 0) {
5983 reportParseError(Loc,
5984 "pseudo-instruction requires $at, which is not available");
5985 return 0;
5986 }
5987 unsigned AT = getReg(
5988 (isGP64bit()) ? Mips::GPR64RegClassID : Mips::GPR32RegClassID, ATIndex);
5989 return AT;
5990}
5991
5992unsigned MipsAsmParser::getReg(int RC, int RegNo) {
5993 return *(getContext().getRegisterInfo()->getRegClass(RC).begin() + RegNo);
5994}
5995
5996bool MipsAsmParser::parseOperand(OperandVector &Operands, StringRef Mnemonic) {
5997 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
5998 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "parseOperand\n");
5999
6000 // Check if the current operand has a custom associated parser, if so, try to
6001 // custom parse the operand, or fallback to the general approach.
6002 OperandMatchResultTy ResTy = MatchOperandParserImpl(Operands, Mnemonic);
6003 if (ResTy == MatchOperand_Success)
6004 return false;
6005 // If there wasn't a custom match, try the generic matcher below. Otherwise,
6006 // there was a match, but an error occurred, in which case, just return that
6007 // the operand parsing failed.
6008 if (ResTy == MatchOperand_ParseFail)
6009 return true;
6010
6011 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << ".. Generic Parser\n");
6012
6013 switch (getLexer().getKind()) {
6014 case AsmToken::Dollar: {
6015 // Parse the register.
6016 SMLoc S = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
6017
6018 // Almost all registers have been parsed by custom parsers. There is only
6019 // one exception to this. $zero (and it's alias $0) will reach this point
6020 // for div, divu, and similar instructions because it is not an operand
6021 // to the instruction definition but an explicit register. Special case
6022 // this situation for now.
6023 if (parseAnyRegister(Operands) != MatchOperand_NoMatch)
6024 return false;
6025
6026 // Maybe it is a symbol reference.
6027 StringRef Identifier;
6028 if (Parser.parseIdentifier(Identifier))
6029 return true;
6030
6031 SMLoc E = SMLoc::getFromPointer(Parser.getTok().getLoc().getPointer() - 1);
6032 MCSymbol *Sym = getContext().getOrCreateSymbol("$" + Identifier);
6033 // Otherwise create a symbol reference.
6034 const MCExpr *Res =
6035 MCSymbolRefExpr::create(Sym, MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_None, getContext());
6036
6037 Operands.push_back(MipsOperand::CreateImm(Res, S, E, *this));
6038 return false;
6039 }
6040 default: {
6041 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << ".. generic integer expression\n");
6042
6043 const MCExpr *Expr;
6044 SMLoc S = Parser.getTok().getLoc(); // Start location of the operand.
6045 if (getParser().parseExpression(Expr))
6046 return true;
6047
6048 SMLoc E = SMLoc::getFromPointer(Parser.getTok().getLoc().getPointer() - 1);
6049
6050 Operands.push_back(MipsOperand::CreateImm(Expr, S, E, *this));
6051 return false;
6052 }
6053 } // switch(getLexer().getKind())
6054 return true;
6055}
6056
6057bool MipsAsmParser::isEvaluated(const MCExpr *Expr) {
6058 switch (Expr->getKind()) {
6059 case MCExpr::Constant:
6060 return true;
6061 case MCExpr::SymbolRef:
6062 return (cast<MCSymbolRefExpr>(Expr)->getKind() != MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_None);
6063 case MCExpr::Binary: {
6064 const MCBinaryExpr *BE = cast<MCBinaryExpr>(Expr);
6065 if (!isEvaluated(BE->getLHS()))
6066 return false;
6067 return isEvaluated(BE->getRHS());
6068 }
6069 case MCExpr::Unary:
6070 return isEvaluated(cast<MCUnaryExpr>(Expr)->getSubExpr());
6071 case MCExpr::Target:
6072 return true;
6073 }
6074 return false;
6075}
6076
6077bool MipsAsmParser::ParseRegister(unsigned &RegNo, SMLoc &StartLoc,
6078 SMLoc &EndLoc) {
6079 SmallVector<std::unique_ptr<MCParsedAsmOperand>, 1> Operands;
6080 OperandMatchResultTy ResTy = parseAnyRegister(Operands);
6081 if (ResTy == MatchOperand_Success) {
6082 assert(Operands.size() == 1);
6083 MipsOperand &Operand = static_cast<MipsOperand &>(*Operands.front());
6084 StartLoc = Operand.getStartLoc();
6085 EndLoc = Operand.getEndLoc();
6086
6087 // AFAIK, we only support numeric registers and named GPR's in CFI
6088 // directives.
6089 // Don't worry about eating tokens before failing. Using an unrecognised
6090 // register is a parse error.
6091 if (Operand.isGPRAsmReg()) {
6092 // Resolve to GPR32 or GPR64 appropriately.
6093 RegNo = isGP64bit() ? Operand.getGPR64Reg() : Operand.getGPR32Reg();
6094 }
6095
6096 return (RegNo == (unsigned)-1);
6097 }
6098
6099 assert(Operands.size() == 0);
6100 return (RegNo == (unsigned)-1);
6101}
6102
6103bool MipsAsmParser::parseMemOffset(const MCExpr *&Res, bool isParenExpr) {
6104 SMLoc S;
6105
6106 if (isParenExpr)
6107 return getParser().parseParenExprOfDepth(0, Res, S);
6108 return getParser().parseExpression(Res);
6109}
6110
6111OperandMatchResultTy
6112MipsAsmParser::parseMemOperand(OperandVector &Operands) {
6113 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
6114 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "parseMemOperand\n");
6115 const MCExpr *IdVal = nullptr;
6116 SMLoc S;
6117 bool isParenExpr = false;
6118 OperandMatchResultTy Res = MatchOperand_NoMatch;
6119 // First operand is the offset.
6120 S = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
6121
6122 if (getLexer().getKind() == AsmToken::LParen) {
6123 Parser.Lex();
6124 isParenExpr = true;
6125 }
6126
6127 if (getLexer().getKind() != AsmToken::Dollar) {
6128 if (parseMemOffset(IdVal, isParenExpr))
6129 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
6130
6131 const AsmToken &Tok = Parser.getTok(); // Get the next token.
6132 if (Tok.isNot(AsmToken::LParen)) {
6133 MipsOperand &Mnemonic = static_cast<MipsOperand &>(*Operands[0]);
6134 if (Mnemonic.getToken() == "la" || Mnemonic.getToken() == "dla") {
6135 SMLoc E =
6136 SMLoc::getFromPointer(Parser.getTok().getLoc().getPointer() - 1);
6137 Operands.push_back(MipsOperand::CreateImm(IdVal, S, E, *this));
6138 return MatchOperand_Success;
6139 }
6140 if (Tok.is(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
6141 SMLoc E =
6142 SMLoc::getFromPointer(Parser.getTok().getLoc().getPointer() - 1);
6143
6144 // Zero register assumed, add a memory operand with ZERO as its base.
6145 // "Base" will be managed by k_Memory.
6146 auto Base = MipsOperand::createGPRReg(
6147 0, "0", getContext().getRegisterInfo(), S, E, *this);
6148 Operands.push_back(
6149 MipsOperand::CreateMem(std::move(Base), IdVal, S, E, *this));
6150 return MatchOperand_Success;
6151 }
6152 MCBinaryExpr::Opcode Opcode;
6153 // GAS and LLVM treat comparison operators different. GAS will generate -1
6154 // or 0, while LLVM will generate 0 or 1. Since a comparsion operator is
6155 // highly unlikely to be found in a memory offset expression, we don't
6156 // handle them.
6157 switch (Tok.getKind()) {
6158 case AsmToken::Plus:
6159 Opcode = MCBinaryExpr::Add;
6160 Parser.Lex();
6161 break;
6162 case AsmToken::Minus:
6163 Opcode = MCBinaryExpr::Sub;
6164 Parser.Lex();
6165 break;
6166 case AsmToken::Star:
6167 Opcode = MCBinaryExpr::Mul;
6168 Parser.Lex();
6169 break;
6170 case AsmToken::Pipe:
6171 Opcode = MCBinaryExpr::Or;
6172 Parser.Lex();
6173 break;
6174 case AsmToken::Amp:
6175 Opcode = MCBinaryExpr::And;
6176 Parser.Lex();
6177 break;
6178 case AsmToken::LessLess:
6179 Opcode = MCBinaryExpr::Shl;
6180 Parser.Lex();
6181 break;
6182 case AsmToken::GreaterGreater:
6183 Opcode = MCBinaryExpr::LShr;
6184 Parser.Lex();
6185 break;
6186 case AsmToken::Caret:
6187 Opcode = MCBinaryExpr::Xor;
6188 Parser.Lex();
6189 break;
6190 case AsmToken::Slash:
6191 Opcode = MCBinaryExpr::Div;
6192 Parser.Lex();
6193 break;
6194 case AsmToken::Percent:
6195 Opcode = MCBinaryExpr::Mod;
6196 Parser.Lex();
6197 break;
6198 default:
6199 Error(Parser.getTok().getLoc(), "'(' or expression expected");
6200 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
6201 }
6202 const MCExpr * NextExpr;
6203 if (getParser().parseExpression(NextExpr))
6204 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
6205 IdVal = MCBinaryExpr::create(Opcode, IdVal, NextExpr, getContext());
6206 }
6207
6208 Parser.Lex(); // Eat the '(' token.
6209 }
6210
6211 Res = parseAnyRegister(Operands);
6212 if (Res != MatchOperand_Success)
6213 return Res;
6214
6215 if (Parser.getTok().isNot(AsmToken::RParen)) {
6216 Error(Parser.getTok().getLoc(), "')' expected");
6217 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
6218 }
6219
6220 SMLoc E = SMLoc::getFromPointer(Parser.getTok().getLoc().getPointer() - 1);
6221
6222 Parser.Lex(); // Eat the ')' token.
6223
6224 if (!IdVal)
6225 IdVal = MCConstantExpr::create(0, getContext());
6226
6227 // Replace the register operand with the memory operand.
6228 std::unique_ptr<MipsOperand> op(
6229 static_cast<MipsOperand *>(Operands.back().release()));
6230 // Remove the register from the operands.
6231 // "op" will be managed by k_Memory.
6232 Operands.pop_back();
6233 // Add the memory operand.
6234 if (const MCBinaryExpr *BE = dyn_cast<MCBinaryExpr>(IdVal)) {
6235 int64_t Imm;
6236 if (IdVal->evaluateAsAbsolute(Imm))
6237 IdVal = MCConstantExpr::create(Imm, getContext());
6238 else if (BE->getLHS()->getKind() != MCExpr::SymbolRef)
6239 IdVal = MCBinaryExpr::create(BE->getOpcode(), BE->getRHS(), BE->getLHS(),
6240 getContext());
6241 }
6242
6243 Operands.push_back(MipsOperand::CreateMem(std::move(op), IdVal, S, E, *this));
6244 return MatchOperand_Success;
6245}
6246
6247bool MipsAsmParser::searchSymbolAlias(OperandVector &Operands) {
6248 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
6249 MCSymbol *Sym = getContext().lookupSymbol(Parser.getTok().getIdentifier());
6250 if (!Sym)
6251 return false;
6252
6253 SMLoc S = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
6254 if (Sym->isVariable()) {
6255 const MCExpr *Expr = Sym->getVariableValue();
6256 if (Expr->getKind() == MCExpr::SymbolRef) {
6257 const MCSymbolRefExpr *Ref = static_cast<const MCSymbolRefExpr *>(Expr);
6258 StringRef DefSymbol = Ref->getSymbol().getName();
6259 if (DefSymbol.startswith("$")) {
6260 OperandMatchResultTy ResTy =
6261 matchAnyRegisterNameWithoutDollar(Operands, DefSymbol.substr(1), S);
6262 if (ResTy == MatchOperand_Success) {
6263 Parser.Lex();
6264 return true;
6265 }
6266 if (ResTy == MatchOperand_ParseFail)
6267 llvm_unreachable("Should never ParseFail");
6268 }
6269 }
6270 } else if (Sym->isUnset()) {
6271 // If symbol is unset, it might be created in the `parseSetAssignment`
6272 // routine as an alias for a numeric register name.
6273 // Lookup in the aliases list.
6274 auto Entry = RegisterSets.find(Sym->getName());
6275 if (Entry != RegisterSets.end()) {
6276 OperandMatchResultTy ResTy =
6277 matchAnyRegisterWithoutDollar(Operands, Entry->getValue(), S);
6278 if (ResTy == MatchOperand_Success) {
6279 Parser.Lex();
6280 return true;
6281 }
6282 }
6283 }
6284
6285 return false;
6286}
6287
6288OperandMatchResultTy
6289MipsAsmParser::matchAnyRegisterNameWithoutDollar(OperandVector &Operands,
6290 StringRef Identifier,
6291 SMLoc S) {
6292 int Index = matchCPURegisterName(Identifier);
6293 if (Index != -1) {
6294 Operands.push_back(MipsOperand::createGPRReg(
6295 Index, Identifier, getContext().getRegisterInfo(), S,
6296 getLexer().getLoc(), *this));
6297 return MatchOperand_Success;
6298 }
6299
6300 Index = matchHWRegsRegisterName(Identifier);
6301 if (Index != -1) {
6302 Operands.push_back(MipsOperand::createHWRegsReg(
6303 Index, Identifier, getContext().getRegisterInfo(), S,
6304 getLexer().getLoc(), *this));
6305 return MatchOperand_Success;
6306 }
6307
6308 Index = matchFPURegisterName(Identifier);
6309 if (Index != -1) {
6310 Operands.push_back(MipsOperand::createFGRReg(
6311 Index, Identifier, getContext().getRegisterInfo(), S,
6312 getLexer().getLoc(), *this));
6313 return MatchOperand_Success;
6314 }
6315
6316 Index = matchFCCRegisterName(Identifier);
6317 if (Index != -1) {
6318 Operands.push_back(MipsOperand::createFCCReg(
6319 Index, Identifier, getContext().getRegisterInfo(), S,
6320 getLexer().getLoc(), *this));
6321 return MatchOperand_Success;
6322 }
6323
6324 Index = matchACRegisterName(Identifier);
6325 if (Index != -1) {
6326 Operands.push_back(MipsOperand::createACCReg(
6327 Index, Identifier, getContext().getRegisterInfo(), S,
6328 getLexer().getLoc(), *this));
6329 return MatchOperand_Success;
6330 }
6331
6332 Index = matchMSA128RegisterName(Identifier);
6333 if (Index != -1) {
6334 Operands.push_back(MipsOperand::createMSA128Reg(
6335 Index, Identifier, getContext().getRegisterInfo(), S,
6336 getLexer().getLoc(), *this));
6337 return MatchOperand_Success;
6338 }
6339
6340 Index = matchMSA128CtrlRegisterName(Identifier);
6341 if (Index != -1) {
6342 Operands.push_back(MipsOperand::createMSACtrlReg(
6343 Index, Identifier, getContext().getRegisterInfo(), S,
6344 getLexer().getLoc(), *this));
6345 return MatchOperand_Success;
6346 }
6347
6348 return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
6349}
6350
6351OperandMatchResultTy
6352MipsAsmParser::matchAnyRegisterWithoutDollar(OperandVector &Operands,
6353 const AsmToken &Token, SMLoc S) {
6354 if (Token.is(AsmToken::Identifier)) {
6355 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << ".. identifier\n");
6356 StringRef Identifier = Token.getIdentifier();
6357 OperandMatchResultTy ResTy =
6358 matchAnyRegisterNameWithoutDollar(Operands, Identifier, S);
6359 return ResTy;
6360 } else if (Token.is(AsmToken::Integer)) {
6361 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << ".. integer\n");
6362 int64_t RegNum = Token.getIntVal();
6363 if (RegNum < 0 || RegNum > 31) {
6364 // Show the error, but treat invalid register
6365 // number as a normal one to continue parsing
6366 // and catch other possible errors.
6367 Error(getLexer().getLoc(), "invalid register number");
6368 }
6369 Operands.push_back(MipsOperand::createNumericReg(
6370 RegNum, Token.getString(), getContext().getRegisterInfo(), S,
6371 Token.getLoc(), *this));
6372 return MatchOperand_Success;
6373 }
6374
6375 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << Token.getKind() << "\n");
6376
6377 return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
6378}
6379
6380OperandMatchResultTy
6381MipsAsmParser::matchAnyRegisterWithoutDollar(OperandVector &Operands, SMLoc S) {
6382 auto Token = getLexer().peekTok(false);
6383 return matchAnyRegisterWithoutDollar(Operands, Token, S);
6384}
6385
6386OperandMatchResultTy
6387MipsAsmParser::parseAnyRegister(OperandVector &Operands) {
6388 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
6389 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "parseAnyRegister\n");
6390
6391 auto Token = Parser.getTok();
6392
6393 SMLoc S = Token.getLoc();
6394
6395 if (Token.isNot(AsmToken::Dollar)) {
6396 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << ".. !$ -> try sym aliasing\n");
6397 if (Token.is(AsmToken::Identifier)) {
6398 if (searchSymbolAlias(Operands))
6399 return MatchOperand_Success;
6400 }
6401 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << ".. !symalias -> NoMatch\n");
6402 return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
6403 }
6404 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << ".. $\n");
6405
6406 OperandMatchResultTy ResTy = matchAnyRegisterWithoutDollar(Operands, S);
6407 if (ResTy == MatchOperand_Success) {
6408 Parser.Lex(); // $
6409 Parser.Lex(); // identifier
6410 }
6411 return ResTy;
6412}
6413
6414OperandMatchResultTy
6415MipsAsmParser::parseJumpTarget(OperandVector &Operands) {
6416 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
6417 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "parseJumpTarget\n");
6418
6419 SMLoc S = getLexer().getLoc();
6420
6421 // Registers are a valid target and have priority over symbols.
6422 OperandMatchResultTy ResTy = parseAnyRegister(Operands);
6423 if (ResTy != MatchOperand_NoMatch)
6424 return ResTy;
6425
6426 // Integers and expressions are acceptable
6427 const MCExpr *Expr = nullptr;
6428 if (Parser.parseExpression(Expr)) {
6429 // We have no way of knowing if a symbol was consumed so we must ParseFail
6430 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
6431 }
6432 Operands.push_back(
6433 MipsOperand::CreateImm(Expr, S, getLexer().getLoc(), *this));
6434 return MatchOperand_Success;
6435}
6436
6437OperandMatchResultTy
6438MipsAsmParser::parseInvNum(OperandVector &Operands) {
6439 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
6440 const MCExpr *IdVal;
6441 // If the first token is '$' we may have register operand. We have to reject
6442 // cases where it is not a register. Complicating the matter is that
6443 // register names are not reserved across all ABIs.
6444 // Peek past the dollar to see if it's a register name for this ABI.
6445 SMLoc S = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
6446 if (Parser.getTok().is(AsmToken::Dollar)) {
6447 return matchCPURegisterName(Parser.getLexer().peekTok().getString()) == -1
6448 ? MatchOperand_ParseFail
6449 : MatchOperand_NoMatch;
6450 }
6451 if (getParser().parseExpression(IdVal))
6452 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
6453 const MCConstantExpr *MCE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(IdVal);
6454 if (!MCE)
6455 return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
6456 int64_t Val = MCE->getValue();
6457 SMLoc E = SMLoc::getFromPointer(Parser.getTok().getLoc().getPointer() - 1);
6458 Operands.push_back(MipsOperand::CreateImm(
6459 MCConstantExpr::create(0 - Val, getContext()), S, E, *this));
6460 return MatchOperand_Success;
6461}
6462
6463OperandMatchResultTy
6464MipsAsmParser::parseRegisterList(OperandVector &Operands) {
6465 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
6466 SmallVector<unsigned, 10> Regs;
6467 unsigned RegNo;
6468 unsigned PrevReg = Mips::NoRegister;
6469 bool RegRange = false;
6470 SmallVector<std::unique_ptr<MCParsedAsmOperand>, 8> TmpOperands;
6471
6472 if (Parser.getTok().isNot(AsmToken::Dollar))
6473 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
6474
6475 SMLoc S = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
6476 while (parseAnyRegister(TmpOperands) == MatchOperand_Success) {
6477 SMLoc E = getLexer().getLoc();
6478 MipsOperand &Reg = static_cast<MipsOperand &>(*TmpOperands.back());
6479 RegNo = isGP64bit() ? Reg.getGPR64Reg() : Reg.getGPR32Reg();
6480 if (RegRange) {
6481 // Remove last register operand because registers from register range
6482 // should be inserted first.
6483 if ((isGP64bit() && RegNo == Mips::RA_64) ||
6484 (!isGP64bit() && RegNo == Mips::RA)) {
6485 Regs.push_back(RegNo);
6486 } else {
6487 unsigned TmpReg = PrevReg + 1;
6488 while (TmpReg <= RegNo) {
6489 if ((((TmpReg < Mips::S0) || (TmpReg > Mips::S7)) && !isGP64bit()) ||
6490 (((TmpReg < Mips::S0_64) || (TmpReg > Mips::S7_64)) &&
6491 isGP64bit())) {
6492 Error(E, "invalid register operand");
6493 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
6494 }
6495
6496 PrevReg = TmpReg;
6497 Regs.push_back(TmpReg++);
6498 }
6499 }
6500
6501 RegRange = false;
6502 } else {
6503 if ((PrevReg == Mips::NoRegister) &&
6504 ((isGP64bit() && (RegNo != Mips::S0_64) && (RegNo != Mips::RA_64)) ||
6505 (!isGP64bit() && (RegNo != Mips::S0) && (RegNo != Mips::RA)))) {
6506 Error(E, "$16 or $31 expected");
6507 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
6508 } else if (!(((RegNo == Mips::FP || RegNo == Mips::RA ||
6509 (RegNo >= Mips::S0 && RegNo <= Mips::S7)) &&
6510 !isGP64bit()) ||
6511 ((RegNo == Mips::FP_64 || RegNo == Mips::RA_64 ||
6512 (RegNo >= Mips::S0_64 && RegNo <= Mips::S7_64)) &&
6513 isGP64bit()))) {
6514 Error(E, "invalid register operand");
6515 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
6516 } else if ((PrevReg != Mips::NoRegister) && (RegNo != PrevReg + 1) &&
6517 ((RegNo != Mips::FP && RegNo != Mips::RA && !isGP64bit()) ||
6518 (RegNo != Mips::FP_64 && RegNo != Mips::RA_64 &&
6519 isGP64bit()))) {
6520 Error(E, "consecutive register numbers expected");
6521 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
6522 }
6523
6524 Regs.push_back(RegNo);
6525 }
6526
6527 if (Parser.getTok().is(AsmToken::Minus))
6528 RegRange = true;
6529
6530 if (!Parser.getTok().isNot(AsmToken::Minus) &&
6531 !Parser.getTok().isNot(AsmToken::Comma)) {
6532 Error(E, "',' or '-' expected");
6533 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
6534 }
6535
6536 Lex(); // Consume comma or minus
6537 if (Parser.getTok().isNot(AsmToken::Dollar))
6538 break;
6539
6540 PrevReg = RegNo;
6541 }
6542
6543 SMLoc E = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
6544 Operands.push_back(MipsOperand::CreateRegList(Regs, S, E, *this));
6545 parseMemOperand(Operands);
6546 return MatchOperand_Success;
6547}
6548
6549/// Sometimes (i.e. load/stores) the operand may be followed immediately by
6550/// either this.
6551/// ::= '(', register, ')'
6552/// handle it before we iterate so we don't get tripped up by the lack of
6553/// a comma.
6554bool MipsAsmParser::parseParenSuffix(StringRef Name, OperandVector &Operands) {
6555 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
6556 if (getLexer().is(AsmToken::LParen)) {
6557 Operands.push_back(
6558 MipsOperand::CreateToken("(", getLexer().getLoc(), *this));
6559 Parser.Lex();
6560 if (parseOperand(Operands, Name)) {
6561 SMLoc Loc = getLexer().getLoc();
6562 return Error(Loc, "unexpected token in argument list");
6563 }
6564 if (Parser.getTok().isNot(AsmToken::RParen)) {
6565 SMLoc Loc = getLexer().getLoc();
6566 return Error(Loc, "unexpected token, expected ')'");
6567 }
6568 Operands.push_back(
6569 MipsOperand::CreateToken(")", getLexer().getLoc(), *this));
6570 Parser.Lex();
6571 }
6572 return false;
6573}
6574
6575/// Sometimes (i.e. in MSA) the operand may be followed immediately by
6576/// either one of these.
6577/// ::= '[', register, ']'
6578/// ::= '[', integer, ']'
6579/// handle it before we iterate so we don't get tripped up by the lack of
6580/// a comma.
6581bool MipsAsmParser::parseBracketSuffix(StringRef Name,
6582 OperandVector &Operands) {
6583 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
6584 if (getLexer().is(AsmToken::LBrac)) {
6585 Operands.push_back(
6586 MipsOperand::CreateToken("[", getLexer().getLoc(), *this));
6587 Parser.Lex();
6588 if (parseOperand(Operands, Name)) {
6589 SMLoc Loc = getLexer().getLoc();
6590 return Error(Loc, "unexpected token in argument list");
6591 }
6592 if (Parser.getTok().isNot(AsmToken::RBrac)) {
6593 SMLoc Loc = getLexer().getLoc();
6594 return Error(Loc, "unexpected token, expected ']'");
6595 }
6596 Operands.push_back(
6597 MipsOperand::CreateToken("]", getLexer().getLoc(), *this));
6598 Parser.Lex();
6599 }
6600 return false;
6601}
6602
6603static std::string MipsMnemonicSpellCheck(StringRef S, const FeatureBitset &FBS,
6604 unsigned VariantID = 0);
6605
6606bool MipsAsmParser::ParseInstruction(ParseInstructionInfo &Info, StringRef Name,
6607 SMLoc NameLoc, OperandVector &Operands) {
6608 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
6609 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "ParseInstruction\n");
6610
6611 // We have reached first instruction, module directive are now forbidden.
6612 getTargetStreamer().forbidModuleDirective();
6613
6614 // Check if we have valid mnemonic
6615 if (!mnemonicIsValid(Name, 0)) {
6616 FeatureBitset FBS = ComputeAvailableFeatures(getSTI().getFeatureBits());
6617 std::string Suggestion = MipsMnemonicSpellCheck(Name, FBS);
6618 return Error(NameLoc, "unknown instruction" + Suggestion);
6619 }
6620 // First operand in MCInst is instruction mnemonic.
6621 Operands.push_back(MipsOperand::CreateToken(Name, NameLoc, *this));
6622
6623 // Read the remaining operands.
6624 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
6625 // Read the first operand.
6626 if (parseOperand(Operands, Name)) {
6627 SMLoc Loc = getLexer().getLoc();
6628 return Error(Loc, "unexpected token in argument list");
6629 }
6630 if (getLexer().is(AsmToken::LBrac) && parseBracketSuffix(Name, Operands))
6631 return true;
6632 // AFAIK, parenthesis suffixes are never on the first operand
6633
6634 while (getLexer().is(AsmToken::Comma)) {
6635 Parser.Lex(); // Eat the comma.
6636 // Parse and remember the operand.
6637 if (parseOperand(Operands, Name)) {
6638 SMLoc Loc = getLexer().getLoc();
6639 return Error(Loc, "unexpected token in argument list");
6640 }
6641 // Parse bracket and parenthesis suffixes before we iterate
6642 if (getLexer().is(AsmToken::LBrac)) {
6643 if (parseBracketSuffix(Name, Operands))
6644 return true;
6645 } else if (getLexer().is(AsmToken::LParen) &&
6646 parseParenSuffix(Name, Operands))
6647 return true;
6648 }
6649 }
6650 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
6651 SMLoc Loc = getLexer().getLoc();
6652 return Error(Loc, "unexpected token in argument list");
6653 }
6654 Parser.Lex(); // Consume the EndOfStatement.
6655 return false;
6656}
6657
6658// FIXME: Given that these have the same name, these should both be
6659// consistent on affecting the Parser.
6660bool MipsAsmParser::reportParseError(Twine ErrorMsg) {
6661 SMLoc Loc = getLexer().getLoc();
6662 return Error(Loc, ErrorMsg);
6663}
6664
6665bool MipsAsmParser::reportParseError(SMLoc Loc, Twine ErrorMsg) {
6666 return Error(Loc, ErrorMsg);
6667}
6668
6669bool MipsAsmParser::parseSetNoAtDirective() {
6670 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
6671 // Line should look like: ".set noat".
6672
6673 // Set the $at register to $0.
6674 AssemblerOptions.back()->setATRegIndex(0);
6675
6676 Parser.Lex(); // Eat "noat".
6677
6678 // If this is not the end of the statement, report an error.
6679 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
6680 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
6681 return false;
6682 }
6683
6684 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveSetNoAt();
6685 Parser.Lex(); // Consume the EndOfStatement.
6686 return false;
6687}
6688
6689bool MipsAsmParser::parseSetAtDirective() {
6690 // Line can be: ".set at", which sets $at to $1
6691 // or ".set at=$reg", which sets $at to $reg.
6692 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
6693 Parser.Lex(); // Eat "at".
6694
6695 if (getLexer().is(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
6696 // No register was specified, so we set $at to $1.
6697 AssemblerOptions.back()->setATRegIndex(1);
6698
6699 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveSetAt();
6700 Parser.Lex(); // Consume the EndOfStatement.
6701 return false;
6702 }
6703
6704 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::Equal)) {
6705 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected equals sign");
6706 return false;
6707 }
6708 Parser.Lex(); // Eat "=".
6709
6710 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::Dollar)) {
6711 if (getLexer().is(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
6712 reportParseError("no register specified");
6713 return false;
6714 } else {
6715 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected dollar sign '$'");
6716 return false;
6717 }
6718 }
6719 Parser.Lex(); // Eat "$".
6720
6721 // Find out what "reg" is.
6722 unsigned AtRegNo;
6723 const AsmToken &Reg = Parser.getTok();
6724 if (Reg.is(AsmToken::Identifier)) {
6725 AtRegNo = matchCPURegisterName(Reg.getIdentifier());
6726 } else if (Reg.is(AsmToken::Integer)) {
6727 AtRegNo = Reg.getIntVal();
6728 } else {
6729 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected identifier or integer");
6730 return false;
6731 }
6732
6733 // Check if $reg is a valid register. If it is, set $at to $reg.
6734 if (!AssemblerOptions.back()->setATRegIndex(AtRegNo)) {
6735 reportParseError("invalid register");
6736 return false;
6737 }
6738 Parser.Lex(); // Eat "reg".
6739
6740 // If this is not the end of the statement, report an error.
6741 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
6742 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
6743 return false;
6744 }
6745
6746 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveSetAtWithArg(AtRegNo);
6747
6748 Parser.Lex(); // Consume the EndOfStatement.
6749 return false;
6750}

6884
6885bool MipsAsmParser::parseSetFpDirective() {
6886 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
6887 MipsABIFlagsSection::FpABIKind FpAbiVal;
6888 // Line can be: .set fp=32
6889 // .set fp=xx
6890 // .set fp=64
6891 Parser.Lex(); // Eat fp token
6892 AsmToken Tok = Parser.getTok();
6893 if (Tok.isNot(AsmToken::Equal)) {
6894 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected equals sign '='");
6895 return false;
6896 }
6897 Parser.Lex(); // Eat '=' token.
6898 Tok = Parser.getTok();
6899
6900 if (!parseFpABIValue(FpAbiVal, ".set"))
6901 return false;
6902
6903 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
6904 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
6905 return false;
6906 }
6907 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveSetFp(FpAbiVal);
6908 Parser.Lex(); // Consume the EndOfStatement.
6909 return false;
6910}

7023
7024bool MipsAsmParser::parseSetPopDirective() {
7025 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
7026 SMLoc Loc = getLexer().getLoc();
7027
7028 Parser.Lex();
7029 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement))
7030 return reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
7031
7032 // Always keep an element on the options "stack" to prevent the user
7033 // from changing the initial options. This is how we remember them.
7034 if (AssemblerOptions.size() == 2)
7035 return reportParseError(Loc, ".set pop with no .set push");
7036
7037 MCSubtargetInfo &STI = copySTI();
7038 AssemblerOptions.pop_back();
7039 setAvailableFeatures(
7040 ComputeAvailableFeatures(AssemblerOptions.back()->getFeatures()));
7041 STI.setFeatureBits(AssemblerOptions.back()->getFeatures());
7042
7043 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveSetPop();
7044 return false;
7045}
7046
7047bool MipsAsmParser::parseSetPushDirective() {
7048 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
7049 Parser.Lex();
7050 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement))
7051 return reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
7052
7053 // Create a copy of the current assembler options environment and push it.
7054 AssemblerOptions.push_back(
7055 llvm::make_unique<MipsAssemblerOptions>(AssemblerOptions.back().get()));
7056
7057 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveSetPush();
7058 return false;
7059}

7082
7083bool MipsAsmParser::parseSetAssignment() {
7084 StringRef Name;
7085 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
7086
7087 if (Parser.parseIdentifier(Name))
7088 return reportParseError("expected identifier after .set");
7089
7090 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::Comma))
7091 return reportParseError("unexpected token, expected comma");
7092 Lex(); // Eat comma
7093
7094 if (getLexer().is(AsmToken::Dollar) &&
7095 getLexer().peekTok().is(AsmToken::Integer)) {
7096 // Parse assignment of a numeric register:
7097 // .set r1,$1
7098 Parser.Lex(); // Eat $.
7099 RegisterSets[Name] = Parser.getTok();
7100 Parser.Lex(); // Eat identifier.
7101 getContext().getOrCreateSymbol(Name);
7102 return false;
7103 }
7104
7105 MCSymbol *Sym;
7106 const MCExpr *Value;
7107 if (MCParserUtils::parseAssignmentExpression(Name, /* allow_redef */ true,
7108 Parser, Sym, Value))
7109 return true;
7110 Sym->setVariableValue(Value);
7111
7112 return false;
7113}
7114
7115bool MipsAsmParser::parseSetMips0Directive() {
7116 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
7117 Parser.Lex();
7118 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement))
7119 return reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
7120
7121 // Reset assembler options to their initial values.
7122 MCSubtargetInfo &STI = copySTI();
7123 setAvailableFeatures(
7124 ComputeAvailableFeatures(AssemblerOptions.front()->getFeatures()));
7125 STI.setFeatureBits(AssemblerOptions.front()->getFeatures());
7126 AssemblerOptions.back()->setFeatures(AssemblerOptions.front()->getFeatures());
7127
7128 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveSetMips0();
7129 return false;
7130}
7131
7132bool MipsAsmParser::parseSetArchDirective() {
7133 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
7134 Parser.Lex();
7135 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::Equal))
7136 return reportParseError("unexpected token, expected equals sign");
7137
7138 Parser.Lex();
7139 StringRef Arch;
7140 if (Parser.parseIdentifier(Arch))
7141 return reportParseError("expected arch identifier");
7142
7143 StringRef ArchFeatureName =
7144 StringSwitch<StringRef>(Arch)
7145 .Case("mips1", "mips1")
7146 .Case("mips2", "mips2")
7147 .Case("mips3", "mips3")
7148 .Case("mips4", "mips4")
7149 .Case("mips5", "mips5")
7150 .Case("mips32", "mips32")
7151 .Case("mips32r2", "mips32r2")
7152 .Case("mips32r3", "mips32r3")
7153 .Case("mips32r5", "mips32r5")
7154 .Case("mips32r6", "mips32r6")
7155 .Case("mips64", "mips64")
7156 .Case("mips64r2", "mips64r2")
7157 .Case("mips64r3", "mips64r3")
7158 .Case("mips64r5", "mips64r5")
7159 .Case("mips64r6", "mips64r6")
7160 .Case("octeon", "cnmips")
7161 .Case("r4000", "mips3") // This is an implementation of Mips3.
7162 .Default("");
7163
7164 if (ArchFeatureName.empty())
7165 return reportParseError("unsupported architecture");
7166
7167 if (ArchFeatureName == "mips64r6" && inMicroMipsMode())
7168 return reportParseError("mips64r6 does not support microMIPS");
7169
7170 selectArch(ArchFeatureName);
7171 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveSetArch(Arch);
7172 return false;
7173}
7174
7175bool MipsAsmParser::parseSetFeature(uint64_t Feature) {
7176 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
7177 Parser.Lex();
7178 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement))
7179 return reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
7180
7181 switch (Feature) {
7182 default:
7183 llvm_unreachable("Unimplemented feature");
7184 case Mips::FeatureDSP:
7185 setFeatureBits(Mips::FeatureDSP, "dsp");
7186 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveSetDsp();
7187 break;
7188 case Mips::FeatureDSPR2:
7189 setFeatureBits(Mips::FeatureDSPR2, "dspr2");
7190 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveSetDspr2();
7191 break;
7192 case Mips::FeatureMicroMips:
7193 setFeatureBits(Mips::FeatureMicroMips, "micromips");
7194 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveSetMicroMips();
7195 break;
7196 case Mips::FeatureMips1:
7197 selectArch("mips1");
7198 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveSetMips1();
7199 break;
7200 case Mips::FeatureMips2:
7201 selectArch("mips2");
7202 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveSetMips2();
7203 break;
7204 case Mips::FeatureMips3:
7205 selectArch("mips3");
7206 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveSetMips3();
7207 break;
7208 case Mips::FeatureMips4:
7209 selectArch("mips4");
7210 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveSetMips4();
7211 break;
7212 case Mips::FeatureMips5:
7213 selectArch("mips5");
7214 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveSetMips5();
7215 break;
7216 case Mips::FeatureMips32:
7217 selectArch("mips32");
7218 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveSetMips32();
7219 break;
7220 case Mips::FeatureMips32r2:
7221 selectArch("mips32r2");
7222 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveSetMips32R2();
7223 break;
7224 case Mips::FeatureMips32r3:
7225 selectArch("mips32r3");
7226 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveSetMips32R3();
7227 break;
7228 case Mips::FeatureMips32r5:
7229 selectArch("mips32r5");
7230 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveSetMips32R5();
7231 break;
7232 case Mips::FeatureMips32r6:
7233 selectArch("mips32r6");
7234 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveSetMips32R6();
7235 break;
7236 case Mips::FeatureMips64:
7237 selectArch("mips64");
7238 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveSetMips64();
7239 break;
7240 case Mips::FeatureMips64r2:
7241 selectArch("mips64r2");
7242 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveSetMips64R2();
7243 break;
7244 case Mips::FeatureMips64r3:
7245 selectArch("mips64r3");
7246 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveSetMips64R3();
7247 break;
7248 case Mips::FeatureMips64r5:
7249 selectArch("mips64r5");
7250 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveSetMips64R5();
7251 break;
7252 case Mips::FeatureMips64r6:
7253 selectArch("mips64r6");
7254 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveSetMips64R6();
7255 break;
7256 case Mips::FeatureCRC:
7257 setFeatureBits(Mips::FeatureCRC, "crc");
7258 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveSetCRC();
7259 break;
7260 case Mips::FeatureVirt:
7261 setFeatureBits(Mips::FeatureVirt, "virt");
7262 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveSetVirt();
7263 break;
7264 case Mips::FeatureGINV:
7265 setFeatureBits(Mips::FeatureGINV, "ginv");
7266 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveSetGINV();
7267 break;
7268 }
7269 return false;
7270}
7271
7272bool MipsAsmParser::eatComma(StringRef ErrorStr) {
7273 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
7274 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::Comma)) {
7275 SMLoc Loc = getLexer().getLoc();
7276 return Error(Loc, ErrorStr);
7277 }
7278
7279 Parser.Lex(); // Eat the comma.
7280 return true;
7281}
7282
7283// Used to determine if .cpload, .cprestore, and .cpsetup have any effect.
7284// In this class, it is only used for .cprestore.
7285// FIXME: Only keep track of IsPicEnabled in one place, instead of in both
7286// MipsTargetELFStreamer and MipsAsmParser.
7287bool MipsAsmParser::isPicAndNotNxxAbi() {
7288 return inPicMode() && !(isABI_N32() || isABI_N64());
7289}
7290
7291bool MipsAsmParser::parseDirectiveCpLoad(SMLoc Loc) {
7292 if (AssemblerOptions.back()->isReorder())
7293 Warning(Loc, ".cpload should be inside a noreorder section");
7294
7295 if (inMips16Mode()) {
7296 reportParseError(".cpload is not supported in Mips16 mode");
7297 return false;
7298 }
7299
7300 SmallVector<std::unique_ptr<MCParsedAsmOperand>, 1> Reg;
7301 OperandMatchResultTy ResTy = parseAnyRegister(Reg);
7302 if (ResTy == MatchOperand_NoMatch || ResTy == MatchOperand_ParseFail) {
7303 reportParseError("expected register containing function address");
7304 return false;
7305 }
7306
7307 MipsOperand &RegOpnd = static_cast<MipsOperand &>(*Reg[0]);
7308 if (!RegOpnd.isGPRAsmReg()) {
7309 reportParseError(RegOpnd.getStartLoc(), "invalid register");
7310 return false;
7311 }
7312
7313 // If this is not the end of the statement, report an error.
7314 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
7315 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
7316 return false;
7317 }
7318
7319 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveCpLoad(RegOpnd.getGPR32Reg());
7320 return false;
7321}
7322
7323bool MipsAsmParser::parseDirectiveCpLocal(SMLoc Loc) {
7324 if (!isABI_N32() && !isABI_N64()) {
7325 reportParseError(".cplocal is allowed only in N32 or N64 mode");
7326 return false;
7327 }
7328
7329 SmallVector<std::unique_ptr<MCParsedAsmOperand>, 1> Reg;
7330 OperandMatchResultTy ResTy = parseAnyRegister(Reg);
7331 if (ResTy == MatchOperand_NoMatch || ResTy == MatchOperand_ParseFail) {
7332 reportParseError("expected register containing global pointer");
7333 return false;
7334 }
7335
7336 MipsOperand &RegOpnd = static_cast<MipsOperand &>(*Reg[0]);
7337 if (!RegOpnd.isGPRAsmReg()) {
7338 reportParseError(RegOpnd.getStartLoc(), "invalid register");
7339 return false;
7340 }
7341
7342 // If this is not the end of the statement, report an error.
7343 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
7344 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
7345 return false;
7346 }
7347 getParser().Lex(); // Consume the EndOfStatement.
7348
7349 unsigned NewReg = RegOpnd.getGPR32Reg();
7350 if (IsPicEnabled)
7351 GPReg = NewReg;
7352
7353 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveCpLocal(NewReg);
7354 return false;
7355}
7356
7357bool MipsAsmParser::parseDirectiveCpRestore(SMLoc Loc) {
7358 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
7359
7360 // Note that .cprestore is ignored if used with the N32 and N64 ABIs or if it
7361 // is used in non-PIC mode.
7362
7363 if (inMips16Mode()) {
7364 reportParseError(".cprestore is not supported in Mips16 mode");
7365 return false;
7366 }
7367
7368 // Get the stack offset value.
7369 const MCExpr *StackOffset;
7370 int64_t StackOffsetVal;
7371 if (Parser.parseExpression(StackOffset)) {
7372 reportParseError("expected stack offset value");
7373 return false;
7374 }
7375
7376 if (!StackOffset->evaluateAsAbsolute(StackOffsetVal)) {
7377 reportParseError("stack offset is not an absolute expression");
7378 return false;
7379 }
7380
7381 if (StackOffsetVal < 0) {
7382 Warning(Loc, ".cprestore with negative stack offset has no effect");
7383 IsCpRestoreSet = false;
7384 } else {
7385 IsCpRestoreSet = true;
7386 CpRestoreOffset = StackOffsetVal;
7387 }
7388
7389 // If this is not the end of the statement, report an error.
7390 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
7391 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
7392 return false;
7393 }
7394
7395 if (!getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveCpRestore(
7396 CpRestoreOffset, [&]() { return getATReg(Loc); }, Loc, STI))
7397 return true;
7398 Parser.Lex(); // Consume the EndOfStatement.
7399 return false;
7400}
7401
7402bool MipsAsmParser::parseDirectiveCPSetup() {
7403 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
7404 unsigned FuncReg;
7405 unsigned Save;
7406 bool SaveIsReg = true;
7407
7408 SmallVector<std::unique_ptr<MCParsedAsmOperand>, 1> TmpReg;
7409 OperandMatchResultTy ResTy = parseAnyRegister(TmpReg);
7410 if (ResTy == MatchOperand_NoMatch) {
7411 reportParseError("expected register containing function address");
7412 return false;
7413 }
7414
7415 MipsOperand &FuncRegOpnd = static_cast<MipsOperand &>(*TmpReg[0]);
7416 if (!FuncRegOpnd.isGPRAsmReg()) {
7417 reportParseError(FuncRegOpnd.getStartLoc(), "invalid register");
7418 return false;
7419 }
7420
7421 FuncReg = FuncRegOpnd.getGPR32Reg();
7422 TmpReg.clear();
7423
7424 if (!eatComma("unexpected token, expected comma"))
7425 return true;
7426
7427 ResTy = parseAnyRegister(TmpReg);
7428 if (ResTy == MatchOperand_NoMatch) {
7429 const MCExpr *OffsetExpr;
7430 int64_t OffsetVal;
7431 SMLoc ExprLoc = getLexer().getLoc();
7432
7433 if (Parser.parseExpression(OffsetExpr) ||
7434 !OffsetExpr->evaluateAsAbsolute(OffsetVal)) {
7435 reportParseError(ExprLoc, "expected save register or stack offset");
7436 return false;
7437 }
7438
7439 Save = OffsetVal;
7440 SaveIsReg = false;
7441 } else {
7442 MipsOperand &SaveOpnd = static_cast<MipsOperand &>(*TmpReg[0]);
7443 if (!SaveOpnd.isGPRAsmReg()) {
7444 reportParseError(SaveOpnd.getStartLoc(), "invalid register");
7445 return false;
7446 }
7447 Save = SaveOpnd.getGPR32Reg();
7448 }
7449
7450 if (!eatComma("unexpected token, expected comma"))
7451 return true;
7452
7453 const MCExpr *Expr;
7454 if (Parser.parseExpression(Expr)) {
7455 reportParseError("expected expression");
7456 return false;
7457 }
7458
7459 if (Expr->getKind() != MCExpr::SymbolRef) {
7460 reportParseError("expected symbol");
7461 return false;
7462 }
7463 const MCSymbolRefExpr *Ref = static_cast<const MCSymbolRefExpr *>(Expr);
7464
7465 CpSaveLocation = Save;
7466 CpSaveLocationIsRegister = SaveIsReg;
7467
7468 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveCpsetup(FuncReg, Save, Ref->getSymbol(),
7469 SaveIsReg);
7470 return false;
7471}
7472
7473bool MipsAsmParser::parseDirectiveCPReturn() {
7474 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveCpreturn(CpSaveLocation,
7475 CpSaveLocationIsRegister);
7476 return false;
7477}
7478
7479bool MipsAsmParser::parseDirectiveNaN() {
7480 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
7481 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
7482 const AsmToken &Tok = Parser.getTok();
7483
7484 if (Tok.getString() == "2008") {
7485 Parser.Lex();
7486 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveNaN2008();
7487 return false;
7488 } else if (Tok.getString() == "legacy") {
7489 Parser.Lex();
7490 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveNaNLegacy();
7491 return false;
7492 }
7493 }
7494 // If we don't recognize the option passed to the .nan
7495 // directive (e.g. no option or unknown option), emit an error.
7496 reportParseError("invalid option in .nan directive");
7497 return false;
7498}
7499
7500bool MipsAsmParser::parseDirectiveSet() {
7501 const AsmToken &Tok = getParser().getTok();
7502 StringRef IdVal = Tok.getString();
7503 SMLoc Loc = Tok.getLoc();
7504
7505 if (IdVal == "noat")
7506 return parseSetNoAtDirective();
7507 if (IdVal == "at")
7508 return parseSetAtDirective();
7509 if (IdVal == "arch")
7510 return parseSetArchDirective();
7511 if (IdVal == "bopt") {
7512 Warning(Loc, "'bopt' feature is unsupported");
7513 getParser().Lex();
7514 return false;
7515 }
7516 if (IdVal == "nobopt") {
7517 // We're already running in nobopt mode, so nothing to do.
7518 getParser().Lex();
7519 return false;
7520 }
7521 if (IdVal == "fp")
7522 return parseSetFpDirective();
7523 if (IdVal == "oddspreg")
7524 return parseSetOddSPRegDirective();
7525 if (IdVal == "nooddspreg")
7526 return parseSetNoOddSPRegDirective();
7527 if (IdVal == "pop")
7528 return parseSetPopDirective();
7529 if (IdVal == "push")
7530 return parseSetPushDirective();
7531 if (IdVal == "reorder")
7532 return parseSetReorderDirective();
7533 if (IdVal == "noreorder")
7534 return parseSetNoReorderDirective();
7535 if (IdVal == "macro")
7536 return parseSetMacroDirective();
7537 if (IdVal == "nomacro")
7538 return parseSetNoMacroDirective();
7539 if (IdVal == "mips16")
7540 return parseSetMips16Directive();
7541 if (IdVal == "nomips16")
7542 return parseSetNoMips16Directive();
7543 if (IdVal == "nomicromips") {
7544 clearFeatureBits(Mips::FeatureMicroMips, "micromips");
7545 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveSetNoMicroMips();
7546 getParser().eatToEndOfStatement();
7547 return false;
7548 }
7549 if (IdVal == "micromips") {
7550 if (hasMips64r6()) {
7551 Error(Loc, ".set micromips directive is not supported with MIPS64R6");
7552 return false;
7553 }
7554 return parseSetFeature(Mips::FeatureMicroMips);
7555 }
7556 if (IdVal == "mips0")
7557 return parseSetMips0Directive();
7558 if (IdVal == "mips1")
7559 return parseSetFeature(Mips::FeatureMips1);
7560 if (IdVal == "mips2")
7561 return parseSetFeature(Mips::FeatureMips2);
7562 if (IdVal == "mips3")
7563 return parseSetFeature(Mips::FeatureMips3);
7564 if (IdVal == "mips4")
7565 return parseSetFeature(Mips::FeatureMips4);
7566 if (IdVal == "mips5")
7567 return parseSetFeature(Mips::FeatureMips5);
7568 if (IdVal == "mips32")
7569 return parseSetFeature(Mips::FeatureMips32);
7570 if (IdVal == "mips32r2")
7571 return parseSetFeature(Mips::FeatureMips32r2);
7572 if (IdVal == "mips32r3")
7573 return parseSetFeature(Mips::FeatureMips32r3);
7574 if (IdVal == "mips32r5")
7575 return parseSetFeature(Mips::FeatureMips32r5);
7576 if (IdVal == "mips32r6")
7577 return parseSetFeature(Mips::FeatureMips32r6);
7578 if (IdVal == "mips64")
7579 return parseSetFeature(Mips::FeatureMips64);
7580 if (IdVal == "mips64r2")
7581 return parseSetFeature(Mips::FeatureMips64r2);
7582 if (IdVal == "mips64r3")
7583 return parseSetFeature(Mips::FeatureMips64r3);
7584 if (IdVal == "mips64r5")
7585 return parseSetFeature(Mips::FeatureMips64r5);
7586 if (IdVal == "mips64r6") {
7587 if (inMicroMipsMode()) {
7588 Error(Loc, "MIPS64R6 is not supported with microMIPS");
7589 return false;
7590 }
7591 return parseSetFeature(Mips::FeatureMips64r6);
7592 }
7593 if (IdVal == "dsp")
7594 return parseSetFeature(Mips::FeatureDSP);
7595 if (IdVal == "dspr2")
7596 return parseSetFeature(Mips::FeatureDSPR2);
7597 if (IdVal == "nodsp")
7598 return parseSetNoDspDirective();
7599 if (IdVal == "msa")
7600 return parseSetMsaDirective();
7601 if (IdVal == "nomsa")
7602 return parseSetNoMsaDirective();
7603 if (IdVal == "mt")
7604 return parseSetMtDirective();
7605 if (IdVal == "nomt")
7606 return parseSetNoMtDirective();
7607 if (IdVal == "softfloat")
7608 return parseSetSoftFloatDirective();
7609 if (IdVal == "hardfloat")
7610 return parseSetHardFloatDirective();
7611 if (IdVal == "crc")
7612 return parseSetFeature(Mips::FeatureCRC);
7613 if (IdVal == "nocrc")
7614 return parseSetNoCRCDirective();
7615 if (IdVal == "virt")
7616 return parseSetFeature(Mips::FeatureVirt);
7617 if (IdVal == "novirt")
7618 return parseSetNoVirtDirective();
7619 if (IdVal == "ginv")
7620 return parseSetFeature(Mips::FeatureGINV);
7621 if (IdVal == "noginv")
7622 return parseSetNoGINVDirective();
7623
7624 // It is just an identifier, look for an assignment.
7625 return parseSetAssignment();
7626}
7627
7628/// parseDirectiveGpWord
7629/// ::= .gpword local_sym
7630bool MipsAsmParser::parseDirectiveGpWord() {
7631 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
7632 const MCExpr *Value;
7633 // EmitGPRel32Value requires an expression, so we are using base class
7634 // method to evaluate the expression.
7635 if (getParser().parseExpression(Value))
7636 return true;
7637 getParser().getStreamer().EmitGPRel32Value(Value);
7638
7639 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement))
7640 return Error(getLexer().getLoc(),
7641 "unexpected token, expected end of statement");
7642 Parser.Lex(); // Eat EndOfStatement token.
7643 return false;
7644}

7735
7736bool MipsAsmParser::parseDirectiveOption() {
7737 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
7738 // Get the option token.
7739 AsmToken Tok = Parser.getTok();
7740 // At the moment only identifiers are supported.
7741 if (Tok.isNot(AsmToken::Identifier)) {
7742 return Error(Parser.getTok().getLoc(),
7743 "unexpected token, expected identifier");
7744 }
7745
7746 StringRef Option = Tok.getIdentifier();
7747
7748 if (Option == "pic0") {
7749 // MipsAsmParser needs to know if the current PIC mode changes.
7750 IsPicEnabled = false;
7751
7752 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveOptionPic0();
7753 Parser.Lex();
7754 if (Parser.getTok().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
7755 return Error(Parser.getTok().getLoc(),
7756 "unexpected token, expected end of statement");
7757 }
7758 return false;
7759 }
7760
7761 if (Option == "pic2") {
7762 // MipsAsmParser needs to know if the current PIC mode changes.
7763 IsPicEnabled = true;
7764
7765 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveOptionPic2();
7766 Parser.Lex();
7767 if (Parser.getTok().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
7768 return Error(Parser.getTok().getLoc(),
7769 "unexpected token, expected end of statement");
7770 }
7771 return false;
7772 }
7773
7774 // Unknown option.
7775 Warning(Parser.getTok().getLoc(),
7776 "unknown option, expected 'pic0' or 'pic2'");
7777 Parser.eatToEndOfStatement();
7778 return false;
7779}
7780
7781/// parseInsnDirective
7782/// ::= .insn
7783bool MipsAsmParser::parseInsnDirective() {
7784 // If this is not the end of the statement, report an error.
7785 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
7786 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
7787 return false;
7788 }
7789
7790 // The actual label marking happens in
7791 // MipsELFStreamer::createPendingLabelRelocs().
7792 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveInsn();
7793
7794 getParser().Lex(); // Eat EndOfStatement token.
7795 return false;
7796}
7797
7798/// parseRSectionDirective
7799/// ::= .rdata
7800bool MipsAsmParser::parseRSectionDirective(StringRef Section) {
7801 // If this is not the end of the statement, report an error.
7802 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
7803 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
7804 return false;
7805 }
7806
7807 MCSection *ELFSection = getContext().getELFSection(
7808 Section, ELF::SHT_PROGBITS, ELF::SHF_ALLOC);
7809 getParser().getStreamer().SwitchSection(ELFSection);
7810
7811 getParser().Lex(); // Eat EndOfStatement token.
7812 return false;
7813}
7814
7815/// parseSSectionDirective
7816/// ::= .sbss
7817/// ::= .sdata
7818bool MipsAsmParser::parseSSectionDirective(StringRef Section, unsigned Type) {
7819 // If this is not the end of the statement, report an error.
7820 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
7821 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
7822 return false;
7823 }
7824
7825 MCSection *ELFSection = getContext().getELFSection(
7826 Section, Type, ELF::SHF_WRITE | ELF::SHF_ALLOC | ELF::SHF_MIPS_GPREL);
7827 getParser().getStreamer().SwitchSection(ELFSection);
7828
7829 getParser().Lex(); // Eat EndOfStatement token.
7830 return false;
7831}
