7833/// parseDirectiveModule
7834/// ::= .module oddspreg
7835/// ::= .module nooddspreg
7836/// ::= .module fp=value
7837/// ::= .module softfloat
7838/// ::= .module hardfloat
7839/// ::= .module mt
7840/// ::= .module crc
7841/// ::= .module nocrc
7842/// ::= .module virt
7843/// ::= .module novirt
7844/// ::= .module ginv
7845/// ::= .module noginv
7846bool MipsAsmParser::parseDirectiveModule() {
7847 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
7848 MCAsmLexer &Lexer = getLexer();
7849 SMLoc L = Lexer.getLoc();
7850
7851 if (!getTargetStreamer().isModuleDirectiveAllowed()) {
7852 // TODO : get a better message.
7853 reportParseError(".module directive must appear before any code");
7854 return false;
7855 }
7856
7857 StringRef Option;
7858 if (Parser.parseIdentifier(Option)) {
7859 reportParseError("expected .module option identifier");
7860 return false;
7861 }
7862
7863 if (Option == "oddspreg") {
7864 clearModuleFeatureBits(Mips::FeatureNoOddSPReg, "nooddspreg");
7865
7866 // Synchronize the abiflags information with the FeatureBits information we
7867 // changed above.
7868 getTargetStreamer().updateABIInfo(*this);
7869
7870 // If printing assembly, use the recently updated abiflags information.
7871 // If generating ELF, don't do anything (the .MIPS.abiflags section gets
7872 // emitted at the end).
7873 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveModuleOddSPReg();
7874
7875 // If this is not the end of the statement, report an error.
7876 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
7877 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
7878 return false;
7879 }
7880
7881 return false; // parseDirectiveModule has finished successfully.
7882 } else if (Option == "nooddspreg") {
7883 if (!isABI_O32()) {
7884 return Error(L, "'.module nooddspreg' requires the O32 ABI");
7885 }
7886
7887 setModuleFeatureBits(Mips::FeatureNoOddSPReg, "nooddspreg");
7888
7889 // Synchronize the abiflags information with the FeatureBits information we
7890 // changed above.
7891 getTargetStreamer().updateABIInfo(*this);
7892
7893 // If printing assembly, use the recently updated abiflags information.
7894 // If generating ELF, don't do anything (the .MIPS.abiflags section gets
7895 // emitted at the end).
7896 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveModuleOddSPReg();
7897
7898 // If this is not the end of the statement, report an error.
7899 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
7900 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
7901 return false;
7902 }
7903
7904 return false; // parseDirectiveModule has finished successfully.
7905 } else if (Option == "fp") {
7906 return parseDirectiveModuleFP();
7907 } else if (Option == "softfloat") {
7908 setModuleFeatureBits(Mips::FeatureSoftFloat, "soft-float");
7909
7910 // Synchronize the ABI Flags information with the FeatureBits information we
7911 // updated above.
7912 getTargetStreamer().updateABIInfo(*this);
7913
7914 // If printing assembly, use the recently updated ABI Flags information.
7915 // If generating ELF, don't do anything (the .MIPS.abiflags section gets
7916 // emitted later).
7917 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveModuleSoftFloat();
7918
7919 // If this is not the end of the statement, report an error.
7920 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
7921 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
7922 return false;
7923 }
7924
7925 return false; // parseDirectiveModule has finished successfully.
7926 } else if (Option == "hardfloat") {
7927 clearModuleFeatureBits(Mips::FeatureSoftFloat, "soft-float");
7928
7929 // Synchronize the ABI Flags information with the FeatureBits information we
7930 // updated above.
7931 getTargetStreamer().updateABIInfo(*this);
7932
7933 // If printing assembly, use the recently updated ABI Flags information.
7934 // If generating ELF, don't do anything (the .MIPS.abiflags section gets
7935 // emitted later).
7936 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveModuleHardFloat();
7937
7938 // If this is not the end of the statement, report an error.
7939 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
7940 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
7941 return false;
7942 }
7943
7944 return false; // parseDirectiveModule has finished successfully.
7945 } else if (Option == "mt") {
7946 setModuleFeatureBits(Mips::FeatureMT, "mt");
7947
7948 // Synchronize the ABI Flags information with the FeatureBits information we
7949 // updated above.
7950 getTargetStreamer().updateABIInfo(*this);
7951
7952 // If printing assembly, use the recently updated ABI Flags information.
7953 // If generating ELF, don't do anything (the .MIPS.abiflags section gets
7954 // emitted later).
7955 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveModuleMT();
7956
7957 // If this is not the end of the statement, report an error.
7958 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
7959 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
7960 return false;
7961 }
7962
7963 return false; // parseDirectiveModule has finished successfully.
7964 } else if (Option == "crc") {
7965 setModuleFeatureBits(Mips::FeatureCRC, "crc");
7966
7967 // Synchronize the ABI Flags information with the FeatureBits information we
7968 // updated above.
7969 getTargetStreamer().updateABIInfo(*this);
7970
7971 // If printing assembly, use the recently updated ABI Flags information.
7972 // If generating ELF, don't do anything (the .MIPS.abiflags section gets
7973 // emitted later).
7974 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveModuleCRC();
7975
7976 // If this is not the end of the statement, report an error.
7977 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
7978 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
7979 return false;
7980 }
7981
7982 return false; // parseDirectiveModule has finished successfully.
7983 } else if (Option == "nocrc") {
7984 clearModuleFeatureBits(Mips::FeatureCRC, "crc");
7985
7986 // Synchronize the ABI Flags information with the FeatureBits information we
7987 // updated above.
7988 getTargetStreamer().updateABIInfo(*this);
7989
7990 // If printing assembly, use the recently updated ABI Flags information.
7991 // If generating ELF, don't do anything (the .MIPS.abiflags section gets
7992 // emitted later).
7993 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveModuleNoCRC();
7994
7995 // If this is not the end of the statement, report an error.
7996 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
7997 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
7998 return false;
7999 }
8000
8001 return false; // parseDirectiveModule has finished successfully.
8002 } else if (Option == "virt") {
8003 setModuleFeatureBits(Mips::FeatureVirt, "virt");
8004
8005 // Synchronize the ABI Flags information with the FeatureBits information we
8006 // updated above.
8007 getTargetStreamer().updateABIInfo(*this);
8008
8009 // If printing assembly, use the recently updated ABI Flags information.
8010 // If generating ELF, don't do anything (the .MIPS.abiflags section gets
8011 // emitted later).
8012 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveModuleVirt();
8013
8014 // If this is not the end of the statement, report an error.
8015 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
8016 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
8017 return false;
8018 }
8019
8020 return false; // parseDirectiveModule has finished successfully.
8021 } else if (Option == "novirt") {
8022 clearModuleFeatureBits(Mips::FeatureVirt, "virt");
8023
8024 // Synchronize the ABI Flags information with the FeatureBits information we
8025 // updated above.
8026 getTargetStreamer().updateABIInfo(*this);
8027
8028 // If printing assembly, use the recently updated ABI Flags information.
8029 // If generating ELF, don't do anything (the .MIPS.abiflags section gets
8030 // emitted later).
8031 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveModuleNoVirt();
8032
8033 // If this is not the end of the statement, report an error.
8034 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
8035 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
8036 return false;
8037 }
8038
8039 return false; // parseDirectiveModule has finished successfully.
8040 } else if (Option == "ginv") {
8041 setModuleFeatureBits(Mips::FeatureGINV, "ginv");
8042
8043 // Synchronize the ABI Flags information with the FeatureBits information we
8044 // updated above.
8045 getTargetStreamer().updateABIInfo(*this);
8046
8047 // If printing assembly, use the recently updated ABI Flags information.
8048 // If generating ELF, don't do anything (the .MIPS.abiflags section gets
8049 // emitted later).
8050 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveModuleGINV();
8051
8052 // If this is not the end of the statement, report an error.
8053 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
8054 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
8055 return false;
8056 }
8057
8058 return false; // parseDirectiveModule has finished successfully.
8059 } else if (Option == "noginv") {
8060 clearModuleFeatureBits(Mips::FeatureGINV, "ginv");
8061
8062 // Synchronize the ABI Flags information with the FeatureBits information we
8063 // updated above.
8064 getTargetStreamer().updateABIInfo(*this);
8065
8066 // If printing assembly, use the recently updated ABI Flags information.
8067 // If generating ELF, don't do anything (the .MIPS.abiflags section gets
8068 // emitted later).
8069 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveModuleNoGINV();
8070
8071 // If this is not the end of the statement, report an error.
8072 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
8073 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
8074 return false;
8075 }
8076
8077 return false; // parseDirectiveModule has finished successfully.
8078 } else {
8079 return Error(L, "'" + Twine(Option) + "' is not a valid .module option.");
8080 }
8081}
8082
8083/// parseDirectiveModuleFP
8084/// ::= =32
8085/// ::= =xx
8086/// ::= =64
8087bool MipsAsmParser::parseDirectiveModuleFP() {
8088 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
8089 MCAsmLexer &Lexer = getLexer();
8090
8091 if (Lexer.isNot(AsmToken::Equal)) {
8092 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected equals sign '='");
8093 return false;
8094 }
8095 Parser.Lex(); // Eat '=' token.
8096
8097 MipsABIFlagsSection::FpABIKind FpABI;
8098 if (!parseFpABIValue(FpABI, ".module"))
8099 return false;
8100
8101 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
8102 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
8103 return false;
8104 }
8105
8106 // Synchronize the abiflags information with the FeatureBits information we
8107 // changed above.
8108 getTargetStreamer().updateABIInfo(*this);
8109
8110 // If printing assembly, use the recently updated abiflags information.
8111 // If generating ELF, don't do anything (the .MIPS.abiflags section gets
8112 // emitted at the end).
8113 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveModuleFP();
8114
8115 Parser.Lex(); // Consume the EndOfStatement.
8116 return false;
8117}
8118
8119bool MipsAsmParser::parseFpABIValue(MipsABIFlagsSection::FpABIKind &FpABI,
8120 StringRef Directive) {
8121 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
8122 MCAsmLexer &Lexer = getLexer();
8123 bool ModuleLevelOptions = Directive == ".module";
8124
8125 if (Lexer.is(AsmToken::Identifier)) {
8126 StringRef Value = Parser.getTok().getString();
8127 Parser.Lex();
8128
8129 if (Value != "xx") {
8130 reportParseError("unsupported value, expected 'xx', '32' or '64'");
8131 return false;
8132 }
8133
8134 if (!isABI_O32()) {
8135 reportParseError("'" + Directive + " fp=xx' requires the O32 ABI");
8136 return false;
8137 }
8138
8139 FpABI = MipsABIFlagsSection::FpABIKind::XX;
8140 if (ModuleLevelOptions) {
8141 setModuleFeatureBits(Mips::FeatureFPXX, "fpxx");
8142 clearModuleFeatureBits(Mips::FeatureFP64Bit, "fp64");
8143 } else {
8144 setFeatureBits(Mips::FeatureFPXX, "fpxx");
8145 clearFeatureBits(Mips::FeatureFP64Bit, "fp64");
8146 }
8147 return true;
8148 }
8149
8150 if (Lexer.is(AsmToken::Integer)) {
8151 unsigned Value = Parser.getTok().getIntVal();
8152 Parser.Lex();
8153
8154 if (Value != 32 && Value != 64) {
8155 reportParseError("unsupported value, expected 'xx', '32' or '64'");
8156 return false;
8157 }
8158
8159 if (Value == 32) {
8160 if (!isABI_O32()) {
8161 reportParseError("'" + Directive + " fp=32' requires the O32 ABI");
8162 return false;
8163 }
8164
8165 FpABI = MipsABIFlagsSection::FpABIKind::S32;
8166 if (ModuleLevelOptions) {
8167 clearModuleFeatureBits(Mips::FeatureFPXX, "fpxx");
8168 clearModuleFeatureBits(Mips::FeatureFP64Bit, "fp64");
8169 } else {
8170 clearFeatureBits(Mips::FeatureFPXX, "fpxx");
8171 clearFeatureBits(Mips::FeatureFP64Bit, "fp64");
8172 }
8173 } else {
8174 FpABI = MipsABIFlagsSection::FpABIKind::S64;
8175 if (ModuleLevelOptions) {
8176 clearModuleFeatureBits(Mips::FeatureFPXX, "fpxx");
8177 setModuleFeatureBits(Mips::FeatureFP64Bit, "fp64");
8178 } else {
8179 clearFeatureBits(Mips::FeatureFPXX, "fpxx");
8180 setFeatureBits(Mips::FeatureFP64Bit, "fp64");
8181 }
8182 }
8183
8184 return true;
8185 }
8186
8187 return false;
8188}
8189
8190bool MipsAsmParser::ParseDirective(AsmToken DirectiveID) {
8191 // This returns false if this function recognizes the directive
8192 // regardless of whether it is successfully handles or reports an
8193 // error. Otherwise it returns true to give the generic parser a
8194 // chance at recognizing it.
8195
8196 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
8197 StringRef IDVal = DirectiveID.getString();
8198
8199 if (IDVal == ".cpload") {
8200 parseDirectiveCpLoad(DirectiveID.getLoc());
8201 return false;
8202 }
8203 if (IDVal == ".cprestore") {
8204 parseDirectiveCpRestore(DirectiveID.getLoc());
8205 return false;
8206 }
8207 if (IDVal == ".cplocal") {
8208 parseDirectiveCpLocal(DirectiveID.getLoc());
8209 return false;
8210 }
8211 if (IDVal == ".ent") {
8212 StringRef SymbolName;
8213
8214 if (Parser.parseIdentifier(SymbolName)) {
8215 reportParseError("expected identifier after .ent");
8216 return false;
8217 }
8218
8219 // There's an undocumented extension that allows an integer to
8220 // follow the name of the procedure which AFAICS is ignored by GAS.
8221 // Example: .ent foo,2
8222 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
8223 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::Comma)) {
8224 // Even though we accept this undocumented extension for compatibility
8225 // reasons, the additional integer argument does not actually change
8226 // the behaviour of the '.ent' directive, so we would like to discourage
8227 // its use. We do this by not referring to the extended version in
8228 // error messages which are not directly related to its use.
8229 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
8230 return false;
8231 }
8232 Parser.Lex(); // Eat the comma.
8233 const MCExpr *DummyNumber;
8234 int64_t DummyNumberVal;
8235 // If the user was explicitly trying to use the extended version,
8236 // we still give helpful extension-related error messages.
8237 if (Parser.parseExpression(DummyNumber)) {
8238 reportParseError("expected number after comma");
8239 return false;
8240 }
8241 if (!DummyNumber->evaluateAsAbsolute(DummyNumberVal)) {
8242 reportParseError("expected an absolute expression after comma");
8243 return false;
8244 }
8245 }
8246
8247 // If this is not the end of the statement, report an error.
8248 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
8249 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
8250 return false;
8251 }
8252
8253 MCSymbol *Sym = getContext().getOrCreateSymbol(SymbolName);
8254
8255 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveEnt(*Sym);
8256 CurrentFn = Sym;
8257 IsCpRestoreSet = false;
8258 return false;
8259 }
8260
8261 if (IDVal == ".end") {
8262 StringRef SymbolName;
8263
8264 if (Parser.parseIdentifier(SymbolName)) {
8265 reportParseError("expected identifier after .end");
8266 return false;
8267 }
8268
8269 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
8270 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
8271 return false;
8272 }
8273
8274 if (CurrentFn == nullptr) {
8275 reportParseError(".end used without .ent");
8276 return false;
8277 }
8278
8279 if ((SymbolName != CurrentFn->getName())) {
8280 reportParseError(".end symbol does not match .ent symbol");
8281 return false;
8282 }
8283
8284 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveEnd(SymbolName);
8285 CurrentFn = nullptr;
8286 IsCpRestoreSet = false;
8287 return false;
8288 }
8289
8290 if (IDVal == ".frame") {
8291 // .frame $stack_reg, frame_size_in_bytes, $return_reg
8292 SmallVector<std::unique_ptr<MCParsedAsmOperand>, 1> TmpReg;
8293 OperandMatchResultTy ResTy = parseAnyRegister(TmpReg);
8294 if (ResTy == MatchOperand_NoMatch || ResTy == MatchOperand_ParseFail) {
8295 reportParseError("expected stack register");
8296 return false;
8297 }
8298
8299 MipsOperand &StackRegOpnd = static_cast<MipsOperand &>(*TmpReg[0]);
8300 if (!StackRegOpnd.isGPRAsmReg()) {
8301 reportParseError(StackRegOpnd.getStartLoc(),
8302 "expected general purpose register");
8303 return false;
8304 }
8305 unsigned StackReg = StackRegOpnd.getGPR32Reg();
8306
8307 if (Parser.getTok().is(AsmToken::Comma))
8308 Parser.Lex();
8309 else {
8310 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected comma");
8311 return false;
8312 }
8313
8314 // Parse the frame size.
8315 const MCExpr *FrameSize;
8316 int64_t FrameSizeVal;
8317
8318 if (Parser.parseExpression(FrameSize)) {
8319 reportParseError("expected frame size value");
8320 return false;
8321 }
8322
8323 if (!FrameSize->evaluateAsAbsolute(FrameSizeVal)) {
8324 reportParseError("frame size not an absolute expression");
8325 return false;
8326 }
8327
8328 if (Parser.getTok().is(AsmToken::Comma))
8329 Parser.Lex();
8330 else {
8331 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected comma");
8332 return false;
8333 }
8334
8335 // Parse the return register.
8336 TmpReg.clear();
8337 ResTy = parseAnyRegister(TmpReg);
8338 if (ResTy == MatchOperand_NoMatch || ResTy == MatchOperand_ParseFail) {
8339 reportParseError("expected return register");
8340 return false;
8341 }
8342
8343 MipsOperand &ReturnRegOpnd = static_cast<MipsOperand &>(*TmpReg[0]);
8344 if (!ReturnRegOpnd.isGPRAsmReg()) {
8345 reportParseError(ReturnRegOpnd.getStartLoc(),
8346 "expected general purpose register");
8347 return false;
8348 }
8349
8350 // If this is not the end of the statement, report an error.
8351 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
8352 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
8353 return false;
8354 }
8355
8356 getTargetStreamer().emitFrame(StackReg, FrameSizeVal,
8357 ReturnRegOpnd.getGPR32Reg());
8358 IsCpRestoreSet = false;
8359 return false;
8360 }
8361
8362 if (IDVal == ".set") {
8363 parseDirectiveSet();
8364 return false;
8365 }
8366
8367 if (IDVal == ".mask" || IDVal == ".fmask") {
8368 // .mask bitmask, frame_offset
8369 // bitmask: One bit for each register used.
8370 // frame_offset: Offset from Canonical Frame Address ($sp on entry) where
8371 // first register is expected to be saved.
8372 // Examples:
8373 // .mask 0x80000000, -4
8374 // .fmask 0x80000000, -4
8375 //
8376
8377 // Parse the bitmask
8378 const MCExpr *BitMask;
8379 int64_t BitMaskVal;
8380
8381 if (Parser.parseExpression(BitMask)) {
8382 reportParseError("expected bitmask value");
8383 return false;
8384 }
8385
8386 if (!BitMask->evaluateAsAbsolute(BitMaskVal)) {
8387 reportParseError("bitmask not an absolute expression");
8388 return false;
8389 }
8390
8391 if (Parser.getTok().is(AsmToken::Comma))
8392 Parser.Lex();
8393 else {
8394 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected comma");
8395 return false;
8396 }
8397
8398 // Parse the frame_offset
8399 const MCExpr *FrameOffset;
8400 int64_t FrameOffsetVal;
8401
8402 if (Parser.parseExpression(FrameOffset)) {
8403 reportParseError("expected frame offset value");
8404 return false;
8405 }
8406
8407 if (!FrameOffset->evaluateAsAbsolute(FrameOffsetVal)) {
8408 reportParseError("frame offset not an absolute expression");
8409 return false;
8410 }
8411
8412 // If this is not the end of the statement, report an error.
8413 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
8414 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
8415 return false;
8416 }
8417
8418 if (IDVal == ".mask")
8419 getTargetStreamer().emitMask(BitMaskVal, FrameOffsetVal);
8420 else
8421 getTargetStreamer().emitFMask(BitMaskVal, FrameOffsetVal);
8422 return false;
8423 }
8424
8425 if (IDVal == ".nan")
8426 return parseDirectiveNaN();
8427
8428 if (IDVal == ".gpword") {
8429 parseDirectiveGpWord();
8430 return false;
8431 }
8432
8433 if (IDVal == ".gpdword") {
8434 parseDirectiveGpDWord();
8435 return false;
8436 }
8437
8438 if (IDVal == ".dtprelword") {
8439 parseDirectiveDtpRelWord();
8440 return false;
8441 }
8442
8443 if (IDVal == ".dtpreldword") {
8444 parseDirectiveDtpRelDWord();
8445 return false;
8446 }
8447
8448 if (IDVal == ".tprelword") {
8449 parseDirectiveTpRelWord();
8450 return false;
8451 }
8452
8453 if (IDVal == ".tpreldword") {
8454 parseDirectiveTpRelDWord();
8455 return false;
8456 }
8457
8458 if (IDVal == ".option") {
8459 parseDirectiveOption();
8460 return false;
8461 }
8462
8463 if (IDVal == ".abicalls") {
8464 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveAbiCalls();
8465 if (Parser.getTok().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
8466 Error(Parser.getTok().getLoc(),
8467 "unexpected token, expected end of statement");
8468 }
8469 return false;
8470 }
8471
8472 if (IDVal == ".cpsetup") {
8473 parseDirectiveCPSetup();
8474 return false;
8475 }
8476 if (IDVal == ".cpreturn") {
8477 parseDirectiveCPReturn();
8478 return false;
8479 }
8480 if (IDVal == ".module") {
8481 parseDirectiveModule();
8482 return false;
8483 }
8484 if (IDVal == ".llvm_internal_mips_reallow_module_directive") {
8485 parseInternalDirectiveReallowModule();
8486 return false;
8487 }
8488 if (IDVal == ".insn") {
8489 parseInsnDirective();
8490 return false;
8491 }
8492 if (IDVal == ".rdata") {
8493 parseRSectionDirective(".rodata");
8494 return false;
8495 }
8496 if (IDVal == ".sbss") {
8497 parseSSectionDirective(IDVal, ELF::SHT_NOBITS);
8498 return false;
8499 }
8500 if (IDVal == ".sdata") {
8501 parseSSectionDirective(IDVal, ELF::SHT_PROGBITS);
8502 return false;
8503 }
8504
8505 return true;
8506}
8507
8508bool MipsAsmParser::parseInternalDirectiveReallowModule() {
8509 // If this is not the end of the statement, report an error.
8510 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
8511 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
8512 return false;
8513 }
8514
8515 getTargetStreamer().reallowModuleDirective();
8516
8517 getParser().Lex(); // Eat EndOfStatement token.
8518 return false;
8519}

8532
8533bool MipsAsmParser::mnemonicIsValid(StringRef Mnemonic, unsigned VariantID) {
8534 // Find the appropriate table for this asm variant.
8535 const MatchEntry *Start, *End;
8536 switch (VariantID) {
8537 default: llvm_unreachable("invalid variant!");
8538 case 0: Start = std::begin(MatchTable0); End = std::end(MatchTable0); break;
8539 }
8540 // Search the table.
8541 auto MnemonicRange = std::equal_range(Start, End, Mnemonic, LessOpcode());
8542 return MnemonicRange.first != MnemonicRange.second;
8543}
